{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864780740,"sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","part":{"id":"prt_d79ca1358001tOpozvoeekz0S3","messageID":"msg_d79c9f005001pkjtulVFxfoH4Q","sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-a83855863b384472be4506762ed91d02","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Extend PicoD's file management capabilities with comprehensive file system manipulation APIs including file deletion, directory creation, file copy/move, permissions modification, and archive operations (tar/zip) for AI agent workspace management. This builds upon AR-015's basic file operations (upload, list, download) with additional REST endpoints for full-featured workspace file management.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Delete request/response structures\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define structures for file/directory deletion request and response.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: DeleteRequest struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `DeleteRequest` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path` (wildcard path from URL)\n26:   - `Recursive bool` with JSON tag `recursive` (for directory deletion)\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: DeleteResponse struct definition\n29: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n30: - **WHEN** reading the `DeleteResponse` struct\n31: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n32:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path`\n33:   - `Deleted bool` with JSON tag `deleted`\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: Delete handler\n38: \n39: The system SHALL implement file/directory deletion handler with recursive support.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler path extraction\n42: - **GIVEN** DELETE request to `/api/files/*path`\n43: - **WHEN** DeleteFileHandler processes request\n44: - **THEN** `c.Param(\"path\")` SHALL extract wildcard path\n45: - AND leading `/` SHALL be stripped from path\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler path sanitization\n48: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n49: - **WHEN** processing delete path\n50: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, strippedPath)` SHALL be called\n51: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if path escape detected\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler file existence check\n54: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n55: - **WHEN** checking path\n56: - **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n57: - AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if path not found\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler file deletion\n60: - **GIVEN** path is a regular file\n61: - **WHEN** DeleteFileHandler processes request\n62: - **THEN** `os.Remove(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n63: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `DeleteResponse`\n64: - AND `Deleted` SHALL be `true`\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler directory deletion with recursive flag\n67: - **GIVEN** path is a directory AND `Recursive` is `true`\n68: - **WHEN** DeleteFileHandler processes request\n69: - **THEN** `os.RemoveAll(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n70: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `DeleteResponse`\n71: - AND `Deleted` SHALL be `true`\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler directory deletion without recursive flag\n74: - **GIVEN** path is a directory AND `Recursive` is `false`\n75: - **WHEN** DeleteFileHandler processes request\n76: - **THEN** `os.Remove(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n77: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if directory is non-empty\n78: - AND error message SHALL indicate directory is not empty\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler empty directory deletion\n81: - **GIVEN** path is an empty directory AND `Recursive` is `false`\n82: - **WHEN** DeleteFileHandler processes request\n83: - **THEN** `os.Remove(sanitizedPath)` SHALL succeed\n84: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Create directory request/response structures\n89: \n90: The system SHALL define structures for directory creation request and response.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryRequest struct definition\n93: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n94: - **WHEN** reading the `CreateDirectoryRequest` struct\n95: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n96:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path` and `binding:\"required\"`\n97:   - `Mode string` with JSON tag `mode` (optional octal string)\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryResponse struct definition\n100: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n101: - **WHEN** reading the `CreateDirectoryResponse` struct\n102: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n103:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path`\n104:   - `Mode string` with JSON tag `mode`\n105:   - `Created bool` with JSON tag `created`\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: Create directory handler\n110: \n111: The system SHALL implement directory creation handler with nested support.\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler request binding\n114: - **GIVEN** POST request to `/api/files/directory`\n115: - **WHEN** CreateDirectoryHandler processes request\n116: - **THEN** `CreateDirectoryRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n117: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler path sanitization\n120: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n121: - **WHEN** processing directory path\n122: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Path)` SHALL be called\n123: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if path escape detected\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler mode parsing\n126: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n127: - **WHEN** parsing directory mode\n128: - **THEN** `parseFileMode(req.Mode)` SHALL be called\n129: - AND default mode SHALL be `defaultDirMode` (`0755`) if mode empty/invalid\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler nested directory creation\n132: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n133: - **WHEN** creating directory\n134: - **THEN** `os.MkdirAll(sanitizedPath, os.FileMode(mode))` SHALL be called\n135: - AND parent directories SHALL be created if not existing\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler already exists\n138: - **GIVEN** directory already exists\n139: - **WHEN** CreateDirectoryHandler processes request\n140: - **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n141: - AND `Created` SHALL be `false`\n142: - AND existing directory mode SHALL be preserved\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler response\n145: - **GIVEN** successful directory creation\n146: - **WHEN** CreateDirectoryHandler completes\n147: - **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n148: - AND `CreateDirectoryResponse` SHALL include path and mode\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ### Requirement: Copy request/response structures\n153: \n154: The system SHALL define structures for file/directory copy request and response.\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: CopyRequest struct definition\n157: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n158: - **WHEN** reading the `CopyRequest` struct\n159: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n160:   - `Source string` with JSON tag `source` and `binding:\"required\"`\n161:   - `Dest string` with JSON tag `dest` and `binding:\"required\"`\n162: \n163: #### Scenario: CopyResponse struct definition\n164: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n165: - **WHEN** reading the `CopyResponse` struct\n166: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n167:   - `Source string` with JSON tag `source`\n168:   - `Dest string` with JSON tag `dest`\n169:   - `Copied bool` with JSON tag `copied`\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ### Requirement: Copy handler\n174: \n175: The system SHALL implement file/directory copy handler with recursive support.\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler request binding\n178: - **GIVEN** POST request to `/api/files/copy`\n179: - **WHEN** CopyFileHandler processes request\n180: - **THEN** `CopyRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n181: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler source sanitization\n184: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n185: - **WHEN** processing source path\n186: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Source)` SHALL be called\n187: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if source path escape detected\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler destination sanitization\n190: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n191: - **WHEN** processing destination path\n192: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Dest)` SHALL be called\n193: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if destination path escape detected\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler source existence check\n196: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n197: - **WHEN** checking source path\n198: - **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedSource)` SHALL be called\n199: - AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if source not found\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler file copy\n202: - **GIVEN** source is a regular file\n203: - **WHEN** CopyFileHandler processes request\n204: - **THEN** `os.Open(source)` SHALL open source file\n205: - AND `os.Create(dest)` SHALL create destination file\n206: - AND `io.Copy(destFile, srcFile)` SHALL copy content\n207: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `CopyResponse`\n208: \n209: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler directory copy\n210: - **GIVEN** source is a directory\n211: - **WHEN** CopyFileHandler processes request\n212: - **THEN** `filepath.Walk(source, walkFunc)` SHALL be called\n213: - AND walkFunc SHALL copy each file to destination with relative path\n214: - AND directory structure SHALL be preserved\n215: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n216: \n217: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler symlink handling\n218: - **GIVEN** source contains symlinks\n219: - **WHEN** CopyFileHandler processes request\n220: - **THEN** symlinks SHALL be skipped OR target SHALL be resolved\n221: - AND symlink escape SHALL be validated via `sanitizePath`\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler destination exists\n224: - **GIVEN** destination path already exists\n225: - **WHEN** CopyFileHandler processes request\n226: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n227: - AND error message SHALL indicate destination exists\n228: \n229: ---\n230: \n231: ### Requirement: Move request/response structures\n232: \n233: The system SHALL define structures for file/directory move request and response.\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: MoveRequest struct definition\n236: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n237: - **WHEN** reading the `MoveRequest` struct\n238: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n239:   - `Source string` with JSON tag `source` and `binding:\"required\"`\n240:   - `Dest string` with JSON tag `dest` and `binding:\"required\"`\n241: \n242: #### Scenario: MoveResponse struct definition\n243: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n244: - **WHEN** reading the `MoveResponse` struct\n245: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n246:   - `Source string` with JSON tag `source`\n247:   - `Dest string` with JSON tag `dest`\n248:   - `Moved bool` with JSON tag `moved`\n249: \n250: ---\n251: \n252: ### Requirement: Move handler\n253: \n254: The system SHALL implement file/directory move/rename handler.\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler request binding\n257: - **GIVEN** POST request to `/api/files/move`\n258: - **WHEN** MoveFileHandler processes request\n259: - **THEN** `MoveRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n260: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n261: \n262: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler source sanitization\n263: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n264: - **WHEN** processing source path\n265: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Source)` SHALL be called\n266: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if source path escape detected\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler destination sanitization\n269: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n270: - **WHEN** processing destination path\n271: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Dest)` SHALL be called\n272: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if destination path escape detected\n273: \n274: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler source existence check\n275: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n276: - **WHEN** checking source path\n277: - **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedSource)` SHALL be called\n278: - AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if source not found\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler rename operation\n281: - **GIVEN** valid source and destination paths\n282: - **WHEN** MoveFileHandler processes request\n283: - **THEN** `os.Rename(sanitizedSource, sanitizedDest)` SHALL be called\n284: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `MoveResponse`\n285: \n286: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler cross-filesystem move\n287: - **GIVEN** source and destination on different filesystems\n288: - **WHEN** `os.Rename` returns cross-device error\n289: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n290: - AND error message SHALL indicate cross-filesystem move not supported\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler destination exists\n293: - **GIVEN** destination path already exists\n294: - **WHEN** MoveFileHandler processes request\n295: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n296: - AND error message SHALL indicate destination exists\n297: \n298: ---\n299: \n300: ### Requirement: Modify permissions request/response structures\n301: \n302: The system SHALL define structures for permissions modification request and response.\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsRequest struct definition\n305: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n306: - **WHEN** reading the `ModifyPermissionsRequest` struct\n307: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n308:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path` (wildcard path from URL)\n309:   - `Mode string` with JSON tag `mode` and `binding:\"required\"` (octal string)\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsResponse struct definition\n312: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n313: - **WHEN** reading the `ModifyPermissionsResponse` struct\n314: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n315:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path`\n316:   - `OldMode string` with JSON tag `old_mode`\n317:   - `NewMode string` with JSON tag `new_mode`\n318: \n319: ---\n320: \n321: ### Requirement: Modify permissions handler\n322: \n323: The system SHALL implement file/directory permissions modification handler.\n324: \n325: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler path extraction\n326: - **GIVEN** PATCH request to `/api/files/*path`\n327: - **WHEN** ModifyPermissionsHandler processes request\n328: - **THEN** `c.Param(\"path\")` SHALL extract wildcard path\n329: - AND leading `/` SHALL be stripped from path\n330: \n331: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler request binding\n332: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n333: - **WHEN** ModifyPermissionsHandler processes request\n334: - **THEN** `ModifyPermissionsRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n335: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n336: \n337: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler path sanitization\n338: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n339: - **WHEN** processing modify path\n340: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, strippedPath)` SHALL be called\n341: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if path escape detected\n342: \n343: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler file existence check\n344: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n345: - **WHEN** checking path\n346: - **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n347: - AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if path not found\n348: \n349: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler old mode retrieval\n350: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n351: - **WHEN** getting old permissions\n352: - **THEN** `info.Mode().Perm()` SHALL extract current mode\n353: - AND old mode SHALL be formatted as octal string\n354: \n355: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler mode parsing\n356: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n357: - **WHEN** parsing new mode\n358: - **THEN** `parseFileMode(req.Mode)` SHALL be called\n359: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if mode invalid\n360: - AND mode SHALL be validated against `maxFileMode` (`0777`)\n361: \n362: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler chmod operation\n363: - **GIVEN** valid new mode\n364: - **WHEN** ModifyPermissionsHandler processes request\n365: - **THEN** `os.Chmod(sanitizedPath, os.FileMode(newMode))` SHALL be called\n366: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `ModifyPermissionsResponse`\n367: - AND response SHALL include old and new modes\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ### Requirement: Archive request/response structures\n372: \n373: The system SHALL define structures for archive creation request and response.\n374: \n375: #### Scenario: ArchiveRequest struct definition\n376: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n377: - **WHEN** reading the `ArchiveRequest` struct\n378: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n379:   - `SourcePath string` with JSON tag `source_path` and `binding:\"required\"`\n380:   - `DestPath string` with JSON tag `dest_path` and `binding:\"required\"`\n381:   - `Format string` with JSON tag `format` (optional: \"tar\", \"zip\", \"tar.gz\", \"tgz\")\n382: \n383: #### Scenario: ArchiveResponse struct definition\n384: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n385: - **WHEN** reading the `ArchiveResponse` struct\n386: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n387:   - `SourcePath string` with JSON tag `source_path`\n388:   - `DestPath string` with JSON tag `dest_path`\n389:   - `Format string` with JSON tag `format`\n390:   - `Size int64` with JSON tag `size`\n391: \n392: ---\n393: \n394: ### Requirement: Archive handler\n395: \n396: The system SHALL implement archive creation handler with tar/zip support.\n397: \n398: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler request binding\n399: - **GIVEN** POST request to `/api/files/archive`\n400: - **WHEN** ArchiveHandler processes request\n401: - **THEN** `ArchiveRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n402: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n403: \n404: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler source path sanitization\n405: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n406: - **WHEN** processing source path\n407: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.SourcePath)` SHALL be called\n408: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if source path escape detected\n409: \n410: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler destination path sanitization\n411: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n412: - **WHEN** processing destination path\n413: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.DestPath)` SHALL be called\n414: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if destination path escape detected\n415: \n416: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler source existence check\n417: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n418: - **WHEN** checking source path\n419: - **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedSource)` SHALL be called\n420: - AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if source not found\n421: \n422: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler format detection\n423: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n424: - **WHEN** determining archive format\n425: - **THEN** format SHALL be detected from `req.Format` OR `filepath.Ext(req.DestPath)`\n426: - AND supported formats SHALL be `allowedArchiveFormats` (\"tar\", \"zip\", \"tar.gz\", \"tgz\")\n427: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned for unsupported format\n428: \n429: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler tar creation\n430: - **GIVEN** format is \"tar\" or \"tar.gz\" or \"tgz\"\n431: - **WHEN** ArchiveHandler creates archive\n432: - **THEN** `tar.Create` SHALL be used with `archive/tar` package\n433: - AND `filepath.Walk(source, walkFunc)` SHALL walk source\n434: - AND each entry SHALL be added with relative path\n435: - AND gzip SHALL be applied for \"tar.gz\" or \"tgz\" format via `compress/gzip`\n436: \n437: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler zip creation\n438: - **GIVEN** format is \"zip\"\n439: - **WHEN** ArchiveHandler creates archive\n440: - **THEN** `zip.Create` SHALL be used with `archive/zip` package\n441: - AND `filepath.Walk(source, walkFunc)` SHALL walk source\n442: - AND each entry SHALL be added with relative path\n443: \n444: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler response\n445: - **GIVEN** successful archive creation\n446: - **WHEN** ArchiveHandler completes\n447: - **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n448: - AND `ArchiveResponse` SHALL include source path, destination path, format, and size\n449: \n450: ---\n451: \n452: ### Requirement: Extract request/response structures\n453: \n454: The system SHALL define structures for archive extraction request and response.\n455: \n456: #### Scenario: ExtractRequest struct definition\n457: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n458: - **WHEN** reading the `ExtractRequest` struct\n459: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n460:   - `SourcePath string` with JSON tag `source_path` and `binding:\"required\"`\n461:   - `DestPath string` with JSON tag `dest_path` (optional: defaults to parent directory)\n462: \n463: #### Scenario: ExtractResponse struct definition\n464: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n465: - **WHEN** reading the `ExtractResponse` struct\n466: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n467:   - `SourcePath string` with JSON tag `source_path`\n468:   - `DestPath string` with JSON tag `dest_path`\n469:   - `Files []FileEntry` with JSON tag `files` (extracted files list)\n470: \n471: ---\n472: \n473: ### Requirement: Extract handler\n474: \n475: The system SHALL implement archive extraction handler with path escape protection.\n476: \n477: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler request binding\n478: - **GIVEN** POST request to `/api/files/extract`\n479: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler processes request\n480: - **THEN** `ExtractRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n481: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n482: \n483: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler source path sanitization\n484: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n485: - **WHEN** processing source path\n486: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.SourcePath)` SHALL be called\n487: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if source path escape detected\n488: \n489: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler destination path resolution\n490: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n491: - **WHEN** `req.DestPath` is empty\n492: - **THEN** `filepath.Dir(sanitizedSource)` SHALL be used as destination\n493: - WHEN `req.DestPath` is non-empty\n494: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.DestPath)` SHALL be called\n495: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if destination path escape detected\n496: \n497: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler source existence check\n498: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n499: - **WHEN** checking source path\n500: - **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedSource)` SHALL be called\n501: - AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if source not found\n502: \n503: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler size limit check\n504: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n505: - **WHEN** checking archive size\n506: - **THEN** `os.Stat(source).Size()` SHALL get archive size\n507: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if size > `maxArchiveSize` (`100 << 20`)\n508: - AND error message SHALL indicate archive exceeds size limit\n509: \n510: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler format detection\n511: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n512: - **WHEN** determining archive format\n513: - **THEN** format SHALL be detected from `filepath.Ext(req.SourcePath)`\n514: - AND supported formats SHALL be `allowedArchiveFormats`\n515: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned for unsupported format\n516: \n517: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler tar extraction\n518: - **GIVEN** format is \"tar\" or \"tar.gz\" or \"tgz\"\n519: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler extracts archive\n520: - **THEN** `tar.NewReader` SHALL be used with `archive/tar` package\n521: - AND gzip SHALL be decompressed for \"tar.gz\" or \"tgz\" via `compress/gzip`\n522: - AND each entry SHALL be extracted to destination\n523: \n524: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler zip extraction\n525: - **GIVEN** format is \"zip\"\n526: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler extracts archive\n527: - **THEN** `zip.OpenReader` SHALL be used with `archive/zip` package\n528: - AND each entry SHALL be extracted to destination\n529: \n530: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler entry path sanitization\n531: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n532: - **WHEN** extracting each archive entry\n533: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(destination, entry.Name)` SHALL be called for each entry path\n534: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if entry path escapes workspace\n535: - AND entry path SHALL reject `..` components\n536: \n537: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler directory entry creation\n538: - **GIVEN** archive entry is a directory\n539: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler extracts entry\n540: - **THEN** `os.MkdirAll(entryPath, entry.Mode)` SHALL create directory\n541: - AND nested directories SHALL be created\n542: \n543: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler file entry creation\n544: - **GIVEN** archive entry is a file\n545: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler extracts entry\n546: - **THEN** `os.Create(entryPath)` SHALL create file\n547: - AND entry content SHALL be written via `io.Copy`\n548: - AND file mode SHALL be set via `os.Chmod`\n549: \n550: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler response\n551: - **GIVEN** successful extraction\n552: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler completes\n553: - **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n554: - AND `ExtractResponse` SHALL include source path, destination path, and extracted files list\n555: \n556: ---\n557: \n558: ### Requirement: Route registration extension\n559: \n560: The system SHALL extend route registration with new file management endpoints.\n561: \n562: #### Scenario: New file management routes registration\n563: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n564: - **WHEN** registering routes\n565: - **THEN** `/api/files/*path` SHALL be registered with `DeleteFileHandler` (DELETE)\n566: - AND `/api/files/directory` SHALL be registered with `CreateDirectoryHandler` (POST)\n567: - AND `/api/files/copy` SHALL be registered with `CopyFileHandler` (POST)\n568: - AND `/api/files/move` SHALL be registered with `MoveFileHandler` (POST)\n569: - AND `/api/files/*path` SHALL be registered with `ModifyPermissionsHandler` (PATCH)\n570: - AND `/api/files/archive` SHALL be registered with `ArchiveHandler` (POST)\n571: - AND `/api/files/extract` SHALL be registered with `ExtractHandler` (POST)\n572: - AND all routes SHALL use existing JWT auth middleware\n573: \n574: ---\n575: \n576: ### Requirement: Constants\n577: \n578: The system SHALL define constants for file management behavior configuration.\n579: \n580: #### Scenario: defaultDirMode constant\n581: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n582: - **WHEN** reading constants\n583: - **THEN** `defaultDirMode` SHALL be `0755`\n584: \n585: #### Scenario: maxArchiveSize constant\n586: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n587: - **WHEN** reading constants\n588: - **THEN** `maxArchiveSize` SHALL be `100 << 20` (100 MiB)\n589: \n590: #### Scenario: allowedArchiveFormats constant\n591: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n592: - **WHEN** reading constants\n593: - **THEN** `allowedArchiveFormats` SHALL be `[\"tar\", \"zip\", \"tar.gz\", \"tgz\"]`\n594: \n595: ---\n596: \n597: ### Requirement: Error handling\n598: \n599: The system SHALL handle errors with appropriate HTTP status codes and messages.\n600: \n601: #### Scenario: Delete non-empty directory without recursive error\n602: - **GIVEN** directory is non-empty AND `Recursive` is `false`\n603: - **WHEN** delete fails\n604: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n605: - AND body SHALL indicate directory is not empty\n606: \n607: #### Scenario: Cross-filesystem move error\n608: - **GIVEN** `os.Rename` returns cross-device error\n609: - **WHEN** MoveFileHandler encounters error\n610: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n611: - AND body SHALL indicate cross-filesystem move not supported\n612: \n613: #### Scenario: Archive size exceeded error\n614: - **GIVEN** archive size > `maxArchiveSize`\n615: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler detects size violation\n616: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n617: - AND body SHALL indicate archive exceeds size limit\n618: \n619: #### Scenario: Unsupported archive format error\n620: - **GIVEN** unsupported archive format\n621: - **WHEN** ArchiveHandler or ExtractHandler detects format\n622: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n623: - AND body SHALL indicate unsupported format\n624: \n625: #### Scenario: Archive entry path escape error\n626: - **GIVEN** archive entry path escapes workspace\n627: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler detects path escape\n628: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n629: - AND body SHALL indicate invalid entry path\n630: \n631: ---\n632: \n633: ## Constants Summary\n634: \n635: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n636: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n637: | `defaultDirMode` | `0755` | `files.go` | Default directory creation mode |\n638: | `maxArchiveSize` | `100 << 20` | `archive.go` | Maximum archive size for extraction (100 MiB) |\n639: | `allowedArchiveFormats` | `[\"tar\", \"zip\", \"tar.gz\", \"tgz\"]` | `archive.go` | Supported archive formats |\n640: \n641: ---\n642: \n643: ## API Endpoints Summary\n644: \n645: | Endpoint | Method | Auth | Handler |\n646: |----------|--------|------|---------|\n647: | `/api/files/*path` | DELETE | JWT | `DeleteFileHandler` |\n648: | `/api/files/directory` | POST | JWT | `CreateDirectoryHandler` |\n649: | `/api/files/copy` | POST | JWT | `CopyFileHandler` |\n650: | `/api/files/move` | POST | JWT | `MoveFileHandler` |\n651: | `/api/files/*path` | PATCH | JWT | `ModifyPermissionsHandler` |\n652: | `/api/files/archive` | POST | JWT | `ArchiveHandler` |\n653: | `/api/files/extract` | POST | JWT | `ExtractHandler` |\n654: \n655: ---\n656: \n657: ## File Changes Summary\n658: \n659: | File | Action | Description |\n660: |------|--------|-------------|\n661: | `pkg/picod/files.go` | Extend | Add `DeleteRequest`, `DeleteResponse`, `CreateDirectoryRequest`, `CreateDirectoryResponse`, `CopyRequest`, `CopyResponse`, `MoveRequest`, `MoveResponse`, `ModifyPermissionsRequest`, `ModifyPermissionsResponse`, and handlers |\n662: | `pkg/picod/archive.go` | Create | `ArchiveRequest`, `ArchiveResponse`, `ExtractRequest`, `ExtractResponse`, `ArchiveHandler`, `ExtractHandler` |\n663: | `pkg/picod/server.go` | Extend | Register new file management routes |\n664: | `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` | Extend | Unit tests for new handlers |\n665: \n666: ---\n667: \n668: ## References\n669: \n670: - `changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md` — Original PicoD implementation\n671: - `pkg/picod/sanitize.go` — Path security logic\n672: - [Go archive/tar](https://pkg.go.dev/archive/tar)\n673: - [Go archive/zip](https://pkg.go.dev/archive/zip)\n674: - [Go compress/gzip](https://pkg.go.dev/compress/gzip)\n\n(End of file - total 674 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n\n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nExtend PicoD's file management capabilities with comprehensive file system manipulation APIs including file deletion, directory creation, file copy/move, permissions modification, and archive operations (tar/zip) for AI agent workspace management. This builds upon AR-015's basic file operations (upload, list, download) with additional REST endpoints for full-featured workspace file management.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Delete request/response structures\n\nThe system SHALL define structures for file/directory deletion request and response.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775864780719,"end":1775864780737}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864780743,"sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","part":{"id":"prt_d79ca1794001aDdnlXNzQdoPna","messageID":"msg_d79c9f005001pkjtulVFxfoH4Q","sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-ff9abd5017484883864d0e838d3ef932","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the PicoD (Pico Daemon) HTTP daemon that runs inside sandbox pods to provide secure command execution and file management within a configurable workspace jail. PicoD exposes REST APIs protected by RS256 JWT authentication, enabling AI agents and code interpreters to execute shell commands and manage workspace files with timeout control, path traversal protection, and workspace jail enforcement.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Config type definition\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define `Config` struct for PicoD server configuration with CLI flag parsing.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Config struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/config.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `Config` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `Port int` for HTTP listening port (default 8080)\n26:   - `Workspace string` for workspace directory path (default empty → CWD)\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: CLI flag parsing\n29: - **GIVEN** `cmd/picod/main.go`\n30: - **WHEN** parsing CLI flags\n31: - **THEN** `-port` flag SHALL be registered with default value `8080`\n32: - AND `-workspace` flag SHALL be registered with default value empty string\n33: - AND klog flags SHALL be registered via `klog.InitFlags(nil)`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Workspace resolution\n36: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n37: - **WHEN** `Config.Workspace` is empty\n38: - **THEN** `os.Getwd()` SHALL be called to get current working directory\n39: - AND result SHALL be used as workspace root\n40: - WHEN `Config.Workspace` is non-empty relative path\n41: - **THEN** `filepath.Abs(workspace)` SHALL resolve to absolute path\n42: - AND resolved path SHALL be used as workspace root\n43: \n44: ---\n45: \n46: ### Requirement: Server type definition\n47: \n48: The system SHALL define `Server` struct as HTTP server with Gin engine for PicoD API routing.\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Server struct definition\n51: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n52: - **WHEN** reading the `Server` struct\n53: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n54:   - `config *Config` for server configuration\n55:   - `engine *gin.Engine` for Gin HTTP framework\n56:   - `httpServer *http.Server` for underlying HTTP server\n57:   - `authManager *AuthManager` for JWT authentication\n58:   - `workspace string` for resolved workspace directory\n59:   - `startTime time.Time` for uptime tracking\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: NewServer constructor\n62: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n63: - **WHEN** calling `NewServer(config *Config)`\n64: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*Server` with:\n65:   - `engine` initialized with `gin.New()`\n66:   - `gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)` set\n67:   - `engine.Use(gin.Logger(), gin.Recovery())` middleware applied\n68:   - `workspace` resolved via workspace resolution logic\n69:   - `startTime` set to `time.Now()`\n70:   - `authManager` initialized via `NewAuthManager()`\n71: - AND error SHALL be returned if workspace resolution fails\n72: - AND error SHALL be returned if `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var is missing/invalid\n73: \n74: #### Scenario: HTTP server configuration\n75: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n76: - **WHEN** initializing `httpServer`\n77: - **THEN** `http.Server` SHALL be configured with:\n78:   - `Addr` = `fmt.Sprintf(\":%d\", config.Port)`\n79:   - `Handler` = `engine`\n80:   - `ReadHeaderTimeout` = `10 * time.Second`\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: Run method\n83: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n84: - **WHEN** calling `server.Run(ctx)`\n85: - **THEN** `httpServer.ListenAndServe()` SHALL be called\n86: - AND error SHALL be logged via `klog.Error` on failure\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ### Requirement: Route registration\n91: \n92: The system SHALL register routes for API endpoints and health check.\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: Health route\n95: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n96: - **WHEN** registering routes\n97: - **THEN** `/health` SHALL be registered with `HealthCheckHandler`\n98: - AND `/health` SHALL NOT require JWT authentication\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: API routes with authentication\n101: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n102: - **WHEN** registering routes\n103: - **THEN** `/api` group SHALL be created\n104: - AND `authManager.AuthMiddleware()` SHALL be applied to `/api` group\n105: - AND `/api/execute` SHALL be registered with `ExecuteHandler` (POST)\n106: - AND `/api/files` SHALL be registered with `UploadFileHandler` (POST)\n107: - AND `/api/files` SHALL be registered with `ListFilesHandler` (GET)\n108: - AND `/api/files/*path` SHALL be registered with `DownloadFileHandler` (GET)\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ### Requirement: AuthManager type definition\n113: \n114: The system SHALL define `AuthManager` for RSA JWT authentication with public key loading.\n115: \n116: #### Scenario: AuthManager struct definition\n117: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n118: - **WHEN** reading the `AuthManager` struct\n119: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n120:   - `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey` for RSA public key\n121:   - `mutex sync.RWMutex` for thread-safe public key access\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: PublicKeyEnvVar constant\n124: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n125: - **WHEN** reading constants\n126: - **THEN** `PublicKeyEnvVar` SHALL be `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"`\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: NewAuthManager constructor\n129: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n130: - **WHEN** calling `NewAuthManager()`\n131: - **THEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` SHALL be called\n132: - AND `publicKey` SHALL be set from PEM public key\n133: - AND error SHALL be returned if env var is missing\n134: - AND error SHALL be returned if PEM decode fails\n135: - AND error SHALL be returned if PKIX parse fails\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: LoadPublicKeyFromEnv PEM format\n138: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n139: - **WHEN** loading public key from PEM\n140: - **THEN** PEM block type SHALL be `\"PUBLIC KEY\"` (PKIX format)\n141: - AND `x509.ParsePKIXPublicKey(block.Bytes)` SHALL be used\n142: - AND result SHALL be type-asserted to `*rsa.PublicKey`\n143: - AND PKCS#1 format (`\"RSA PUBLIC KEY\"`) SHALL NOT be supported\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ### Requirement: JWT authentication middleware\n148: \n149: The system SHALL implement JWT authentication middleware with RS256 validation.\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware Bearer extraction\n152: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n153: - **WHEN** processing request with `Authorization` header\n154: - **THEN** header SHALL be extracted via `c.GetHeader(\"Authorization\")`\n155: - AND prefix `\"Bearer \"` SHALL be stripped\n156: - AND token string SHALL be parsed via `jwt.Parse(tokenString, keyFunc, options...)`\n157: \n158: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware missing header\n159: - **GIVEN** request without `Authorization` header\n160: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware processes request\n161: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n162: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"missing authorization header\"}`\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware invalid token format\n165: - **GIVEN** request with malformed JWT token\n166: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware processes request\n167: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n168: - AND body SHALL indicate invalid token format\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware RSA method validation\n171: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n172: - **WHEN** JWT keyFunc validates signing method\n173: - **THEN** `token.Method` SHALL be type-asserted to `*jwt.SigningMethodRSA`\n174: - AND non-RSA methods (HS256, etc.) SHALL be rejected\n175: - AND HTTP `401` SHALL be returned for non-RSA methods\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware expiration enforcement\n178: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n179: - **WHEN** parsing JWT\n180: - **THEN** `jwt.WithExpirationRequired()` SHALL be applied\n181: - AND `jwt.WithIssuedAt()` SHALL be applied\n182: - AND `jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute)` SHALL be applied\n183: - AND expired tokens SHALL be rejected with HTTP `401`\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware MaxBytesReader application\n186: - **GIVEN** valid JWT token\n187: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware completes validation\n188: - **THEN** `http.MaxBytesReader(c.Writer, c.Request.Body, MaxBodySize)` SHALL be applied\n189: - AND `MaxBodySize` SHALL be `32 << 20` (32 MiB)\n190: \n191: ---\n192: \n193: ### Requirement: Execute request/response structures\n194: \n195: The system SHALL define structures for command execution request and response.\n196: \n197: #### Scenario: ExecuteRequest struct definition\n198: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/execute.go`\n199: - **WHEN** reading the `ExecuteRequest` struct\n200: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n201:   - `Command []string` with JSON tag `command` and `binding:\"required\"`\n202:   - `Timeout string` with JSON tag `timeout` (optional duration string)\n203:   - `WorkingDir string` with JSON tag `working_dir` (optional)\n204:   - `Env map[string]string` with JSON tag `env` (optional)\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: ExecuteResponse struct definition\n207: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/execute.go`\n208: - **WHEN** reading the `ExecuteResponse` struct\n209: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n210:   - `Stdout string` with JSON tag `stdout`\n211:   - `Stderr string` with JSON tag `stderr`\n212:   - `ExitCode int` with JSON tag `exit_code`\n213:   - `Duration float64` with JSON tag `duration` (seconds)\n214:   - `StartTime time.Time` with JSON tag `start_time`\n215:   - `EndTime time.Time` with JSON tag `end_time`\n216: \n217: #### Scenario: TimeoutExitCode constant\n218: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/execute.go`\n219: - **WHEN** reading constants\n220: - **THEN** `TimeoutExitCode` SHALL be `124`\n221: \n222: ---\n223: \n224: ### Requirement: Execute handler\n225: \n226: The system SHALL implement command execution handler with timeout and context control.\n227: \n228: #### Scenario: ExecuteHandler binds request\n229: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/execute.go`\n230: - **WHEN** processing POST request to `/api/execute`\n231: - **THEN** `ExecuteRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n232: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n233: \n234: #### Scenario: ExecuteHandler empty command\n235: - **GIVEN** `ExecuteRequest` with empty `Command` array\n236: - **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n237: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n238: - AND body SHALL indicate missing command\n239: \n240: #### Scenario: ExecuteHandler timeout parsing\n241: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/execute.go`\n242: - **WHEN** `req.Timeout` is non-empty\n243: - **THEN** `time.ParseDuration(req.Timeout)` SHALL be called\n244: - AND default timeout SHALL be `60 * time.Second` if empty or invalid\n245: - AND invalid timeout string SHALL NOT cause error (use default)\n246: \n247: #### Scenario: ExecuteHandler context timeout\n248: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/execute.go`\n249: - **WHEN** executing command\n250: - **THEN** `context.WithTimeout(ctx, timeout)` SHALL be called\n251: - AND `exec.CommandContext(timeoutCtx, req.Command[0], req.Command[1:]...)` SHALL be used\n252: \n253: #### Scenario: ExecuteHandler working directory\n254: - **GIVEN** `req.WorkingDir` is non-empty\n255: - **WHEN** executing command\n256: - **THEN** `cmd.Dir` SHALL be set to sanitized working directory\n257: - AND path SHALL be validated via `sanitizePath`\n258: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if path escape detected\n259: \n260: #### Scenario: ExecuteHandler environment augmentation\n261: - **GIVEN** `req.Env` is non-empty\n262: - **WHEN** executing command\n263: - **THEN** `cmd.Env` SHALL be set to `os.Environ()` augmented with `req.Env` entries\n264: - AND existing env vars SHALL be overwritten by `req.Env` keys\n265: \n266: #### Scenario: ExecuteHandler stdout/stderr capture\n267: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/execute.go`\n268: - **WHEN** executing command\n269: - **THEN** stdout SHALL be captured via `bytes.Buffer`\n270: - AND stderr SHALL be captured via `bytes.Buffer`\n271: - AND `cmd.Stdout = stdoutBuffer`\n272: - AND `cmd.Stderr = stderrBuffer`\n273: - AND stdin SHALL NOT be connected (nil)\n274: \n275: #### Scenario: ExecuteHandler successful execution\n276: - **GIVEN** command that completes successfully\n277: - **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n278: - **THEN** `ExecuteResponse` SHALL be returned with:\n279:   - `Stdout` = captured stdout content\n280:   - `Stderr` = captured stderr content\n281:   - `ExitCode` = process exit code\n282:   - `Duration` = execution duration in seconds\n283:   - `StartTime` = command start timestamp\n284:   - `EndTime` = command end timestamp\n285: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n286: \n287: #### Scenario: ExecuteHandler timeout exceeded\n288: - **GIVEN** command that exceeds timeout\n289: - **WHEN** context deadline is exceeded\n290: - **THEN** process SHALL be killed by context cancellation\n291: - AND `ExitCode` SHALL be `TimeoutExitCode` (`124`)\n292: - AND `Stderr` SHALL indicate `\"command timed out\"`\n293: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned (successful response with timeout exit code)\n294: \n295: ---\n296: \n297: ### Requirement: File info and upload structures\n298: \n299: The system SHALL define structures for file information and upload requests.\n300: \n301: #### Scenario: FileInfo struct definition\n302: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n303: - **WHEN** reading the `FileInfo` struct\n304: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n305:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path` (relative to workspace)\n306:   - `Size int64` with JSON tag `size`\n307:   - `Mode string` with JSON tag `mode` (octal string)\n308:   - `Modified time.Time` with JSON tag `modified`\n309: \n310: #### Scenario: UploadFileRequest struct definition\n311: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n312: - **WHEN** reading the `UploadFileRequest` struct\n313: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n314:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path` and `binding:\"required\"`\n315:   - `Content string` with JSON tag `content` and `binding:\"required\"` (Base64 encoded)\n316:   - `Mode string` with JSON tag `mode` (optional octal string)\n317: \n318: #### Scenario: FileEntry struct definition\n319: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n320: - **WHEN** reading the `FileEntry` struct\n321: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n322:   - `Name string` with JSON tag `name`\n323:   - `Size int64` with JSON tag `size`\n324:   - `Modified time.Time` with JSON tag `modified`\n325:   - `Mode string` with JSON tag `mode` (octal string)\n326:   - `IsDir bool` with JSON tag `is_dir`\n327: \n328: #### Scenario: ListFilesResponse struct definition\n329: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n330: - **WHEN** reading the `ListFilesResponse` struct\n331: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n332:   - `Files []FileEntry` with JSON tag `files`\n333:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path` (directory path)\n334: \n335: ---\n336: \n337: ### Requirement: File upload handler\n338: \n339: The system SHALL implement file upload handler supporting multipart and JSON/Base64 formats.\n340: \n341: #### Scenario: UploadFileHandler content type detection\n342: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n343: - **WHEN** processing POST request to `/api/files`\n344: - **THEN** Content-Type SHALL be inspected via `c.ContentType()`\n345: - AND `\"multipart/\"` prefix SHALL trigger multipart handling\n346: - AND other content types SHALL trigger JSON handling\n347: \n348: #### Scenario: UploadFileHandler multipart path extraction\n349: - **GIVEN** multipart request\n350: - **WHEN** UploadFileHandler processes request\n351: - **THEN** `c.PostForm(\"path\")` SHALL extract path field\n352: - AND path SHALL be required (HTTP `400` if missing)\n353: \n354: #### Scenario: UploadFileHandler multipart file extraction\n355: - **GIVEN** multipart request\n356: - **WHEN** UploadFileHandler processes request\n357: - **THEN** `c.FormFile(\"file\")` SHALL extract uploaded file\n358: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if file missing\n359: \n360: #### Scenario: UploadFileHandler multipart mode extraction\n361: - **GIVEN** multipart request\n362: - **WHEN** UploadFileHandler processes request\n363: - **THEN** `c.PostForm(\"mode\")` SHALL extract optional mode field\n364: - AND default mode SHALL be `0644` if mode missing/invalid\n365: \n366: #### Scenario: UploadFileHandler JSON Base64 decoding\n367: - **GIVEN** JSON request\n368: - **WHEN** UploadFileHandler processes request\n369: - **THEN** `UploadFileRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n370: - AND `base64.StdEncoding.DecodeString(req.Content)` SHALL decode content\n371: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if Base64 decode fails\n372: \n373: #### Scenario: UploadFileHandler path sanitization\n374: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n375: - **WHEN** processing file path\n376: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Path)` SHALL be called\n377: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if path escape detected\n378: \n379: #### Scenario: UploadFileHandler parent directory creation\n380: - **GIVEN** upload path with parent directories\n381: - **WHEN** writing file\n382: - **THEN** `os.MkdirAll(filepath.Dir(sanitizedPath), 0755)` SHALL create parents\n383: - AND parent directories SHALL use mode `0755`\n384: \n385: #### Scenario: UploadFileHandler file mode parsing\n386: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n387: - **WHEN** parsing file mode\n388: - **THEN** `strconv.ParseUint(modeStr, 8, 32)` SHALL parse octal string\n389: - AND mode SHALL be validated against `maxFileMode` (`0777`)\n390: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if mode > `0777`\n391: - AND default mode SHALL be `0644` if parsing fails\n392: \n393: #### Scenario: UploadFileHandler file writing\n394: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n395: - **WHEN** writing file\n396: - **THEN** `os.WriteFile(sanitizedPath, content, os.FileMode(mode))` SHALL be called\n397: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `FileInfo` response\n398: \n399: ---\n400: \n401: ### Requirement: File list handler\n402: \n403: The system SHALL implement file list handler for directory contents.\n404: \n405: #### Scenario: ListFilesHandler path parameter\n406: - **GIVEN** GET request to `/api/files`\n407: - **WHEN** ListFilesHandler processes request\n408: - **THEN** `c.Query(\"path\")` SHALL extract path parameter\n409: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if path missing\n410: \n411: #### Scenario: ListFilesHandler path sanitization\n412: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n413: - **WHEN** processing list path\n414: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, path)` SHALL be called\n415: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if path escape detected\n416: \n417: #### Scenario: ListFilesHandler directory read\n418: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n419: - **WHEN** listing directory\n420: - **THEN** `os.ReadDir(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n421: - AND HTTP `500` SHALL be returned if directory read fails\n422: \n423: #### Scenario: ListFilesHandler file entry building\n424: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n425: - **WHEN** building file entries\n426: - **THEN** `entry.Info()` SHALL be called for each entry\n427: - AND entries with failed `Info()` SHALL be skipped (not error)\n428: - AND `FileEntry` SHALL be built with:\n429:   - `Name` = entry name\n430:   - `Size` = file size\n431:   - `Modified` = modification time\n432:   - `Mode` = mode as octal string via `fmt.Sprintf(\"%04o\", info.Mode().Perm())`\n433:   - `IsDir` = entry is directory\n434: \n435: #### Scenario: ListFilesHandler response\n436: - **GIVEN** successful directory listing\n437: - **WHEN** ListFilesHandler completes\n438: - **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n439: - AND body SHALL be `ListFilesResponse` with file entries\n440: \n441: ---\n442: \n443: ### Requirement: File download handler\n444: \n445: The system SHALL implement file download handler for single file retrieval.\n446: \n447: #### Scenario: DownloadFileHandler path extraction\n448: - **GIVEN** GET request to `/api/files/*path`\n449: - **WHEN** DownloadFileHandler processes request\n450: - **THEN** `c.Param(\"path\")` SHALL extract wildcard path\n451: - AND leading `/` SHALL be stripped from path\n452: \n453: #### Scenario: DownloadFileHandler path sanitization\n454: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n455: - **WHEN** processing download path\n456: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, strippedPath)` SHALL be called\n457: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if path escape detected\n458: \n459: #### Scenario: DownloadFileHandler file existence check\n460: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n461: - **WHEN** checking path\n462: - **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n463: - AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if path not found\n464: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if path is directory (not file)\n465: \n466: #### Scenario: DownloadFileHandler content type detection\n467: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n468: - **WHEN** setting response headers\n469: - **THEN** `mime.TypeByExtension(filepath.Ext(sanitizedPath))` SHALL detect Content-Type\n470: - AND Content-Type header SHALL be set\n471: - AND Content-Disposition SHALL be set with `filename` attribute\n472: \n473: #### Scenario: DownloadFileHandler file streaming\n474: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n475: - **WHEN** streaming file\n476: - **THEN** `c.File(sanitizedPath)` SHALL stream file content\n477: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n478: \n479: ---\n480: \n481: ### Requirement: Health check handler\n482: \n483: The system SHALL implement unauthenticated health check endpoint.\n484: \n485: #### Scenario: HealthCheckHandler response\n486: - **GIVEN** GET request to `/health`\n487: - **WHEN** HealthCheckHandler processes request\n488: - **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n489: - AND body SHALL be JSON with fields:\n490:   - `status` = `\"ok\"`\n491:   - `service` = `\"PicoD\"`\n492:   - `version` = `\"0.0.1\"`\n493:   - `uptime` = duration since `startTime` formatted as string\n494: \n495: #### Scenario: HealthCheckHandler no authentication\n496: - **GIVEN** `/health` endpoint\n497: - **WHEN** request is processed\n498: - **THEN** JWT authentication SHALL NOT be required\n499: - AND request SHALL proceed without `Authorization` header\n500: \n501: ---\n502: \n503: ### Requirement: Path sanitization\n504: \n505: The system SHALL implement `sanitizePath` function for workspace jail security.\n506: \n507: #### Scenario: sanitizePath workspace symlink resolution\n508: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/sanitize.go`\n509: - **WHEN** sanitizing path\n510: - **THEN** `filepath.EvalSymlinks(workspace)` SHALL resolve workspace directory symlinks\n511: - AND resolved workspace SHALL be used for validation\n512: \n513: #### Scenario: sanitizePath path cleaning\n514: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/sanitize.go`\n515: - **WHEN** cleaning requested path\n516: - **THEN** `filepath.Clean(requestedPath)` SHALL be called\n517: - AND leading `/` SHALL be stripped if path is absolute\n518: - AND `strings.TrimPrefix(cleanedPath, \"/\")` SHALL remove leading slash\n519: \n520: #### Scenario: sanitizePath path joining\n521: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/sanitize.go`\n522: - **WHEN** joining path with workspace\n523: - **THEN** `filepath.Join(workspace, relativePath)` SHALL be called\n524: - AND result SHALL be candidate absolute path\n525: \n526: #### Scenario: sanitizePath traversal check\n527: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/sanitize.go`\n528: - **WHEN** checking for path traversal\n529: - **THEN** `filepath.Rel(workspace, candidatePath)` SHALL compute relative path\n530: - AND relative path starting with `..` SHALL indicate traversal attempt\n531: - AND error SHALL be returned if traversal detected\n532: \n533: #### Scenario: sanitizePath existing path re-validation\n534: - **GIVEN** candidate path that exists on filesystem\n535: - **WHEN** sanitizing path\n536: - **THEN** `filepath.EvalSymlinks(candidatePath)` SHALL resolve symlinks\n537: - AND resolved path SHALL be re-checked against workspace via `filepath.Rel`\n538: - AND error SHALL be returned if resolved path escapes workspace\n539: \n540: #### Scenario: sanitizePath return value\n541: - **GIVEN** valid path within workspace\n542: - **WHEN** sanitizing completes\n543: - **THEN** sanitized absolute path SHALL be returned\n544: - AND path SHALL be guaranteed within workspace jail\n545: \n546: ---\n547: \n548: ### Requirement: Constants\n549: \n550: The system SHALL define constants for PicoD behavior configuration.\n551: \n552: #### Scenario: TimeoutExitCode constant\n553: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/execute.go`\n554: - **WHEN** reading constants\n555: - **THEN** `TimeoutExitCode` SHALL be `124`\n556: \n557: #### Scenario: MaxBodySize constant\n558: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n559: - **WHEN** reading constants\n560: - **THEN** `MaxBodySize` SHALL be `32 << 20` (32 MiB)\n561: \n562: #### Scenario: PublicKeyEnvVar constant\n563: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n564: - **WHEN** reading constants\n565: - **THEN** `PublicKeyEnvVar` SHALL be `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"`\n566: \n567: #### Scenario: maxFileMode constant\n568: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n569: - **WHEN** reading constants\n570: - **THEN** `maxFileMode` SHALL be `0777`\n571: \n572: #### Scenario: Default timeout constant\n573: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/execute.go`\n574: - **WHEN** reading constants\n575: - **THEN** default timeout SHALL be `60 * time.Second`\n576: \n577: #### Scenario: Default file mode constant\n578: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n579: - **WHEN** reading constants\n580: - **THEN** default file mode SHALL be `0644`\n581: \n582: ---\n583: \n584: ### Requirement: Entry point main\n585: \n586: The system SHALL provide `cmd/picod/main.go` entry point.\n587: \n588: #### Scenario: main.go klog initialization\n589: - **GIVEN** `cmd/picod/main.go`\n590: - **WHEN** program starts\n591: - **THEN** `flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")` SHALL be called\n592: - AND `klog.InitFlags(nil)` SHALL register klog flags\n593: - AND `flag.Parse()` SHALL parse all flags\n594: \n595: #### Scenario: main.go config creation\n596: - **GIVEN** `cmd/picod/main.go`\n597: - **WHEN** creating config\n598: - **THEN** `Config` SHALL be created with:\n599:   - `Port` from `-port` flag value\n600:   - `Workspace` from `-workspace` flag value\n601: \n602: #### Scenario: main.go server creation\n603: - **GIVEN** `cmd/picod/main.go`\n604: - **WHEN** creating server\n605: - **THEN** `NewServer(config)` SHALL be called\n606: - AND `klog.Fatalf` SHALL be called if server creation fails\n607: \n608: #### Scenario: main.go server run\n609: - **GIVEN** `cmd/picod/main.go`\n610: - **WHEN** running server\n611: - **THEN** `server.Run(context.Background())` SHALL be called\n612: - AND `klog.InfoS(\"PicoD started\", \"port\", config.Port, \"workspace\", server.workspace)` SHALL log startup\n613: \n614: ---\n615: \n616: ### Requirement: Error handling\n617: \n618: The system SHALL handle errors with appropriate HTTP status codes and messages.\n619: \n620: #### Scenario: JWT authentication error\n621: - **GIVEN** JWT validation failure\n622: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware returns error\n623: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n624: - AND body SHALL be JSON with `error` field\n625: \n626: #### Scenario: Path traversal error\n627: - **GIVEN** path escape detected\n628: - **WHEN** sanitizePath returns error\n629: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n630: - AND body SHALL indicate invalid path\n631: \n632: #### Scenario: File not found error\n633: - **GIVEN** download path not existing\n634: - **WHEN** os.Stat returns error\n635: - **THEN** HTTP `404` SHALL be returned\n636: - AND body SHALL indicate file not found\n637: \n638: #### Scenario: Directory read error\n639: - **GIVEN** os.ReadDir failure\n640: - **WHEN** ListFilesHandler encounters error\n641: - **THEN** HTTP `500` SHALL be returned\n642: - AND body SHALL indicate directory read failure\n643: \n644: #### Scenario: Binding error\n645: - **GIVEN** JSON binding failure\n646: - **WHEN** ShouldBindJSON returns error\n647: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n648: - AND body SHALL indicate invalid request body\n649: \n650: ---\n651: \n652: ## Constants Summary\n653: \n654: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n655: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n656: | `TimeoutExitCode` | `124` | `execute.go` | Exit code when command timeout |\n657: | `MaxBodySize` | `32 << 20` | `auth.go` | Request body size limit (32 MiB) |\n658: | `PublicKeyEnvVar` | `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"` | `auth.go` | Env var for PEM public key |\n659: | `maxFileMode` | `0777` | `files.go` | Maximum file mode permission |\n660: | Default timeout | `60 * time.Second` | `execute.go` | Command timeout when not specified |\n661: | Default file mode | `0644` | `files.go` | File mode when mode invalid/empty |\n662: \n663: ---\n664: \n665: ## Environment Variables\n666: \n667: | Variable | Required | Purpose |\n668: |----------|----------|---------|\n669: | `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` | Yes | PEM-encoded RSA public key (PKIX format) |\n670: \n671: ---\n672: \n673: ## API Endpoints Summary\n674: \n675: | Endpoint | Method | Auth | Handler |\n676: |----------|--------|------|---------|\n677: | `/health` | GET | No | `HealthCheckHandler` |\n678: | `/api/execute` | POST | JWT | `ExecuteHandler` |\n679: | `/api/files` | POST | JWT | `UploadFileHandler` |\n680: | `/api/files` | GET | JWT | `ListFilesHandler` |\n681: | `/api/files/*path` | GET | JWT | `DownloadFileHandler` |\n682: \n683: ---\n684: \n685: ## File Changes Summary\n686: \n687: | File | Action | Description |\n688: |------|--------|-------------|\n689: | `pkg/picod/config.go` | Create | `Config` struct definition |\n690: | `pkg/picod/server.go` | Create | `Server` struct, `NewServer`, `Run`, route registration |\n691: | `pkg/picod/auth.go` | Create | `AuthManager`, `NewAuthManager`, `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv`, `AuthMiddleware` |\n692: | `pkg/picod/execute.go` | Create | `ExecuteRequest`, `ExecuteResponse`, `ExecuteHandler` |\n693: | `pkg/picod/files.go` | Create | `FileInfo`, `UploadFileRequest`, `FileEntry`, `ListFilesResponse`, file handlers |\n694: | `pkg/picod/health.go` | Create | `HealthCheckHandler` |\n695: | `pkg/picod/sanitize.go` | Create | `sanitizePath` function |\n696: | `cmd/picod/main.go` | Create | Entry point with CLI flags |\n697: | `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` | Create | Unit tests |\n698: \n699: ---\n700: \n701: ## References\n702: \n703: - `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client for sandbox pod configuration\n704: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` — `AuthModePicoD` constant\n705: - `pkg/router/jwt.go` — Router JWT issuance (key pair generation)\n706: - `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` — HTTP framework\n707: - `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` — JWT parsing and validation\n\n(End of file - total 707 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API\n\n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the PicoD (Pico Daemon) HTTP daemon that runs inside sandbox pods to provide secure command execution and file management within a configurable workspace jail. PicoD exposes REST APIs protected by RS256 JWT authentication, enabling AI agents and code interpreters to execute shell commands and manage workspace files with timeout control, path traversal protection, and workspace jail enforcement.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Config type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `Config` struct for PicoD server configuration with CLI flag parsing.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775864780722,"end":1775864780741}}}}
