{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864792776,"sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","part":{"id":"prt_d79ca3e8a001FKxYZoCW3ZSGUN","messageID":"msg_d79ca1800001Ai06Q2QJNcX0vR","sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-ee79596f380c4f7ba892802eb74db7f1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter Type Definition\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n10: \n11: ### Requirement: Package structure and registration\n12: \n13: The system SHALL define the `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` with proper package structure, scheme registration, and CRD markers for controller-gen.\n14: \n15: #### Scenario: Package structure exists\n16: - **GIVEN** the repository root at `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n17: - **WHEN** examining `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n18: - **THEN** the directory SHALL contain:\n19:   - `doc.go` with `+k8s:deepcopy-gen=package` marker\n20:   - `register.go` with `SchemeGroupVersion` set to `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n21:   - `codeinterpreter_types.go` with `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types\n22:   - `shared_types.go` with `AuthModeType` enum and `TargetPort` type\n23:   - `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` (generated)\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Scheme group version is correct\n26: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/groupversion_info.go`\n27: - **WHEN** reading the file\n28: - **THEN** `GroupVersion` SHALL be `schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Kind registration\n31: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go`\n32: - **WHEN** reading the file\n33: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreterKind` SHALL be `\"CodeInterpreter\"`\n34: - AND `CodeInterpreterListKind` SHALL be `\"CodeInterpreterList\"`\n35: - AND `CodeInterpreterGroupVersionKind` SHALL be `GroupVersion.WithKind(\"CodeInterpreter\")`\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter type definition\n40: \n41: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreter` as a Kubernetes-style typed object with `TypeMeta`, `ObjectMeta`, `Spec`, and `Status`.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter struct shape\n44: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n45: - **WHEN** reading the `CodeInterpreter` struct definition\n46: - **THEN** the struct SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ObjectMeta` and have `Spec CodeInterpreterSpec` and `Status CodeInterpreterStatus` fields with JSON tags `spec` and `status`\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterList struct shape\n49: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n50: - **WHEN** reading the `CodeInterpreterList` struct definition\n51: - **THEN** the struct SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta`, have `metav1.ListMeta` with JSON tag `metadata`, and `Items []CodeInterpreter` with JSON tag `items`\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: CRD markers on CodeInterpreter\n54: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n55: - **WHEN** examining type-level markers\n56: - **THEN** the `CodeInterpreter` type SHALL have:\n57:   - `+genclient` marker\n58:   - `+k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object` marker\n59:   - `+kubebuilder:object:root=true` marker\n60:   - `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` marker\n61:   - `+kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced` marker\n62:   - `+kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"` marker\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterSpec definition\n67: \n68: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterSpec` with fields for sandbox template, session management, warm pool, and authentication.\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterSpec fields\n71: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n72: - **WHEN** reading the `CodeInterpreterSpec` struct\n73: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n74:   - `Ports []TargetPort` with JSON tag `ports` (optional)\n75:   - `Template *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` with JSON tag `template` (required)\n76:   - `SessionTimeout *metav1.Duration` with JSON tag `sessionTimeout` (optional, default 15m)\n77:   - `MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration` with JSON tag `maxSessionDuration` (optional, default 8h)\n78:   - `WarmPoolSize *int32` with JSON tag `warmPoolSize` (optional)\n79:   - `AuthMode AuthModeType` with JSON tag `authMode` (optional, default picod)\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Template field is required\n82: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n83: - **WHEN** examining the `Template` field markers\n84: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+kubebuilder:validation:Required` marker\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: SessionTimeout default\n87: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n88: - **WHEN** examining the `SessionTimeout` field marker\n89: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"` marker\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: MaxSessionDuration default\n92: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n93: - **WHEN** examining the `MaxSessionDuration` field marker\n94: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"` marker\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: AuthMode enum and default\n97: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n98: - **WHEN** examining the `AuthMode` field marker\n99: - **THEN** it SHALL have:\n100:   - `+kubebuilder:default=picod` marker\n101:   - `+kubebuilder:validation:Enum=picod;none` marker\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate definition\n106: \n107: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` for configuring code interpreter pods.\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate fields\n110: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n111: - **WHEN** reading the `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` struct\n112: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain:\n113:   - `Labels map[string]string` with JSON tag `labels` (optional)\n114:   - `Annotations map[string]string` with JSON tag `annotations` (optional)\n115:   - `RuntimeClassName *string` with JSON tag `runtimeClassName` (optional)\n116:   - `Image string` with JSON tag `image` (optional)\n117:   - `ImagePullPolicy corev1.PullPolicy` with JSON tag `imagePullPolicy` (optional)\n118:   - `ImagePullSecrets []corev1.LocalObjectReference` with JSON tag `imagePullSecrets` (optional)\n119:   - `Environment []corev1.EnvVar` with JSON tag `environment` (optional)\n120:   - `Command []string` with JSON tag `command` (optional)\n121:   - `Args []string` with JSON tag `args` (optional)\n122:   - `Resources corev1.ResourceRequirements` with JSON tag `resources` (optional)\n123: \n124: #### Scenario: ImagePullSecrets list markers\n125: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n126: - **WHEN** examining the `ImagePullSecrets` field\n127: - **THEN** it SHALL have:\n128:   - `+patchMergeKey=name` marker\n129:   - `+patchStrategy=merge` marker\n130:   - `+listType=map` marker\n131:   - `+listMapKey=name` marker\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterStatus definition\n136: \n137: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterStatus` with conditions and readiness flag.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterStatus fields\n140: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n141: - **WHEN** reading the `CodeInterpreterStatus` struct\n142: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain:\n143:   - `Conditions []metav1.Condition` with JSON tag `conditions` (optional)\n144:   - `Ready bool` with JSON tag `ready` (optional)\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Conditions field markers\n147: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n148: - **WHEN** examining the `Conditions` field\n149: - **THEN** it SHALL have:\n150:   - `+optional` marker\n151:   - `+listType=atomic` marker\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ### Requirement: AuthModeType enum definition\n156: \n157: The system SHALL define `AuthModeType` in `shared_types.go` as an enum for authentication modes.\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: AuthModeType type definition\n160: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go`\n161: - **WHEN** reading the file\n162: - **THEN** `AuthModeType` SHALL be defined as `type AuthModeType string`\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: AuthModeType constants\n165: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go`\n166: - **WHEN** reading the file\n167: - **THEN** the following constants SHALL be defined:\n168:   - `AuthModePicoD AuthModeType = \"picod\"`\n169:   - `AuthModeNone AuthModeType = \"none\"`\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ### Requirement: DeepCopy generation\n174: \n175: The system SHALL generate `DeepCopy` methods for all types using controller-gen.\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for CodeInterpreter\n178: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` (after `make generate`)\n179: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n180: - **THEN** `func (in *CodeInterpreter) DeepCopyInto(out *CodeInterpreter)` SHALL exist and correctly copy all nested fields\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for CodeInterpreterList\n183: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n184: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n185: - **THEN** `func (in *CodeInterpreterList) DeepCopyInto(out *CodeInterpreterList)` SHALL exist and correctly copy `Items` slice\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for CodeInterpreterSpec\n188: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n189: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n190: - **THEN** `func (in *CodeInterpreterSpec) DeepCopyInto(out *CodeInterpreterSpec)` SHALL exist and correctly copy pointer fields including `Template`, `SessionTimeout`, `MaxSessionDuration`, and `WarmPoolSize`\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate\n193: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n194: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n195: - **THEN** `func (in *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate) DeepCopyInto(out *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate)` SHALL exist\n196: \n197: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for CodeInterpreterStatus\n198: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n199: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n200: - **THEN** `func (in *CodeInterpreterStatus) DeepCopyInto(out *CodeInterpreterStatus)` SHALL exist\n201: \n202: #### Scenario: DeepCopyObject implementation\n203: - **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types\n204: - **WHEN** the DeepCopy methods are generated\n205: - **THEN** both types SHALL implement `runtime.Object` interface via `DeepCopyObject()` method\n206: \n207: ---\n208: \n209: ### Requirement: Client-go code generation compatibility\n210: \n211: The system SHALL define types compatible with `k8s.io/code-generator` for generating typed clients, informers, and listers for CodeInterpreter.\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: Generated typed client for CodeInterpreter\n214: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n215: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n216: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreterInterface` SHALL define methods: `Create`, `Update`, `UpdateStatus`, `Delete`, `DeleteCollection`, `Get`, `List`, `Watch`, `Patch`\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: CodeInterpretersGetter interface\n219: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n220: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`\n221: - **THEN** `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` SHALL include `CodeInterpretersGetter`\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Generated informer for CodeInterpreter\n224: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n225: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n226: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreterInformer` interface SHALL define `Informer() cache.SharedIndexInformer` and `Lister() runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister`\n227: \n228: #### Scenario: Generated lister for CodeInterpreter\n229: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n230: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n231: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreterLister` interface SHALL define `List(selector labels.Selector)` and `CodeInterpreters(namespace string)` methods\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: REST resource plural\n234: - **GIVEN** the generated typed client for CodeInterpreter\n235: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n236: - **THEN** the REST resource plural SHALL be `codeinterpreters`\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ### Requirement: JSON serialization\n241: \n242: The system SHALL ensure all types serialize correctly to/from JSON with camelCase field names.\n243: \n244: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter JSON serialization\n245: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` instance with all fields populated\n246: - **WHEN** serializing to JSON\n247: - **THEN** the output SHALL use camelCase field names: `sessionTimeout`, `maxSessionDuration`, `warmPoolSize`, `authMode`, `pathPrefix`\n248: \n249: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter JSON deserialization\n250: - **GIVEN** a JSON document with camelCase field names\n251: - **WHEN** deserializing to `CodeInterpreter`\n252: - **THEN** all fields SHALL be correctly populated including nested `Template` and `Ports` slice\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: Default values applied on deserialization\n255: - **GIVEN** a JSON document without `sessionTimeout`, `maxSessionDuration`, and `authMode` fields\n256: - **WHEN** deserializing to `CodeInterpreterSpec` with defaulting enabled\n257: - **THEN** `SessionTimeout` SHALL default to `15m`\n258: - AND `MaxSessionDuration` SHALL default to `8h`\n259: - AND `AuthMode` SHALL default to `picod`\n260: \n261: ---\n262: \n263: ### Requirement: List type markers\n264: \n265: The system SHALL use correct Kubernetes list type markers for slice fields.\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: Ports list type\n268: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n269: - **WHEN** examining the `Ports` field in `CodeInterpreterSpec`\n270: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+listType=atomic` marker\n271: \n272: #### Scenario: Conditions list type\n273: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n274: - **WHEN** examining the `Conditions` field in `CodeInterpreterStatus`\n275: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+listType=atomic` marker\n276: \n277: #### Scenario: Environment list type\n278: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n279: - **WHEN** examining the `Environment` field in `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`\n280: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+listType=atomic` marker\n281: \n282: #### Scenario: Command list type\n283: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n284: - **WHEN** examining the `Command` field in `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`\n285: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+listType=atomic` marker\n286: \n287: #### Scenario: Args list type\n288: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n289: - **WHEN** examining the `Args` field in `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`\n290: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+listType=atomic` marker\n\n(End of file - total 290 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter Type Definition\n\n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Package structure and registration\n\nThe system SHALL define the `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` with proper package structure, scheme registration, and CRD markers for controller-gen.\n\n#### Scenario: Package structure exists\n- **GIVEN** the repository root at `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n- **WHEN** examining `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n- **THEN** the directory SHALL contain:\n  - `doc.go` with `+k8s:deepcopy-gen=package` marker\n  - `register.go` with `SchemeGroupVersion` set to `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775864792759,"end":1775864792774}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864792778,"sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","part":{"id":"prt_d79ca427e001HLrqVD8ufU3KA4","messageID":"msg_d79ca1800001Ai06Q2QJNcX0vR","sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-7cb4fe98c734461b95055b4613e36870","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package workloadmanager\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"time\"\n6: \n7: \tapierrors \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n8: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n9: \t\"k8s.io/utils/ptr\"\n10: \n11: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n12: )\n13: \n14: type LifecycleConfig struct {\n15: \tDefaultTTL          time.Duration\n16: \tDefaultIdleTimeout  time.Duration\n17: \tDefaultMaxDuration  time.Duration\n18: \tGCInterval          time.Duration\n19: \tGCOnceTimeout       time.Duration\n20: \tDeletionGracePeriod int64\n21: \tDeletionTimeout     time.Duration\n22: }\n23: \n24: func DefaultLifecycleConfig() LifecycleConfig {\n25: \treturn LifecycleConfig{\n26: \t\tDefaultTTL:          DefaultSandboxTTL,\n27: \t\tDefaultIdleTimeout:  DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout,\n28: \t\tDefaultMaxDuration:  DefaultMaxSessionDuration,\n29: \t\tGCInterval:          GarbageCollectorInterval,\n30: \t\tGCOnceTimeout:       2 * time.Minute,\n31: \t\tDeletionGracePeriod: 0,\n32: \t\tDeletionTimeout:     SandboxDeleteTimeout,\n33: \t}\n34: }\n35: \n36: type SandboxLifecycleManager struct {\n37: \tk8sClient *K8sClient\n38: \tstore     Store\n39: \tconfig    LifecycleConfig\n40: \tlogger    Logger\n41: }\n42: \n43: func NewSandboxLifecycleManager(k8sClient *K8sClient, store Store, config LifecycleConfig, logger Logger) *SandboxLifecycleManager {\n44: \treturn &SandboxLifecycleManager{\n45: \t\tk8sClient: k8sClient,\n46: \t\tstore:     store,\n47: \t\tconfig:    config,\n48: \t\tlogger:    logger,\n49: \t}\n50: }\n51: \n52: func (m *SandboxLifecycleManager) DeleteSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\n53: \tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, m.config.DeletionTimeout)\n54: \tdefer cancel()\n55: \n56: \tsandboxInfo, err := m.store.GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n57: \tif err != nil {\n58: \t\tif _, ok := err.(*NotFoundError); ok {\n59: \t\t\treturn &NotFoundError{Resource: \"session\", Name: sessionID}\n60: \t\t}\n61: \t\treturn &InternalError{Err: err}\n62: \t}\n63: \n64: \tdeleteOpts := metav1.DeleteOptions{\n65: \t\tGracePeriodSeconds: ptr.To(m.config.DeletionGracePeriod),\n66: \t}\n67: \n68: \terr = m.k8sClient.DynamicClient().Resource(SandboxGVR).\n69: \t\tNamespace(sandboxInfo.SandboxNamespace).\n70: \t\tDelete(ctx, sandboxInfo.SandboxName, deleteOpts)\n71: \n72: \tif err != nil && !apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n73: \t\treturn handleDeleteError(err)\n74: \t}\n75: \n76: \tif sandboxInfo.Kind == types.SandboxClaimKind {\n77: \t\terr = m.k8sClient.DynamicClient().Resource(SandboxClaimGVR).\n78: \t\t\tNamespace(sandboxInfo.SandboxNamespace).\n79: \t\t\tDelete(ctx, sandboxInfo.SandboxName, deleteOpts)\n80: \n81: \t\tif err != nil && !apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n82: \t\t\tm.logger.Error(\"failed to delete SandboxClaim\", \"sandboxName\", sandboxInfo.SandboxName, \"err\", err)\n83: \t\t}\n84: \t}\n85: \n86: \terr = m.store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n87: \tif err != nil {\n88: \t\tm.logger.Error(\"failed to delete from store\", \"sessionID\", sessionID, \"err\", err)\n89: \t}\n90: \n91: \treturn nil\n92: }\n93: \n94: func (m *SandboxLifecycleManager) IsExpired(sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) bool {\n95: \treturn time.Now().After(sandbox.ExpiresAt)\n96: }\n97: \n98: func (m *SandboxLifecycleManager) IsIdleExpired(sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, idleTimeout time.Duration) bool {\n99: \tif sandbox.LastActivity.IsZero() {\n100: \t\treturn false\n101: \t}\n102: \treturn time.Now().After(sandbox.LastActivity.Add(idleTimeout))\n103: }\n104: \n105: func (m *SandboxLifecycleManager) ForceDeleteSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\n106: \tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, m.config.DeletionTimeout)\n107: \tdefer cancel()\n108: \n109: \tsandboxInfo, err := m.store.GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n110: \tif err != nil {\n111: \t\tif _, ok := err.(*NotFoundError); ok {\n112: \t\t\treturn nil\n113: \t\t}\n114: \t\treturn &InternalError{Err: err}\n115: \t}\n116: \n117: \tdeleteOpts := metav1.DeleteOptions{\n118: \t\tGracePeriodSeconds: ptr.To[int64](0),\n119: \t}\n120: \n121: \terr = m.k8sClient.DynamicClient().Resource(SandboxGVR).\n122: \t\tNamespace(sandboxInfo.SandboxNamespace).\n123: \t\tDelete(ctx, sandboxInfo.SandboxName, deleteOpts)\n124: \n125: \tif err != nil && !apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n126: \t\tm.logger.Error(\"force delete sandbox CR failed\", \"sandboxName\", sandboxInfo.SandboxName, \"err\", err)\n127: \t}\n128: \n129: \tif sandboxInfo.Kind == types.SandboxClaimKind {\n130: \t\tm.k8sClient.DynamicClient().Resource(SandboxClaimGVR).\n131: \t\t\tNamespace(sandboxInfo.SandboxNamespace).\n132: \t\t\tDelete(ctx, sandboxInfo.SandboxName, deleteOpts)\n133: \t}\n134: \n135: \terr = m.store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n136: \tif err != nil {\n137: \t\tm.logger.Error(\"failed to delete from store during force delete\", \"sessionID\", sessionID, \"err\", err)\n138: \t}\n139: \n140: \treturn nil\n141: }\n142: \n143: func (m *SandboxLifecycleManager) GetSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n144: \treturn m.store.GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n145: }\n146: \n147: func (m *SandboxLifecycleManager) UpdateSandboxStatus(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, status string) error {\n148: \tsandbox, err := m.store.GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n149: \tif err != nil {\n150: \t\treturn err\n151: \t}\n152: \n153: \tsandbox.Status = status\n154: \treturn m.store.UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)\n155: }\n156: \n157: func handleDeleteError(err error) error {\n158: \tif apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n159: \t\treturn nil\n160: \t}\n161: \tif apierrors.IsConflict(err) {\n162: \t\treturn &ConflictError{Resource: \"sandbox\", Err: err}\n163: \t}\n164: \treturn &InternalError{Err: err}\n165: }\n166: \n167: func determineDeletionReason(sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, now time.Time, idleTimeout time.Duration) DeletionReason {\n168: \tif now.After(sandbox.ExpiresAt) {\n169: \t\treturn DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached\n170: \t}\n171: \tif !sandbox.LastActivity.IsZero() && now.After(sandbox.LastActivity.Add(idleTimeout)) {\n172: \t\treturn DeletionReasonIdleTimeout\n173: \t}\n174: \treturn DeletionReasonUserRequest\n175: }\n\n(End of file - total 175 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package workloadmanager\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\tapierrors \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n\t\"k8s.io/utils/ptr\"\n\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n)\n\ntype LifecycleConfig struct {\n\tDefaultTTL          time.Duration\n\tDefaultIdleTimeout  time.Duration\n\tDefaultMaxDuration  time.Duration\n\tGCInterval          time.Duration\n\tGCOnceTimeout       time.Duration\n\tDeletionGracePeriod int64","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go","time":{"start":1775864792763,"end":1775864792777}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864792781,"sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","part":{"id":"prt_d79ca46b2001aP0JuIZTLddouy","messageID":"msg_d79ca1800001Ai06Q2QJNcX0vR","sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-23086f530a2e42728956aae69611550c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package workloadmanager\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"sync\"\n6: \t\"time\"\n7: )\n8: \n9: const GCBatchSize = 16\n10: \n11: type GarbageCollector struct {\n12: \tmanager     *SandboxLifecycleManager\n13: \tinterval    time.Duration\n14: \tonceTimeout time.Duration\n15: \tstopCh      chan struct{}\n16: \twg          sync.WaitGroup\n17: \tlogger      Logger\n18: \tidleTimeout time.Duration\n19: \tidleMu      sync.RWMutex\n20: }\n21: \n22: func NewGarbageCollector(manager *SandboxLifecycleManager, interval, onceTimeout time.Duration, logger Logger) *GarbageCollector {\n23: \tif interval == 0 {\n24: \t\tinterval = GarbageCollectorInterval\n25: \t}\n26: \tif onceTimeout == 0 {\n27: \t\tonceTimeout = 2 * time.Minute\n28: \t}\n29: \n30: \treturn &GarbageCollector{\n31: \t\tmanager:     manager,\n32: \t\tinterval:    interval,\n33: \t\tonceTimeout: onceTimeout,\n34: \t\tstopCh:      make(chan struct{}),\n35: \t\tlogger:      logger,\n36: \t\tidleTimeout: manager.config.DefaultIdleTimeout,\n37: \t}\n38: }\n39: \n40: func (gc *GarbageCollector) getIdleTimeout() time.Duration {\n41: \tgc.idleMu.RLock()\n42: \tdefer gc.idleMu.RUnlock()\n43: \treturn gc.idleTimeout\n44: }\n45: \n46: func (gc *GarbageCollector) Start() {\n47: \tgc.wg.Add(1)\n48: \tgo gc.runLoop()\n49: }\n50: \n51: func (gc *GarbageCollector) Stop() {\n52: \tclose(gc.stopCh)\n53: \tgc.wg.Wait()\n54: }\n55: \n56: func (gc *GarbageCollector) runLoop() {\n57: \tdefer gc.wg.Done()\n58: \n59: \tticker := time.NewTicker(gc.interval)\n60: \tdefer ticker.Stop()\n61: \n62: \tgc.runOnce(context.Background())\n63: \n64: \tfor {\n65: \t\tselect {\n66: \t\tcase <-gc.stopCh:\n67: \t\t\tgc.logger.Info(\"garbage collector stopped\")\n68: \t\t\treturn\n69: \t\tcase <-ticker.C:\n70: \t\t\tgc.runOnce(context.Background())\n71: \t\t}\n72: \t}\n73: }\n74: \n75: func (gc *GarbageCollector) runOnce(ctx context.Context) error {\n76: \tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, gc.onceTimeout)\n77: \tdefer cancel()\n78: \n79: \tnow := time.Now()\n80: \tidleTimeout := gc.getIdleTimeout()\n81: \n82: \texpired, err := gc.manager.store.ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, now, GCBatchSize)\n83: \tif err != nil {\n84: \t\tgc.logger.Error(\"failed to list expired sandboxes\", \"err\", err)\n85: \t\treturn err\n86: \t}\n87: \n88: \tinactiveBefore := now.Add(-idleTimeout)\n89: \tinactive, err := gc.manager.store.ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, inactiveBefore, GCBatchSize)\n90: \tif err != nil {\n91: \t\tgc.logger.Error(\"failed to list inactive sandboxes\", \"err\", err)\n92: \t\treturn err\n93: \t}\n94: \n95: \tallSandboxes := append(expired, inactive...)\n96: \n97: \tfor _, sb := range allSandboxes {\n98: \t\tif err := gc.manager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID); err != nil {\n99: \t\t\tif _, ok := err.(*NotFoundError); ok {\n100: \t\t\t\tcontinue\n101: \t\t\t}\n102: \t\t\tgc.logger.Error(\"gc delete failed\", \"sessionID\", sb.SessionID, \"err\", err)\n103: \t\t\tcontinue\n104: \t\t}\n105: \n106: \t\treason := determineDeletionReason(sb, now, idleTimeout)\n107: \t\tgc.logger.Info(\"gc deleted sandbox\", \"sessionID\", sb.SessionID, \"sandboxName\", sb.SandboxName, \"reason\", reason)\n108: \t}\n109: \n110: \treturn nil\n111: }\n112: \n113: func (gc *GarbageCollector) SetIdleTimeout(timeout time.Duration) {\n114: \tgc.idleMu.Lock()\n115: \tdefer gc.idleMu.Unlock()\n116: \tgc.idleTimeout = timeout\n117: }\n118: \n119: func (gc *GarbageCollector) GetStats() GarbageCollectorStats {\n120: \tgc.idleMu.RLock()\n121: \tdefer gc.idleMu.RUnlock()\n122: \treturn GarbageCollectorStats{\n123: \t\tInterval:    gc.interval,\n124: \t\tOnceTimeout: gc.onceTimeout,\n125: \t\tIdleTimeout: gc.idleTimeout,\n126: \t}\n127: }\n128: \n129: type GarbageCollectorStats struct {\n130: \tInterval    time.Duration\n131: \tOnceTimeout time.Duration\n132: \tIdleTimeout time.Duration\n133: }\n\n(End of file - total 133 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package workloadmanager\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"sync\"\n\t\"time\"\n)\n\nconst GCBatchSize = 16\n\ntype GarbageCollector struct {\n\tmanager     *SandboxLifecycleManager\n\tinterval    time.Duration\n\tonceTimeout time.Duration\n\tstopCh      chan struct{}\n\twg          sync.WaitGroup\n\tlogger      Logger\n\tidleTimeout time.Duration\n\tidleMu      sync.RWMutex\n}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go","time":{"start":1775864792765,"end":1775864792779}}}}
