{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775864803109,"sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","part":{"id":"prt_d79ca6f240017nWqagPpRTMC88","messageID":"msg_d79ca60590011UDNzZCJlpUz3I","sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864807145,"sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","part":{"id":"prt_d79ca77f7001XutNgr7bLi5K3G","messageID":"msg_d79ca60590011UDNzZCJlpUz3I","sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-fd8de0d907ce4ab3a82bf98a97219c83","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/router`\n4: **Language:** Go\n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: 为 Router 模块添加 JWT 认证与签发能力，包括 RSA 密钥生成、Token 签发、PEM 编解码、Kubernetes Secret 持久化等功能。JWT 用于在反向代理请求中注入认证信息，供下游 Sandbox Pod 验证请求来源。\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: JWTManager 类型定义\n18: \n19: 系统 SHALL 定义 `JWTManager` 结构体用于 JWT Token 签发与密钥管理。\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: JWTManager struct 定义\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n23: - **WHEN** 读取 `JWTManager` 结构体\n24: - **THEN** 结构体 SHALL 包含字段:\n25:   - `privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey` 用于 RSA 签名\n26:   - `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey` 用于签名验证\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: RSA 密钥大小常量\n29: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n30: - **WHEN** 读取常量定义\n31: - **THEN** `rsaKeySize` SHALL 为 `2048` bits\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: JWT 过期时间常量\n34: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n35: - **WHEN** 读取常量定义\n36: - **THEN** `jwtExpiration` SHALL 为 `5 * time.Minute`\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: Secret 名称常量\n39: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n40: - **WHEN** 读取常量定义\n41: - **THEN** `IdentitySecretName` SHALL 为 `\"picod-router-identity\"`\n42: - AND `PrivateKeyDataKey` SHALL 为 `\"private.pem\"`\n43: - AND `PublicKeyDataKey` SHALL 为 `\"public.pem\"`\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ### Requirement: JWTManager 构造函数\n48: \n49: 系统 SHALL 提供 `NewJWTManager` 构造函数生成 RSA 密钥对。\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: NewJWTManager 生成密钥对\n52: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n53: - **WHEN** 调用 `NewJWTManager()`\n54: - **THEN** RSA 密钥对 SHALL 通过 `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, rsaKeySize)` 生成\n55: - AND 密钥大小 SHALL 为 `2048` bits\n56: - AND 返回 `*JWTManager` 包含 `privateKey` 和 `publicKey`\n57: - AND `publicKey` SHALL 为 `&privateKey.PublicKey`\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: NewJWTManager 密钥生成失败\n60: - **GIVEN** 系统熵不足或其他异常\n61: - **WHEN** `rsa.GenerateKey` 返回错误\n62: - **THEN** 构造函数 SHALL 返回 `nil` 和 `error`\n63: - AND 错误信息 SHALL 包含 `\"failed to generate RSA key\"`\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ### Requirement: Token 签发功能\n68: \n69: 系统 SHALL 提供 `GenerateToken` 方法生成 RS256 签名的 JWT Token。\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: GenerateToken 基本签发\n72: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go` 中的 `JWTManager`\n73: - **WHEN** 调用 `GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{})`\n74: - **THEN** JWT Token SHALL 使用 `jwt.SigningMethodRS256` 算法\n75: - AND Token SHALL 包含标准 Claims:\n76:   - `exp` = `now + jwtExpiration` (5分钟过期)\n77:   - `iat` = `now` (签发时间)\n78:   - `iss` = `\"agentcube-router\"` (签发者)\n79: - AND 用户提供的 claims SHALL 合并到 Token Claims 中\n80: - AND Token SHALL 使用 `privateKey` 签名\n81: - AND 返回签名的 Token 字符串\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: GenerateToken 包含自定义 Claims\n84: - **GIVEN** 用户提供 claims `{\"session_id\": \"abc\", \"sandbox_id\": \"xyz\"}`\n85: - **WHEN** 调用 `GenerateToken(claims)`\n86: - **THEN** 生成的 Token SHALL 包含:\n87:   - `session_id` = `\"abc\"`\n88:   - `sandbox_id` = `\"xyz\"`\n89:   - 以及标准 Claims (`exp`, `iat`, `iss`)\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: GenerateToken 签名失败\n92: - **GIVEN** `jwt.SignedString` 返回错误\n93: - **WHEN** Token 签名过程失败\n94: - **THEN** SHALL 返回 `\"\"` 和 `JWTSigningError`\n95: - AND 错误 SHALL 包装底层错误\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: GenerateToken 过期时间计算\n98: - **GIVEN** 当前时间 `now`\n99: - **WHEN** 生成 Token\n100: - **THEN** `exp` Claim SHALL 为 `now.Unix() + int64(jwtExpiration.Seconds())`\n101: - AND 容差 SHALL 为 ±5秒\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ### Requirement: PEM 编解码功能\n106: \n107: 系统 SHALL 提供 PEM 格式的 RSA 密钥编解码函数。\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: encodePrivateKeyPEM 编码私钥\n110: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n111: - **WHEN** 调用 `encodePrivateKeyPEM(key *rsa.PrivateKey)`\n112: - **THEN** 返回 PEM 格式字节\n113: - AND PEM Block Type SHALL 为 `\"RSA PRIVATE KEY\"`\n114: - AND 私钥 SHALL 使用 PKCS1 格式 (`x509.MarshalPKCS1PrivateKey`)\n115: - AND PEM 格式 SHALL 包含 `-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----`\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: encodePublicKeyPEM 编码公钥\n118: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n119: - **WHEN** 调用 `encodePublicKeyPEM(key *rsa.PublicKey)`\n120: - **THEN** 返回 PEM 格式字节\n121: - AND PEM Block Type SHALL 为 `\"PUBLIC KEY\"`\n122: - AND 公钥 SHALL 使用 PKIX 格式 (`x509.MarshalPKIXPublicKey`)\n123: - AND PEM 格式 SHALL 包含 `-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----`\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: encodePublicKeyPEM 编码失败\n126: - **GIVEN** `x509.MarshalPKIXPublicKey` 返回错误\n127: - **WHEN** 编码公钥失败\n128: - **THEN** 函数 SHALL 返回 `nil`\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: loadPrivateKeyPEM 解码私钥\n131: - **GIVEN** PEM 格式的私钥字节\n132: - **WHEN** 调用 `loadPrivateKeyPEM(data []byte)`\n133: - **THEN** SHALL 使用 `pem.Decode` 解析 PEM Block\n134: - AND SHALL 使用 `x509.ParsePKCS1PrivateKey` 解析私钥\n135: - AND 返回 `*rsa.PrivateKey` 和 `nil` error\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: loadPrivateKeyPEM PEM 解析失败\n138: - **GIVEN** 无效 PEM 数据\n139: - **WHEN** `pem.Decode` 返回 `nil` Block\n140: - **THEN** SHALL 返回 `nil` 和 error\n141: - AND 错误信息 SHALL 为 `\"failed to decode PEM block\"`\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: loadPrivateKeyPEM 私钥解析失败\n144: - **GIVEN** 有效 PEM Block 但无效私钥数据\n145: - **WHEN** `x509.ParsePKCS1PrivateKey` 失败\n146: - **THEN** SHALL 返回 `nil` 和 error\n147: - AND 错误信息 SHALL 包含 `\"failed to parse private key\"`\n148: \n149: ---\n150: \n151: ### Requirement: 公钥获取功能\n152: \n153: 系统 SHALL 提供 `GetPublicKey` 方法获取 RSA 公钥。\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: GetPublicKey 返回公钥\n156: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go` 中的 `JWTManager`\n157: - **WHEN** 调用 `GetPublicKey()`\n158: - **THEN** SHALL 返回 `*rsa.PublicKey`\n159: - AND 公钥大小 SHALL 为 `2048/8 = 256` bytes\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: GetPublicKey 用于验证\n162: - **GIVEN** Token 使用 RS256 签名\n163: - **WHEN** 使用 `jwt.Parse` 验证 Token\n164: - **THEN** `GetPublicKey()` 返回的公钥 SHALL 用于签名验证\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ### Requirement: Secret 持久化功能\n169: \n170: 系统 SHALL 提供 `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret` 方法在 Kubernetes 中持久化密钥。\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret 基本行为\n173: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n174: - **WHEN** 调用 `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx context.Context)`\n175: - **THEN** SHALL 尝试在 Kubernetes 中存储/加载密钥 Secret\n176: - AND Secret 名称 SHALL 为 `IdentitySecretName` (`\"picod-router-identity\"`)\n177: - AND Secret Namespace SHALL 为 `IdentityNamespace`\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret 非集群环境\n180: - **GIVEN** 非 Kubernetes 集群环境运行\n181: - **WHEN** 调用 `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret`\n182: - **THEN** SHALL 使用 `klog.Warningf` 记录 `\"not in cluster, skipping secret persistence\"`\n183: - AND 返回 `nil` error\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: IdentityNamespace 环境变量\n186: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go` init 函数\n187: - **WHEN** 系统启动\n188: - **THEN** SHALL 读取 `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` 环境变量\n189: - AND 默认 `IdentityNamespace` SHALL 为 `\"default\"`\n190: - AND 若环境变量设置，`IdentityNamespace` SHALL 使用该值\n191: \n192: ---\n193: \n194: ### Requirement: JWTSigningError 错误类型\n195: \n196: 系统 SHALL 定义 `JWTSigningError` 错误类型用于 JWT 签名失败。\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: JWTSigningError struct 定义\n199: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n200: - **WHEN** 读取 `JWTSigningError` 结构体\n201: - **THEN** 结构体 SHALL 包含字段:\n202:   - `Err error` 用于包装底层错误\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: JWTSigningError Error 方法\n205: - **GIVEN** `JWTSigningError` 实例\n206: - **WHEN** 调用 `Error()` 方法\n207: - **THEN** 返回字符串 SHALL 为 `\"jwt signing failed: \" + e.Err.Error()`\n208: \n209: #### Scenario: JWTSigningError Status 方法\n210: - **GIVEN** `JWTSigningError` 实例\n211: - **WHEN** 调用 `Status()` 方法\n212: - **THEN** 返回 HTTP Status SHALL 为 `500`\n213: \n214: #### Scenario: JWTSigningError Code 方法\n215: - **GIVEN** `JWTSigningError` 实例\n216: - **WHEN** 调用 `Code()` 方法\n217: - **THEN** 返回错误码 SHALL 为 `\"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"`\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: JWTSigningError Message 方法\n220: - **GIVEN** `JWTSigningError` 实例\n221: - **WHEN** 调用 `Message()` 方法\n222: - **THEN** 返回消息 SHALL 为 `\"jwt signing failed\"`\n223: \n224: ---\n225: \n226: ### Requirement: JWT Token 验证场景\n227: \n228: 系统 SHALL 支持 JWT Token 的外部验证。\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: 使用公钥验证 Token\n231: - **GIVEN** 通过 `GenerateToken` 生成的 Token\n232: - **WHEN** 使用 `jwt.Parse` 和 `GetPublicKey()` 验证\n233: - **THEN** Token SHALL 被成功解析\n234: - AND `token.Valid` SHALL 为 `true`\n235: - AND Claims SHALL 包含所有自定义字段\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: 拒绝无效签名 Token\n238: - **GIVEN** 使用错误私钥签名的 Token\n239: - **WHEN** 使用正确公钥验证\n240: - **THEN** SHALL 返回 `jwt.ErrSignatureInvalid` 错误\n241: \n242: #### Scenario: 拒绝过期 Token\n243: - **GIVEN** 已超过 `jwtExpiration` (5分钟) 的 Token\n244: - **WHEN** 验证 Token\n245: - **THEN** SHALL 返回过期错误\n246: \n247: #### Scenario: 签名方法验证\n248: - **GIVEN** Token 使用非 RSA 签名方法\n249: - **WHEN** 解析 Token\n250: - **THEN** SHALL 返回 `jwt.ErrSignatureInvalid` 错误\n251: \n252: ---\n253: \n254: ### Requirement: JWT 在反向代理中的使用\n255: \n256: 系统 SHALL 在反向代理请求中注入 JWT Token。\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: handleInvoke JWT 生成\n259: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go` 的 `handleInvoke` 方法\n260: - **WHEN** 处理 Sandbox/Claim 类请求\n261: - **THEN** `jwtManager.GenerateToken` SHALL 被调用\n262: - AND Claims SHALL 包含:\n263:   - `session_id` = `sandbox.SessionID`\n264:   - `sandbox_id` = `sandbox.SandboxID`\n265:   - `namespace` = `sandbox.SandboxNamespace`\n266:   - `name` = `sandbox.SandboxName`\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: handleInvoke JWT 注入 Header\n269: - **GIVEN** 生成的 JWT Token\n270: - **WHEN** 反向代理转发请求\n271: - **THEN** `Authorization: Bearer <jwt>` Header SHALL 被添加\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: handleInvoke JWT 签名失败\n274: - **GIVEN** `GenerateToken` 返回错误\n275: - **WHEN** JWT 签名失败\n276: - **THEN** HTTP `500` SHALL 被返回\n277: - AND 响应 SHALL 包含 `{\"error\": \"jwt signing failed\", \"code\": \"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"}`\n278: \n279: ---\n280: \n281: ### Requirement: 单元测试覆盖\n282: \n283: 系统 SHALL 有全面的 JWT 功能单元测试。\n284: \n285: #### Scenario: TestNewJWTManager 测试\n286: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n287: - **WHEN** 运行测试\n288: - **THEN** 测试 SHALL 验证:\n289:   - `JWTManager` 构造成功\n290:   - `privateKey` 非 nil\n291:   - `publicKey` 非 nil\n292: \n293: #### Scenario: TestJWTManagerGenerateToken 测试\n294: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n295: - **WHEN** 运行测试\n296: - **THEN** 测试 SHALL 验证:\n297:   - Token 生成成功\n298:   - Token 可被正确解析验证\n299:   - Token 包含正确的自定义 Claims\n300:   - Token 签发者 `iss` = `\"agentcube-router\"`\n301: \n302: #### Scenario: TestJWTManagerTokenExpiration 测试\n303: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n304: - **WHEN** 运行测试\n305: - **THEN** 测试 SHALL 验证:\n306:   - Token 过期时间正确设置\n307:   - `exp` Claim 约为 `now + 5m`\n308:   - Token 未过期\n309: \n310: #### Scenario: TestJWTManagerGetPublicKey 测试\n311: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n312: - **WHEN** 运行测试\n313: - **THEN** 测试 SHALL 验证:\n314:   - `GetPublicKey` 返回非 nil\n315:   - 公钥大小为 `2048/8 = 256` bytes\n316: \n317: #### Scenario: TestEncodePrivateKeyPEM 测试\n318: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n319: - **WHEN** 运行测试\n320: - **THEN** 测试 SHALL 验证:\n321:   - PEM 编码返回非 nil\n322:   - PEM 数据包含 `\"RSA PRIVATE KEY\"`\n323: \n324: #### Scenario: TestEncodePublicKeyPEM 测试\n325: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n326: - **WHEN** 运行测试\n327: - **THEN** 测试 SHALL 验证:\n328:   - PEM 编码返回非 nil\n329:   - PEM 数据包含 `\"PUBLIC KEY\"`\n330: \n331: #### Scenario: TestLoadPrivateKeyPEM 测试\n332: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n333: - **WHEN** 运行测试\n334: - **THEN** 测试 SHALL 验证:\n335:   - PEM 解码成功\n336:   - 加载的私钥与原始私钥匹配 (`N.Cmp` = 0)\n337: \n338: #### Scenario: TestLoadPrivateKeyPEMInvalid 测试\n339: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n340: - **WHEN** 使用无效 PEM 数据运行测试\n341: - **THEN** 测试 SHALL 验证返回错误\n342: \n343: #### Scenario: TestJWTSigningError 测试\n344: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors_test.go`\n345: - **WHEN** 运行测试\n346: - **THEN** 测试 SHALL 验证:\n347:   - `Error()` 方法返回正确字符串\n348:   - `Code()` 返回 `\"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"`\n349:   - `Message()` 返回 `\"jwt signing failed\"`\n350:   - `Status()` 返回 `500`\n351: \n352: ---\n353: \n354: ### Requirement: 文件结构\n355: \n356: 系统 SHALL 正确组织 JWT 相关文件。\n357: \n358: #### Scenario: jwt.go 位置\n359: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n360: - **WHEN** 列出文件\n361: - **THEN** `jwt.go` SHALL 存在，包含 JWTManager 实现\n362: \n363: #### Scenario: jwt_test.go 位置\n364: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n365: - **WHEN** 列出文件\n366: - **THEN** `jwt_test.go` SHALL 存在，包含单元测试\n367: \n368: #### Scenario: errors.go JWTSigningError\n369: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n370: - **WHEN** 读取文件\n371: - **THEN** `JWTSigningError` SHALL 定义\n372: \n373: ---\n374: \n375: ## Implementation Files\n376: \n377: | File | Purpose |\n378: |------|---------|\n379: | `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWTManager 结构体、GenerateToken、PEM 编解码、Secret 持久化 |\n380: | `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` | JWT 功能单元测试 |\n381: | `pkg/router/errors.go` | JWTSigningError 错误类型定义 |\n382: | `pkg/router/errors_test.go` | 错误类型单元测试 |\n383: | `pkg/router/server.go` | handleInvoke 中 JWT 生成与注入 |\n384: | `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go` | Director 中 JWT Header 设置 |\n385: \n386: ---\n387: \n388: ## Dependencies\n389: \n390: | Package | Purpose |\n391: |---------|---------|\n392: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | JWT 标准 Claims 和 RS256 签名 |\n393: | `crypto/rsa` | RSA 密钥生成和签名 |\n394: | `crypto/rand` | 安全随机数生成器 |\n395: | `crypto/x509` | PKCS1/PKIX 密钥编解码 |\n396: | `encoding/pem` | PEM 格式编解码 |\n397: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | 结构化日志 |\n398: | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Kubernetes Secret 操作 |\n399: | `net/http` | HTTP 客户端和反向代理 |\n400: \n401: ---\n402: \n403: ## JWT Claims 结构\n404: \n405: | Claim | 类型 | 来源 | 描述 |\n406: |-------|------|------|------|\n407: | `exp` | int64 | 自动生成 | 过期时间 (now + 5m) |\n408: | `iat` | int64 | 自动生成 | 签发时间 (now) |\n409: | `iss` | string | 固定值 | 签发者 `\"agentcube-router\"` |\n410: | `session_id` | string | 用户传入 | Session ID |\n411: | `sandbox_id` | string | 用户传入 | Sandbox ID |\n412: | `namespace` | string | 用户传入 | Sandbox Namespace |\n413: | `name` | string | 用户传入 | Sandbox Name |\n414: \n415: ---\n416: \n417: ## Constants\n418: \n419: | 常量 | 值 | 用途 |\n420: |------|-----|------|\n421: | `rsaKeySize` | `2048` | RSA 密钥大小 (bits) |\n422: | `jwtExpiration` | `5 * time.Minute` | Token 有效期 |\n423: | `IdentitySecretName` | `\"picod-router-identity\"` | Kubernetes Secret 名称 |\n424: | `PrivateKeyDataKey` | `\"private.pem\"` | Secret 中私钥数据键 |\n425: | `PublicKeyDataKey` | `\"public.pem\"` | Secret 中公钥数据键 |\n426: | `IdentityNamespace` | `\"default\"` (可配置) | Secret Namespace |\n427: \n428: ---\n429: \n430: ## Environment Variables\n431: \n432: | 变量 | 必需 | 默认值 | 用途 |\n433: |------|------|--------|------|\n434: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | No | `\"default\"` | JWT Secret 存储的 Namespace |\n435: \n436: ---\n437: \n438: ## Request Flow with JWT\n439: \n440: ```\n441: handleInvoke (server.go)\n442: │\n443: ├── 获取 SandboxInfo\n444: │\n445: ├── JWT Generation (if kind == Sandbox/Claim)\n446: │   │\n447: │   ├── jwtManager.GenerateToken(claims)\n448: │   │   ├── 创建 MapClaims\n449: │   │   │   ├── exp = now + 5m\n450: │   │   │   ├── iat = now\n451: │   │   │   ├── iss = \"agentcube-router\"\n452: │   │   │   ├── session_id, sandbox_id, namespace, name\n453: │   │   │\n454: │   │   ├── jwt.NewWithClaims(SigningMethodRS256)\n455: │   │   ├── token.SignedString(privateKey)\n456: │   │   │\n457: │   │   └── Return JWT string\n458: │   │\n459: │   └── Error: JWTSigningError\n460: │       ├── Status: 500\n461: │       ├── Code: \"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"\n462: │       └── Message: \"jwt signing failed\"\n463: │\n464: ├── ReverseProxy.ServeHTTP\n465: │   │\n466: │   ├── Director (reverse_proxy.go)\n467: │   │   ├── req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+jwt)\n468: │   │   └── Forward to sandbox pod\n469: │   │\n470: │   └── Sandbox Pod validates JWT\n471: │       ├── Parse with publicKey\n472: │       ├── Verify RS256 signature\n473: │       ├── Check exp claim\n474: │       └── Extract session/sandbox info\n475: │\n476: └── Response\n477: ```\n478: \n479: ---\n480: \n481: ## Validation Checklist\n482: \n483: - [ ] JWTManager 结构体定义包含 privateKey 和 publicKey\n484: - [ ] rsaKeySize 常量为 2048\n485: - [ ] jwtExpiration 常量为 5 分钟\n486: - [ ] IdentitySecretName 常量为 \"picod-router-identity\"\n487: - [ ] NewJWTManager 生成有效 RSA 密钥对\n488: - [ ] GenerateToken 使用 RS256 算法\n489: - [ ] GenerateToken 包含 exp, iat, iss Claims\n490: - [ ] GenerateToken 合并用户 Claims\n491: - [ ] GenerateToken 失败返回 JWTSigningError\n492: - [ ] encodePrivateKeyPEM 使用 PKCS1 格式\n493: - [ ] encodePublicKeyPEM 使用 PKIX 格式\n494: - [ ] loadPrivateKeyPEM 解析 PKCS1 私钥\n495: - [ ] loadPrivateKeyPEM 处理无效数据错误\n496: - [ ] GetPublicKey 返回 RSA 公钥\n497: - [ ] TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret 在非集群环境跳过\n498: - [ ] IdentityNamespace 从 AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE 读取\n499: - [ ] JWTSigningError 实现 APIStatus 接口\n500: - [ ] JWTSigningError.Error 返回正确格式\n501: - [ ] JWTSigningError.Status 返回 500\n502: - [ ] JWTSigningError.Code 返回 \"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"\n503: - [ ] handleInvoke 为 Sandbox/Claim 生成 JWT\n504: - [ ] JWT 注入 Authorization Header\n505: - [ ] JWT 签名失败返回 500 响应\n506: - [ ] 单元测试覆盖所有 JWT 功能\n507: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n508: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n509: - [ ] 测试覆盖率 ≥ 80%\n\n(End of file - total 509 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发\n\n**Module:** `pkg/router`\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\n为 Router 模块添加 JWT 认证与签发能力，包括 RSA 密钥生成、Token 签发、PEM 编解码、Kubernetes Secret 持久化等功能。JWT 用于在反向代理请求中注入认证信息，供下游 Sandbox Pod 验证请求来源。\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: JWTManager 类型定义\n\n系统 SHALL 定义 `JWTManager` 结构体用于 JWT Token 签发与密钥管理。\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775864807129,"end":1775864807143}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864807147,"sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","part":{"id":"prt_d79ca7b22001NUddalfYWD7a8x","messageID":"msg_d79ca60590011UDNzZCJlpUz3I","sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-774779226ffe460fb5bdcd924aca9bd1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-010 — Router 会话管理\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/router`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: [待填写: Router 会话管理的概述]\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: [待填写]\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: [待填写]\n20: - **GIVEN** [待填写]\n21: - **WHEN** [待填写]\n22: - **THEN** [待填写]\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## Implementation Files\n27: \n28: | File | Purpose |\n29: |------|---------|\n30: | [待填写] | [待填写] |\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## Dependencies\n35: \n36: | Package | Purpose |\n37: |---------|---------|\n38: | [待填写] | [待填写] |\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ## Validation Checklist\n43: \n44: - [ ] [待填写]\n\n(End of file - total 44 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-010 — Router 会话管理\n\n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\n[待填写: Router 会话管理的概述]\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: [待填写]\n\n#### Scenario: [待填写]\n- **GIVEN** [待填写]","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775864807132,"end":1775864807146}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864807151,"sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","part":{"id":"prt_d79ca7ebe001Th4XNkN9WoqZL0","messageID":"msg_d79ca60590011UDNzZCJlpUz3I","sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-30d5b132bc214556907bd920d8cfc715","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/router`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the HTTP reverse proxy core for the AgentCube Router component. This provides session-aware routing that resolves session IDs from request headers, creates sandboxes via Workload Manager, forwards HTTP requests to sandbox pod endpoints using `httputil.ReverseProxy`, generates RS256-signed JWT tokens, updates session activity timestamps, and limits concurrent requests via semaphore middleware.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Server type definition\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define `Server` as an HTTP server with Gin engine for reverse proxy routing.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Server struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `Server` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `config *Config` for server configuration\n26:   - `engine *gin.Engine` for Gin HTTP framework\n27:   - `httpServer *http.Server` for underlying HTTP server\n28:   - `sessionManager SessionManager` for session resolution\n29:   - `store Store` for session state persistence\n30:   - `jwtManager JWTManager` for JWT token generation\n31:   - `transport *http.Transport` for HTTP transport sharing\n32:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: Config struct definition\n35: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/config.go`\n36: - **WHEN** reading the `Config` struct\n37: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n38:   - `Port int` for listening port (default 8080)\n39:   - `EnableTLS bool` for TLS enablement\n40:   - `TLSCert string` for TLS certificate file path\n41:   - `TLSKey string` for TLS private key file path\n42:   - `MaxConcurrentRequests int` for concurrency limit\n43:   - `Debug bool` for debug mode\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: NewServer constructor\n46: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n47: - **WHEN** calling `NewServer(config *Config, sessionManager SessionManager, store Store, jwtManager JWTManager, logger Logger)`\n48: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*Server` with:\n49:   - `engine` initialized with `gin.New()`\n50:   - `gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)` if `config.Debug == false`\n51:   - `gin.SetMode(gin.DebugMode)` if `config.Debug == true`\n52:   - `transport` initialized with shared HTTP transport\n53:   - `httpServer` initialized with h2c configuration\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: DefaultConfig\n56: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/config.go`\n57: - **WHEN** calling `DefaultConfig()`\n58: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*Config` with:\n59:   - `Port` = `8080`\n60:   - `EnableTLS` = `false`\n61:   - `MaxConcurrentRequests` = `1000`\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ### Requirement: Server lifecycle\n66: \n67: The system SHALL provide Start/Stop lifecycle methods with graceful shutdown.\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Start without TLS\n70: - **GIVEN** a `Server` with `config.EnableTLS == false`\n71: - **WHEN** calling `server.Start(ctx)`\n72: - **THEN** `httpServer.ListenAndServe()` SHALL be called\n73: - AND h2c server SHALL handle HTTP/2 without TLS\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Start with TLS\n76: - **GIVEN** a `Server` with `config.EnableTLS == true`\n77: - **WHEN** calling `server.Start(ctx)`\n78: - **THEN** `httpServer.ListenAndServeTLS(config.TLSCert, config.TLSKey)` SHALL be called\n79: - AND error SHALL be returned if cert/key files are missing\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Graceful shutdown\n82: - **GIVEN** a running `Server`\n83: - **WHEN** context is cancelled\n84: - **THEN** `httpServer.Shutdown(shutdownCtx)` SHALL be called\n85: - AND shutdown deadline SHALL be `10s`\n86: - AND server SHALL stop accepting new connections\n87: - AND existing connections SHALL complete\n88: \n89: #### Scenario: Server timeouts\n90: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n91: - **WHEN** initializing `httpServer`\n92: - **THEN** timeouts SHALL be configured:\n93:   - `ReadTimeout` = `30s`\n94:   - `IdleTimeout` = `90s`\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: ### Requirement: Route registration\n99: \n100: The system SHALL register routes for health endpoints and invocation paths.\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Health routes\n103: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n104: - **WHEN** registering routes\n105: - **THEN** `/health/live` SHALL be registered with `handleHealthLive`\n106: - AND `/health/ready` SHALL be registered with `handleHealthReady`\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Invocation routes\n109: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n110: - **WHEN** registering routes\n111: - **THEN** `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` SHALL be registered\n112: - AND `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` SHALL be registered\n113: - AND both `GET` and `POST` methods SHALL be supported\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Middleware chain\n116: - **GIVEN** route registration\n117: - **WHEN** applying middleware\n118: - **THEN** `concurrencyLimitMiddleware` SHALL be applied globally\n119: - AND `loggingMiddleware` SHALL be applied for request logging\n120: - AND `recoveryMiddleware` SHALL be applied for panic recovery\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ### Requirement: SessionManager interface\n125: \n126: The system SHALL define `SessionManager` interface for session resolution and sandbox creation.\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: SessionManager interface definition\n129: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n130: - **WHEN** reading the `SessionManager` interface\n131: - **THEN** interface SHALL include:\n132:   - `GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID, namespace, name, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n133: \n134: #### Scenario: manager struct definition\n135: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n136: - **WHEN** reading the `manager` struct\n137: - **THEN** struct SHALL contain:\n138:   - `storeClient Store` for session lookup\n139:   - `workloadMgrAddr string` for Workload Manager URL\n140:   - `httpClient *http.Client` for sandbox creation requests\n141:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: NewSessionManager constructor\n144: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n145: - **WHEN** calling `NewSessionManager(store Store, logger Logger)`\n146: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*manager` with:\n147:   - `workloadMgrAddr` from `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable\n148:   - startup SHALL fail if `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is not set\n149:   - `httpClient` with `Timeout=2m`, `MaxIdleConnsPerHost=100`\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: HTTP client configuration\n152: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n153: - **WHEN** initializing `httpClient`\n154: - **THEN** HTTP2 SHALL be configured with:\n155:   - `ReadIdleTimeout` = `30s`\n156:   - `PingTimeout` = `15s`\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ### Requirement: Session resolution\n161: \n162: The system SHALL resolve sessions by ID and create new sandboxes when missing.\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: GetSandboxBySession with existing session\n165: - **GIVEN** a session ID that exists in store\n166: - **WHEN** calling `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)`\n167: - **THEN** `store.GetSession(ctx, sessionID)` SHALL be called\n168: - AND `*SandboxInfo` SHALL be returned if found\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: GetSandboxBySession creates new sandbox\n171: - **GIVEN** a session ID that does NOT exist in store\n172: - **WHEN** calling `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)`\n173: - **THEN** `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)` SHALL be called\n174: - AND POST request SHALL be sent to Workload Manager\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: createSandbox POST request\n177: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n178: - **WHEN** calling `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)`\n179: - **THEN** POST SHALL be sent to:\n180:   - `/v1/agent-runtime` for `AgentRuntimeKind`\n181:   - `/v1/code-interpreter` for `CodeInterpreterKind`\n182: - AND request body SHALL be `CreateSandboxRequest`\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: createSandbox with K8s SA token\n185: - **GIVEN** in-cluster deployment\n186: - **WHEN** sending POST to Workload Manager\n187: - **THEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` SHALL be read\n188: - AND token SHALL be set as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: createSandbox namespace\n191: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n192: - **WHEN** creating sandbox\n193: - **THEN** `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` environment variable SHALL be read for target namespace\n194: - AND default namespace SHALL be `\"default\"` if not set\n195: \n196: ---\n197: \n198: ### Requirement: Reverse proxy implementation\n199: \n200: The system SHALL implement reverse proxy with custom Director and error handling.\n201: \n202: #### Scenario: ReverseProxy struct definition\n203: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n204: - **WHEN** reading the implementation\n205: - **THEN** `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy` SHALL be used as base\n206: - AND custom `Director` function SHALL be set\n207: - AND custom `ModifyResponse` function SHALL be set\n208: - AND custom `ErrorHandler` function SHALL be set\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: Director path normalization\n211: - **GIVEN** a request with path `/api/run`\n212: - **WHEN** Director processes the request\n213: - **THEN** leading slash SHALL be prefixed if missing: `//api/run` → `/api/run`\n214: - AND path SHALL match entry point from `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints`\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: Director forwarding headers\n217: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n218: - **WHEN** Director processes request\n219: - **THEN** `req.Host` SHALL be set to target host\n220: - AND `X-Forwarded-For` SHALL be set with client IP\n221: - AND `X-Real-IP` SHALL be set with client IP\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Director JWT injection\n224: - **GIVEN** a proxied request\n225: - **WHEN** Director processes request\n226: - **THEN** JWT token SHALL be generated by `jwtManager`\n227: - AND `Authorization: Bearer <jwt>` SHALL be added to request headers\n228: \n229: #### Scenario: ModifyResponse session header injection\n230: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n231: - **WHEN** ModifyResponse processes response\n232: - **THEN** `x-agentcube-session-id` header SHALL be added to response\n233: - AND value SHALL be the resolved session ID\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: ErrorHandler connection refused\n236: - **GIVEN** proxy error with connection refused\n237: - **WHEN** ErrorHandler processes error\n238: - **THEN** HTTP `502` SHALL be returned\n239: - AND error code SHALL be `sandbox unreachable`\n240: \n241: #### Scenario: ErrorHandler timeout\n242: - **GIVEN** proxy error with timeout\n243: - **WHEN** ErrorHandler processes error\n244: - **THEN** HTTP `504` SHALL be returned\n245: - AND error code SHALL be `sandbox timeout`\n246: \n247: #### Scenario: Entry point matching\n248: - **GIVEN** `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints` with multiple entry points\n249: - **WHEN** selecting entry point\n250: - **THEN** first entry point with matching path prefix SHALL be used\n251: - AND `Endpoint` SHALL be the proxy target URL\n252: \n253: ---\n254: \n255: ### Requirement: JWT Manager\n256: \n257: The system SHALL implement JWT token generation with RSA signing and K8s Secret persistence.\n258: \n259: #### Scenario: JWTManager interface definition\n260: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n261: - **WHEN** reading the `JWTManager` interface\n262: - **THEN** interface SHALL include:\n263:   - `GenerateToken(ctx context.Context, kind, name, namespace string) (string, error)`\n264:   - `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx context.Context) error`\n265: \n266: #### Scenario: jwtManager struct definition\n267: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n268: - **WHEN** reading the `jwtManager` struct\n269: - **THEN** struct SHALL contain:\n270:   - `privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey` for RSA private key\n271:   - `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey` for RSA public key\n272:   - `kubeClient kubernetes.Interface` for K8s Secret operations\n273:   - `namespace string` for Secret namespace\n274:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: RSA key generation\n277: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n278: - **WHEN** generating RSA key\n279: - **THEN** `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)` SHALL be called\n280: - AND key size SHALL be `2048` bits (constant `rsaKeySize`)\n281: - AND private key SHALL be PKCS1 encoded\n282: - AND public key SHALL be PKIX encoded\n283: \n284: #### Scenario: GenerateToken\n285: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n286: - **WHEN** calling `GenerateToken(ctx, kind, name, namespace)`\n287: - **THEN** JWT SHALL be created with claims:\n288:   - `exp` = `now + 5m` (constant `jwtExpiration`)\n289:   - `iat` = `now`\n290:   - `iss` = `\"agentcube-router\"`\n291:   - `kind` = kind parameter\n292:   - `name` = name parameter\n293:   - `namespace` = namespace parameter\n294: - AND JWT SHALL be signed with RS256 algorithm\n295: \n296: #### Scenario: TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret create\n297: - **GIVEN** no existing Secret `picod-router-identity`\n298: - **WHEN** calling `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)`\n299: - **THEN** K8s Secret SHALL be created with:\n300:   - `name` = `IdentitySecretName` (`\"picod-router-identity\"`)\n301:   - `data[\"private-key\"]` = PKCS1 encoded private key\n302:   - `data[\"public-key\"]` = PKIX encoded public key\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret load\n305: - **GIVEN** existing Secret `picod-router-identity`\n306: - **WHEN** calling `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)`\n307: - **THEN** Secret SHALL be loaded via `kubeClient.CoreV1().Secrets(namespace).Get`\n308: - AND keys SHALL be decoded from Secret data\n309: - AND `privateKey` and `publicKey` SHALL be set from loaded data\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret AlreadyExists\n312: - **GIVEN** multiple router replicas starting simultaneously\n313: - **WHEN** Secret creation returns `AlreadyExists` error\n314: - **THEN** existing Secret SHALL be loaded instead\n315: - AND no error SHALL be returned\n316: \n317: ---\n318: \n319: ### Requirement: Middleware concurrency limit\n320: \n321: The system SHALL limit concurrent requests using semaphore middleware.\n322: \n323: #### Scenario: concurrencyLimitMiddleware\n324: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n325: - **WHEN** reading middleware implementation\n326: - **THEN** buffered channel SHALL be used as semaphore\n327: - AND channel capacity SHALL be `MaxConcurrentRequests`\n328: - AND default capacity SHALL be `1000` when `MaxConcurrentRequests <= 0`\n329: \n330: #### Scenario: Request acquires semaphore\n331: - **GIVEN** middleware with capacity 1000\n332: - **WHEN** request enters middleware\n333: - **THEN** `semaphore <- struct{}{}` SHALL acquire slot\n334: - AND request SHALL proceed if slot available\n335: \n336: #### Scenario: Semaphore full returns 429\n337: - **GIVEN** middleware with all slots occupied\n338: - **WHEN** new request enters middleware\n339: - **THEN** `select` with `default` case SHALL trigger\n340: - AND HTTP `429` SHALL be returned\n341: - AND response body SHALL have `SERVER_OVERLOADED` code\n342: \n343: #### Scenario: Request releases semaphore\n344: - **GIVEN** request completing processing\n345: - **WHEN** middleware exits\n346: - **THEN** `<-semaphore` SHALL release slot\n347: - AND deferred release SHALL guarantee cleanup\n348: \n349: ---\n350: \n351: ### Requirement: Health handlers\n352: \n353: The system SHALL implement health endpoints for Kubernetes probes.\n354: \n355: #### Scenario: handleHealthLive\n356: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n357: - **WHEN** calling `/health/live`\n358: - **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n359: - AND body SHALL be `{\"status\":\"alive\"}`\n360: \n361: #### Scenario: handleHealthReady sessionManager nil\n362: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n363: - **WHEN** calling `/health/ready` with `sessionManager == nil`\n364: - **THEN** HTTP `503` SHALL be returned\n365: - AND body SHALL indicate service unavailable\n366: \n367: #### Scenario: handleHealthReady sessionManager set\n368: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n369: - **WHEN** calling `/health/ready` with valid `sessionManager`\n370: - **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n371: - AND body SHALL be `{\"status\":\"ready\"}`\n372: \n373: ---\n374: \n375: ### Requirement: Invocation handler\n376: \n377: The system SHALL implement invocation handler for proxying requests to sandboxes.\n378: \n379: #### Scenario: handleInvoke extracts session ID\n380: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n381: - **WHEN** processing invocation request\n382: - **THEN** `x-agentcube-session-id` header SHALL be read\n383: - AND session ID SHALL be extracted for session resolution\n384: \n385: #### Scenario: handleInvoke resolves session\n386: - **GIVEN** request with session ID header\n387: - **WHEN** processing invocation\n388: - **THEN** `sessionManager.GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)` SHALL be called\n389: - AND `namespace`, `name`, `kind` SHALL be extracted from URL path\n390: \n391: #### Scenario: handleInvoke creates new session\n392: - **GIVEN** request without session ID header\n393: - **WHEN** processing invocation\n394: - **THEN** new session ID SHALL be generated\n395: - AND new sandbox SHALL be created via session manager\n396: \n397: #### Scenario: handleInvoke proxies request\n398: - **GIVEN** resolved `SandboxInfo`\n399: - **WHEN** processing invocation\n400: - **THEN** reverse proxy SHALL forward request to `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints[0].Endpoint`\n401: - AND request body SHALL be forwarded unchanged\n402: \n403: #### Scenario: handleInvoke updates activity\n404: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n405: - **WHEN** invocation completes\n406: - **THEN** `store.UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID)` SHALL be called\n407: - AND `LastActivity` timestamp SHALL be updated twice:\n408:   - After sandbox resolution\n409:   - After proxy completion\n410: \n411: #### Scenario: handleInvoke error mapping\n412: - **GIVEN** an error from session resolution or proxy\n413: - **WHEN** returning response\n414: - **THEN** error type SHALL map to HTTP code:\n415:   - `SessionNotFoundError` → `404`\n416:   - `SandboxUnreachableError` → `502`\n417:   - `TimeoutError` → `504`\n418:   - `JWTSigningFailedError` → `500`\n419: \n420: ---\n421: \n422: ### Requirement: Error types\n423: \n424: The system SHALL define custom error types for categorizing failures.\n425: \n426: #### Scenario: SessionNotFoundError\n427: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n428: - **WHEN** reading error types\n429: - **THEN** `SessionNotFoundError` SHALL be defined\n430: - AND error code SHALL be `SESSION_NOT_FOUND`\n431: \n432: #### Scenario: SandboxUnreachableError\n433: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n434: - **WHEN** reading error types\n435: - **THEN** `SandboxUnreachableError` SHALL be defined\n436: - AND error code SHALL be `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE`\n437: \n438: #### Scenario: TimeoutError\n439: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n440: - **WHEN** reading error types\n441: - **THEN** `TimeoutError` SHALL be defined\n442: - AND error code SHALL be `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT`\n443: \n444: #### Scenario: JWTSigningFailedError\n445: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n446: - **WHEN** reading error types\n447: - **THEN** `JWTSigningFailedError` SHALL be defined\n448: - AND error code SHALL be `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED`\n449: \n450: #### Scenario: ServerOverloadedError\n451: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n452: - **WHEN** reading error types\n453: - **THEN** `ServerOverloadedError` SHALL be defined\n454: - AND error code SHALL be `SERVER_OVERLOADED`\n455: \n456: #### Scenario: APIStatus interface\n457: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n458: - **WHEN** reading error types\n459: - **THEN** `APIStatus` interface SHALL be defined with:\n460:   - `Status() int` for HTTP status code\n461:   - `Code() string` for error code\n462:   - `Message() string` for error message\n463: \n464: ---\n465: \n466: ### Requirement: Store interface usage\n467: \n468: The system SHALL use Store interface for session state operations.\n469: \n470: #### Scenario: Store interface methods\n471: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n472: - **WHEN** using Store interface\n473: - **THEN** methods SHALL be used:\n474:   - `GetSession(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n475:   - `CreateSession(ctx, sandboxInfo) error`\n476:   - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID) error`\n477: \n478: ---\n479: \n480: ### Requirement: Environment variables\n481: \n482: The system SHALL read configuration from environment variables.\n483: \n484: #### Scenario: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n485: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n486: - **WHEN** initializing SessionManager\n487: - **THEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable SHALL be required\n488: - AND startup SHALL fail if not set\n489: \n490: #### Scenario: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n491: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n492: - **WHEN** determining namespace for sandbox creation\n493: - **THEN** `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` environment variable SHALL be read\n494: - AND default SHALL be `\"default\"` if not set\n495: \n496: ---\n497: \n498: ### Requirement: Constants\n499: \n500: The system SHALL define constants for configuration values.\n501: \n502: #### Scenario: rsaKeySize constant\n503: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n504: - **WHEN** reading constants\n505: - **THEN** `rsaKeySize` SHALL be `2048`\n506: \n507: #### Scenario: jwtExpiration constant\n508: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n509: - **WHEN** reading constants\n510: - **THEN** `jwtExpiration` SHALL be `5 * time.Minute`\n511: \n512: #### Scenario: IdentitySecretName constant\n513: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n514: - **WHEN** reading constants\n515: - **THEN** `IdentitySecretName` SHALL be `\"picod-router-identity\"`\n516: \n517: ---\n518: \n519: ### Requirement: Unit tests for Server\n520: \n521: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for Server behavior.\n522: \n523: #### Scenario: TestNewServer\n524: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server_test.go`\n525: - **WHEN** running tests\n526: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n527:   - Constructor returns valid instance\n528:   - Gin mode is set correctly based on Debug config\n529:   - All fields are properly initialized\n530: \n531: #### Scenario: TestServer_StartTLS\n532: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server_test.go`\n533: - **WHEN** running tests\n534: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n535:   - TLS server starts with valid cert/key\n536:   - Error returned for missing cert/key files\n537: \n538: #### Scenario: TestServer_GracefulShutdown\n539: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server_test.go`\n540: - **WHEN** running tests\n541: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n542:   - Server stops on context cancellation\n543:   - Shutdown deadline is 10s\n544:   - Existing requests complete before shutdown\n545: \n546: #### Scenario: TestServer_Routes\n547: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server_test.go`\n548: - **WHEN** running tests\n549: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n550:   - Health routes are registered\n551:   - Invocation routes are registered\n552:   - Middleware chain is applied\n553: \n554: ---\n555: \n556: ### Requirement: Unit tests for SessionManager\n557: \n558: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for SessionManager.\n559: \n560: #### Scenario: TestNewSessionManager\n561: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go`\n562: - **WHEN** running tests\n563: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n564:   - Constructor returns valid instance\n565:   - Fails when WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL not set\n566:   - HTTP client configured correctly\n567: \n568: #### Scenario: TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_Existing\n569: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go`\n570: - **WHEN** running tests with existing session\n571: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n572:   - Store lookup is called\n573:   - SandboxInfo returned correctly\n574: \n575: #### Scenario: TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_Create\n576: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go`\n577: - **WHEN** running tests with missing session\n578: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n579:   - POST request sent to Workload Manager\n580:   - Correct endpoint based on kind\n581:   - Sandbox created and stored\n582: \n583: #### Scenario: TestSessionManager_createSandbox\n584: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go`\n585: - **WHEN** running tests\n586: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n587:   - Request body is CreateSandboxRequest\n588:   - K8s SA token added when available\n589:   - Error handling for failed requests\n590: \n591: ---\n592: \n593: ### Requirement: Unit tests for ReverseProxy\n594: \n595: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for reverse proxy.\n596: \n597: #### Scenario: TestReverseProxy_Director\n598: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go`\n599: - **WHEN** running tests\n600: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n601:   - Path normalization adds leading slash\n602:   - Forwarding headers are set\n603:   - JWT is injected\n604: \n605: #### Scenario: TestReverseProxy_ModifyResponse\n606: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go`\n607: - **WHEN** running tests\n608: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n609:   - Session ID header added to response\n610: \n611: #### Scenario: TestReverseProxy_ErrorHandler\n612: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go`\n613: - **WHEN** running tests\n614: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n615:   - Connection refused → 502\n616:   - Timeout → 504\n617:   - Other errors → 500\n618: \n619: ---\n620: \n621: ### Requirement: Unit tests for JWTManager\n622: \n623: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for JWT operations.\n624: \n625: #### Scenario: TestJWTManager_GenerateToken\n626: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n627: - **WHEN** running tests\n628: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n629:   - Token contains correct claims\n630:   - Token is signed with RS256\n631:   - Token expires in 5 minutes\n632: \n633: #### Scenario: TestJWTManager_RSAKeyGeneration\n634: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n635: - **WHEN** running tests\n636: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n637:   - Key size is 2048 bits\n638:   - Keys are valid RSA keys\n639: \n640: #### Scenario: TestJWTManager_TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret\n641: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n642: - **WHEN** running tests\n643: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n644:   - Secret created when not exists\n645:   - Secret loaded when exists\n646:   - AlreadyExists handled gracefully\n647: \n648: ---\n649: \n650: ### Requirement: Unit tests for Middleware\n651: \n652: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for concurrency middleware.\n653: \n654: #### Scenario: TestConcurrencyLimitMiddleware\n655: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/middleware_test.go`\n656: - **WHEN** running tests\n657: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n658:   - Requests proceed when slots available\n659:   - 429 returned when full\n660:   - Slots released after request completes\n661: \n662: #### Scenario: TestConcurrencyLimitMiddleware_DefaultCapacity\n663: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/middleware_test.go`\n664: - **WHEN** running tests with MaxConcurrentRequests <= 0\n665: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n666:   - Capacity defaults to 1000\n667: \n668: ---\n669: \n670: ### Requirement: Unit tests for Handlers\n671: \n672: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for handlers.\n673: \n674: #### Scenario: TestHandleHealthLive\n675: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers_test.go`\n676: - **WHEN** running tests\n677: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n678:   - Returns 200 with {\"status\":\"alive\"}\n679: \n680: #### Scenario: TestHandleHealthReady\n681: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers_test.go`\n682: - **WHEN** running tests\n683: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n684:   - Returns 200 when sessionManager valid\n685:   - Returns 503 when sessionManager nil\n686: \n687: #### Scenario: TestHandleInvoke\n688: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers_test.go`\n689: - **WHEN** running tests\n690: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n691:   - Session ID extracted from header\n692:   - New session created when missing\n693:   - Request proxied to sandbox endpoint\n694:   - Activity timestamp updated\n695: \n696: ---\n697: \n698: ### Requirement: Unit tests for Errors\n699: \n700: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for error types.\n701: \n702: #### Scenario: TestErrorTypes\n703: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors_test.go`\n704: - **WHEN** running tests\n705: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n706:   - All error types implement APIStatus\n707:   - Status codes are correct\n708:   - Error codes are correct\n709: \n710: ---\n711: \n712: ### Requirement: File structure\n713: \n714: The system SHALL organize router files correctly.\n715: \n716: #### Scenario: server.go location\n717: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n718: - **WHEN** listing files\n719: - **THEN** `server.go` SHALL exist with Server implementation\n720: \n721: #### Scenario: config.go location\n722: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n723: - **WHEN** listing files\n724: - **THEN** `config.go` SHALL exist with Config struct\n725: \n726: #### Scenario: session_manager.go location\n727: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n728: - **WHEN** listing files\n729: - **THEN** `session_manager.go` SHALL exist with SessionManager\n730: \n731: #### Scenario: reverse_proxy.go location\n732: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n733: - **WHEN** listing files\n734: - **THEN** `reverse_proxy.go` SHALL exist with proxy implementation\n735: \n736: #### Scenario: jwt.go location\n737: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n738: - **WHEN** listing files\n739: - **THEN** `jwt.go` SHALL exist with JWTManager\n740: \n741: #### Scenario: middleware.go location\n742: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n743: - **WHEN** listing files\n744: - **THEN** `middleware.go` SHALL exist with concurrency middleware\n745: \n746: #### Scenario: handlers.go location\n747: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n748: - **WHEN** listing files\n749: - **THEN** `handlers.go` SHALL exist with health and invocation handlers\n750: \n751: #### Scenario: errors.go location\n752: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n753: - **WHEN** listing files\n754: - **THEN** `errors.go` SHALL exist with error types\n755: \n756: #### Scenario: Test files location\n757: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n758: - **WHEN** listing files\n759: - **THEN** `*_test.go` SHALL exist for each implementation file\n760: \n761: ---\n762: \n763: ## Implementation Files\n764: \n765: | File | Purpose |\n766: |------|---------|\n767: | `pkg/router/server.go` | HTTP Server with Gin engine, route registration, lifecycle |\n768: | `pkg/router/server_test.go` | Server unit tests |\n769: | `pkg/router/config.go` | Config struct with Port, TLS, MaxConcurrentRequests |\n770: | `pkg/router/config_test.go` | Config unit tests |\n771: | `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | SessionManager interface and implementation |\n772: | `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go` | SessionManager unit tests |\n773: | `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go` | Reverse proxy with Director, ModifyResponse, ErrorHandler |\n774: | `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go` | Reverse proxy unit tests |\n775: | `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWTManager with RSA key generation, token signing |\n776: | `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` | JWT unit tests |\n777: | `pkg/router/middleware.go` | Concurrency limit middleware |\n778: | `pkg/router/middleware_test.go` | Middleware unit tests |\n779: | `pkg/router/handlers.go` | Health and invocation handlers |\n780: | `pkg/router/handlers_test.go` | Handlers unit tests |\n781: | `pkg/router/errors.go` | Error types with APIStatus interface |\n782: | `pkg/router/errors_test.go` | Error types unit tests |\n783: | `pkg/router/doc.go` | Package documentation |\n784: \n785: ---\n786: \n787: ## Dependencies\n788: \n789: | Package | Purpose |\n790: |---------|---------|\n791: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP framework for routing and middleware |\n792: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | RS256 JWT signing |\n793: | `golang.org/x/net/http2` | h2c server configuration |\n794: | `net/http/httputil` | ReverseProxy for request forwarding |\n795: | `crypto/rsa` | RSA key generation and signing |\n796: | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Core Kubernetes API for Secret management |\n797: | `pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response, kind constants |\n798: | `pkg/store` | Store interface for session lookup and activity updates |\n799: \n800: ---\n801: \n802: ## Request Flow\n803: \n804: ```\n805: Client Request\n806: │\n807: ├── Middleware Chain\n808: │   ├── concurrencyLimitMiddleware (semaphore acquire)\n809: │   ├── loggingMiddleware\n810: │   └── recoveryMiddleware\n811: │\n812: ├── Handler: handleInvoke\n813: │   ├── Extract session ID from x-agentcube-session-id header\n814: │   ├── If missing: Generate new session ID\n815: │   │\n816: │   ├── SessionManager.GetSandboxBySession\n817: │   │   ├── Check store for existing session\n818: │   │   ├── If not found: createSandbox\n819: │   │   │   ├── POST to Workload Manager\n820: │   │   │   │   ├── /v1/agent-runtime (AgentRuntime)\n821: │   │   │   │   └── /v1/code-interpreter (CodeInterpreter)\n822: │   │   │   ├── With K8s SA token if available\n823: │   │   │   └── Store sandbox info\n824: │   │   └── Update activity timestamp (1st)\n825: │   │\n826: │   ├── ReverseProxy.ServeHTTP\n827: │   │   ├── Director\n828: │   │   │   ├── Path normalization (add leading slash)\n829: │   │   │   ├── Set Host, X-Forwarded-For, X-Real-IP\n830: │   │   │   ├── JWTManager.GenerateToken → Authorization header\n831: │   │   │   └── Target: SandboxInfo.EntryPoints[0].Endpoint\n832: │   │   ├── Forward to sandbox pod\n833: │   │   ├── ModifyResponse\n834: │   │   │   └── Add x-agentcube-session-id header\n835: │   │   └── ErrorHandler\n836: │   │       ├── Connection refused → 502\n837: │   │       └── Timeout → 504\n838: │   │\n839: │   └── Update activity timestamp (2nd)\n840: │\n841: └── Middleware Chain (exit)\n842:     └── concurrencyLimitMiddleware (semaphore release)\n843: ```\n844: \n845: ---\n846: \n847: ## Error Mapping\n848: \n849: | Error Type | HTTP Status | Error Code | Condition |\n850: |------------|-------------|------------|-----------|\n851: | `SessionNotFoundError` | 404 | `SESSION_NOT_FOUND` | Session not in store |\n852: | `SandboxUnreachableError` | 502 | `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE` | Connection refused to pod |\n853: | `TimeoutError` | 504 | `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT` | Proxy timeout |\n854: | `JWTSigningFailedError` | 500 | `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED` | JWT generation failure |\n855: | `ServerOverloadedError` | 429 | `SERVER_OVERLOADED` | Semaphore full |\n856: | `NoEntryPointError` | 404 | `NO_ENTRY_POINT` | Empty EntryPoints array |\n857: \n858: ---\n859: \n860: ## Configuration Values\n861: \n862: | Parameter | Default | Source | Description |\n863: |-----------|---------|--------|-------------|\n864: | `Port` | 8080 | Config | Listening port |\n865: | `EnableTLS` | false | Config | TLS enablement |\n866: | `TLSCert` | \"\" | Config | Certificate file path |\n867: | `TLSKey` | \"\" | Config | Private key file path |\n868: | `MaxConcurrentRequests` | 1000 | Config | Semaphore capacity |\n869: | `ReadTimeout` | 30s | Server | HTTP read timeout |\n870: | `IdleTimeout` | 90s | Server | HTTP idle timeout |\n871: | `ShutdownTimeout` | 10s | Server | Graceful shutdown deadline |\n872: | `rsaKeySize` | 2048 | Const | RSA key bits |\n873: | `jwtExpiration` | 5m | Const | JWT validity duration |\n874: | `IdentitySecretName` | picod-router-identity | Const | JWT Secret name |\n875: | `HttpClientTimeout` | 2m | SessionManager | HTTP client timeout |\n876: | `MaxIdleConnsPerHost` | 100 | SessionManager | Connection pool size |\n877: | `HTTP2ReadIdleTimeout` | 30s | SessionManager | HTTP2 read idle |\n878: | `HTTP2PingTimeout` | 15s | SessionManager | HTTP2 ping timeout |\n879: \n880: ---\n881: \n882: ## Environment Variables\n883: \n884: | Variable | Required | Default | Usage |\n885: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n886: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Yes | - | Workload Manager service URL |\n887: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | No | default | Namespace for sandbox creation |\n888: \n889: ---\n890: \n891: ## Validation Checklist\n892: \n893: - [ ] Server struct defined with all required fields\n894: - [ ] Config struct with Port, TLS, MaxConcurrentRequests\n895: - [ ] NewServer constructor initializes Gin engine\n896: - [ ] Gin mode set based on Debug config\n897: - [ ] Server.Start supports TLS and non-TLS\n898: - [ ] Graceful shutdown with 10s deadline\n899: - [ ] Health routes registered (/health/live, /health/ready)\n900: - [ ] Invocation routes registered with GET and POST\n901: - [ ] Middleware chain applied (concurrency, logging, recovery)\n902: - [ ] SessionManager interface defined\n903: - [ ] GetSandboxBySession resolves or creates sessions\n904: - [ ] createSandbox POST to Workload Manager\n905: - [ ] K8s SA token added for in-cluster auth\n906: - [ ] ReverseProxy with custom Director\n907: - [ ] Director normalizes path and injects JWT\n908: - [ ] ModifyResponse adds session header\n909: - [ ] ErrorHandler maps errors to HTTP codes\n910: - [ ] JWTManager with RSA key generation\n911: - [ ] GenerateToken with RS256, 5m expiration\n912: - [ ] TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret handles creation/loading\n913: - [ ] AlreadyExists handled for concurrent routers\n914: - [ ] concurrencyLimitMiddleware with semaphore\n915: - [ ] 429 returned when overloaded\n916: - [ ] handleHealthLive returns 200\n917: - [ ] handleHealthReady checks sessionManager\n918: - [ ] handleInvoke proxies to sandbox\n919: - [ ] Activity timestamp updated twice\n920: - [ ] Error types implement APIStatus\n921: - [ ] WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL required\n922: - [ ] AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE with default\n923: - [ ] Constants defined (rsaKeySize, jwtExpiration, IdentitySecretName)\n924: - [ ] Unit tests for all components\n925: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n926: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n927: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n\n(End of file - total 927 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心\n\n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the HTTP reverse proxy core for the AgentCube Router component. This provides session-aware routing that resolves session IDs from request headers, creates sandboxes via Workload Manager, forwards HTTP requests to sandbox pod endpoints using `httputil.ReverseProxy`, generates RS256-signed JWT tokens, updates session activity timestamps, and limits concurrent requests via semaphore middleware.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Server type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `Server` as an HTTP server with Gin engine for reverse proxy routing.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775864807134,"end":1775864807147}}}}
