{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775864811195,"sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","part":{"id":"prt_d79ca8eb8001W65X3nVlCOOL3x","messageID":"msg_d79ca7f24001sR3XA6SUiDCUPb","sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864816421,"sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","part":{"id":"prt_d79ca9739001Xh7FcJEoLhNknJ","messageID":"msg_d79ca7f24001sR3XA6SUiDCUPb","sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-8101cea04b384891b6793cd6d0b9bbbc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the Sandbox creation handler that processes sandbox creation requests for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, including pod creation, session management, status updates, and warm pool handling.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: SandboxHandler type definition\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define `SandboxHandler` as an HTTP handler for sandbox creation operations.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: SandboxHandler struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `SandboxHandler` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `client clientset.Interface` for Kubernetes API access\n26:   - `kubeClient kubernetes.Interface` for core Kubernetes API\n27:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n28:   - `namespace string` for default namespace\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: NewSandboxHandler constructor\n31: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n32: - **WHEN** calling `NewSandboxHandler(client clientset.Interface, kubeClient kubernetes.Interface, logger Logger, namespace string)`\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*SandboxHandler` with all fields initialized\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: Handler registration interface\n38: \n39: The system SHALL implement `Handler` interface for route registration.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Handler interface implementation\n42: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n43: - **WHEN** examining `SandboxHandler`\n44: - **THEN** it SHALL implement `Register(r chi.Router)` method from `workloadmanager.Handler` interface\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Register method routes\n47: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxHandler` instance\n48: - **WHEN** calling `Register(r chi.Router)`\n49: - **THEN** it SHALL register the following routes:\n50:   - `POST /api/v1/sandboxes` for sandbox creation\n51:   - `GET /api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` for sandbox retrieval\n52:   - `DELETE /api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` for sandbox deletion\n53:   - `GET /api/v1/sandboxes` for sandbox listing\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ### Requirement: CreateSandboxRequest type definition\n58: \n59: The system SHALL define request types for sandbox creation API.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: CreateSandboxRequest struct definition\n62: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n63: - **WHEN** reading the `CreateSandboxRequest` struct\n64: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n65:   - `Name string` with JSON tag `name` (required)\n66:   - `RuntimeName string` with JSON tag `runtimeName` (required)\n67:   - `RuntimeKind string` with JSON tag `runtimeKind` (required, enum: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n68:   - `SessionID string` with JSON tag `sessionId` (optional)\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: RuntimeKind validation\n71: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n72: - **WHEN** examining the `RuntimeKind` field\n73: - **THEN** valid values SHALL be `\"AgentRuntime\"` and `\"CodeInterpreter\"`\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: SandboxResponse type definition\n78: \n79: The system SHALL define response types for sandbox API.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: SandboxResponse struct definition\n82: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n83: - **WHEN** reading the `SandboxResponse` struct\n84: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n85:   - `Name string` with JSON tag `name`\n86:   - `PodName string` with JSON tag `podName`\n87:   - `Namespace string` with JSON tag `namespace`\n88:   - `Status string` with JSON tag `status`\n89:   - `SessionID string` with JSON tag `sessionId`\n90:   - `CreatedAt time.Time` with JSON tag `createdAt`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: SandboxListResponse struct definition\n93: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n94: - **WHEN** reading the `SandboxListResponse` struct\n95: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain field `Items []SandboxResponse` with JSON tag `items`\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ### Requirement: Sandbox creation logic\n100: \n101: The system SHALL create Kubernetes Pods based on AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter templates.\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: Retrieve AgentRuntime spec\n104: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with `RuntimeKind=\"AgentRuntime\"`\n105: - **WHEN** processing the sandbox creation request\n106: - **THEN** `SandboxHandler.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, runtimeName, metav1.GetOptions{})` SHALL be called to retrieve the AgentRuntime\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Retrieve CodeInterpreter spec\n109: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with `RuntimeKind=\"CodeInterpreter\"`\n110: - **WHEN** processing the sandbox creation request\n111: - **THEN** `SandboxHandler.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(ctx, runtimeName, metav1.GetOptions{})` SHALL be called to retrieve the CodeInterpreter\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Pod creation from AgentRuntime template\n114: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime spec with `Template *SandboxTemplate`\n115: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n116: - **THEN** the Pod SHALL be created using `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Create(ctx, pod, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n117: - AND the Pod's `Spec` SHALL be derived from `AgentRuntime.Spec.Template.Spec`\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: Pod creation from CodeInterpreter template\n120: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter spec with `Template *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`\n121: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n122: - **THEN** the Pod SHALL be created using `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Create(ctx, pod, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n123: - AND the Pod's container image SHALL be from `CodeInterpreter.Spec.Template.Image`\n124: \n125: ---\n126: \n127: ### Requirement: Label application\n128: \n129: The system SHALL apply required labels to sandbox pods according to shared_types.go constants.\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: Owner runtime label\n132: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created\n133: - **WHEN** applying labels\n134: - **THEN** label `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime` SHALL be set to the runtime name\n135: \n136: #### Scenario: Owner kind label\n137: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created\n138: - **WHEN** applying labels\n139: - **THEN** label `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-kind` SHALL be set to `RuntimeKind` value\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Sandbox type label for AgentRuntime\n142: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created for AgentRuntime\n143: - **WHEN** applying labels\n144: - **THEN** label `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type` SHALL be set to `\"agent\"`\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Sandbox type label for CodeInterpreter\n147: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created for CodeInterpreter\n148: - **WHEN** applying labels\n149: - **THEN** label `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type` SHALL be set to `\"code-interpreter\"`\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: Session ID label\n152: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created with `SessionID`\n153: - **WHEN** applying labels\n154: - **THEN** label `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-id` SHALL be set to the session ID\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: Merge template labels\n157: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter with template labels\n158: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n159: - **THEN** template labels SHALL be merged with system labels\n160: - AND system labels SHALL not be overridden by template labels\n161: \n162: ---\n163: \n164: ### Requirement: Annotation application\n165: \n166: The system SHALL apply required annotations to sandbox pods.\n167: \n168: #### Scenario: Session start annotation\n169: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created\n170: - **WHEN** applying annotations\n171: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-start` SHALL be set to current timestamp in RFC3339 format\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Last activity annotation\n174: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created\n175: - **WHEN** applying annotations\n176: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity` SHALL be set to current timestamp\n177: \n178: #### Scenario: Auth mode annotation for CodeInterpreter\n179: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter sandbox pod being created\n180: - **WHEN** applying annotations\n181: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/auth-mode` SHALL be set to `CodeInterpreter.Spec.AuthMode`\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: Merge template annotations\n184: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter with template annotations\n185: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n186: - **THEN** template annotations SHALL be merged with system annotations\n187: - AND system annotations SHALL not be overridden by template annotations\n188: \n189: ---\n190: \n191: ### Requirement: Pod naming convention\n192: \n193: The system SHALL generate unique pod names for sandboxes.\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Pod name format\n196: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with `Name=\"my-sandbox\"`\n197: - **WHEN** generating the pod name\n198: - **THEN** the pod name SHALL follow format `{sandbox-name}-{randomSuffix}`\n199: - AND the random suffix SHALL be 5 characters alphanumeric\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Pod name uniqueness\n202: - **GIVEN** an existing pod with the same sandbox name\n203: - **WHEN** creating a new sandbox\n204: - **THEN** the pod name SHALL be unique due to random suffix\n205: \n206: ---\n207: \n208: ### Requirement: Validation error handling\n209: \n210: The system SHALL validate request parameters and return appropriate errors.\n211: \n212: #### Scenario: Missing name validation\n213: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with empty `Name`\n214: - **WHEN** processing the request\n215: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 400 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"VALIDATION_ERROR\"`\n216: - AND `Details.field` SHALL be `\"name\"`\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: Missing runtimeName validation\n219: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with empty `RuntimeName`\n220: - **WHEN** processing the request\n221: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 400 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"VALIDATION_ERROR\"`\n222: - AND `Details.field` SHALL be `\"runtimeName\"`\n223: \n224: #### Scenario: Invalid RuntimeKind validation\n225: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with `RuntimeKind=\"InvalidKind\"`\n226: - **WHEN** processing the request\n227: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 400 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"VALIDATION_ERROR\"`\n228: - AND `Details.field` SHALL be `\"runtimeKind\"`\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: Runtime not found\n231: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with non-existent `RuntimeName`\n232: - **WHEN** processing the request\n233: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 404 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"NOT_FOUND\"`\n234: \n235: ---\n236: \n237: ### Requirement: Sandbox retrieval\n238: \n239: The system SHALL retrieve sandbox pod information.\n240: \n241: #### Scenario: Get sandbox by name\n242: - **GIVEN** a GET request to `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}`\n243: - **WHEN** processing the request\n244: - **THEN** the handler SHALL list pods with label selector `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime={runtimeName}`\n245: - AND return `SandboxResponse` for the matching pod\n246: \n247: #### Scenario: Sandbox not found\n248: - **GIVEN** a GET request for a non-existent sandbox\n249: - **WHEN** processing the request\n250: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 404 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"NOT_FOUND\"`\n251: \n252: #### Scenario: List sandboxes\n253: - **GIVEN** a GET request to `/api/v1/sandboxes`\n254: - **WHEN** processing the request\n255: - **THEN** the handler SHALL list all pods with label selector containing `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type`\n256: - AND return `SandboxListResponse` with all matching pods\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: List sandboxes by runtime\n259: - **GIVEN** a GET request to `/api/v1/sandboxes?runtimeName={runtimeName}`\n260: - **WHEN** processing the request\n261: - **THEN** the handler SHALL list pods with label selector `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime={runtimeName}`\n262: \n263: ---\n264: \n265: ### Requirement: Sandbox deletion\n266: \n267: The system SHALL delete sandbox pods.\n268: \n269: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox\n270: - **GIVEN** a DELETE request to `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}`\n271: - **WHEN** processing the request\n272: - **THEN** the handler SHALL find the pod by sandbox name\n273: - AND call `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Delete(ctx, podName, metav1.DeleteOptions{})`\n274: \n275: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox with grace period\n276: - **GIVEN** a DELETE request with query parameter `gracePeriodSeconds=30`\n277: - **WHEN** processing the request\n278: - **THEN** `DeleteOptions.GracePeriodSeconds` SHALL be set to 30\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: Sandbox deletion updates session annotation\n281: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being deleted\n282: - **WHEN** the pod is found before deletion\n283: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-end` SHALL be set to current timestamp\n284: - AND the pod SHALL be updated before deletion\n285: \n286: ---\n287: \n288: ### Requirement: Warm pool handling for CodeInterpreter\n289: \n290: The system SHALL support warm pool management for CodeInterpreter sandboxes.\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: Check warm pool availability\n293: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `WarmPoolSize > 0`\n294: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n295: - **THEN** the handler SHALL check for available warm pool pods with annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/warm-pool-member=true`\n296: \n297: #### Scenario: Use warm pool pod\n298: - **GIVEN** an available warm pool pod exists\n299: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n300: - **THEN** the handler SHALL update the warm pool pod instead of creating a new pod\n301: - AND remove `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/warm-pool-member` annotation\n302: - AND set `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-id` label\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: Warm pool pod not available\n305: - **GIVEN** no warm pool pod is available\n306: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n307: - **THEN** the handler SHALL create a new pod normally\n308: \n309: #### Scenario: Warm pool annotation for new pods\n310: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter sandbox pod created outside warm pool usage\n311: - **WHEN** the pod is created\n312: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/warm-pool-member` SHALL NOT be set\n313: \n314: ---\n315: \n316: ### Requirement: Port configuration\n317: \n318: The system SHALL configure container ports based on TargetPort definitions.\n319: \n320: #### Scenario: Add container ports\n321: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `Spec.Ports []TargetPort`\n322: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n323: - **THEN** each `TargetPort` SHALL be mapped to a `corev1.ContainerPort` in the pod spec\n324: \n325: #### Scenario: Port name from TargetPort\n326: - **GIVEN** a `TargetPort` with `Name=\"http\"`\n327: - **WHEN** creating the container port\n328: - **THEN** the `corev1.ContainerPort.Name` SHALL be set to `\"http\"`\n329: \n330: #### Scenario: Port number from TargetPort\n331: - **GIVEN** a `TargetPort` with `Port=8080`\n332: - **WHEN** creating the container port\n333: - **THEN** the `corev1.ContainerPort.ContainerPort` SHALL be set to `8080`\n334: \n335: ---\n336: \n337: ### Requirement: RuntimeClassName handling\n338: \n339: The system SHALL apply RuntimeClassName for sandbox pods.\n340: \n341: #### Scenario: RuntimeClassName from CodeInterpreter template\n342: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.RuntimeClassName=\" KataContainers\"`\n343: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n344: - **THEN** `Pod.Spec.RuntimeClassName` SHALL be set to `\"KataContainers\"`\n345: \n346: #### Scenario: RuntimeClassName nil handling\n347: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.RuntimeClassName` nil\n348: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n349: - **THEN** `Pod.Spec.RuntimeClassName` SHALL NOT be set\n350: \n351: ---\n352: \n353: ### Requirement: Image configuration for CodeInterpreter\n354: \n355: The system SHALL configure container image for CodeInterpreter sandboxes.\n356: \n357: #### Scenario: Image from template\n358: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.Image=\"python:3.11\"`\n359: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n360: - **THEN** the container image SHALL be `\"python:3.11\"`\n361: \n362: #### Scenario: ImagePullPolicy from template\n363: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.ImagePullPolicy=\"Always\"`\n364: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n365: - **THEN** the container `ImagePullPolicy` SHALL be `corev1.PullPolicy(\"Always\")`\n366: \n367: #### Scenario: ImagePullSecrets from template\n368: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.ImagePullSecrets`\n369: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n370: - **THEN** `Pod.Spec.ImagePullSecrets` SHALL be set from template\n371: \n372: ---\n373: \n374: ### Requirement: Environment variables handling\n375: \n376: The system SHALL apply environment variables from template.\n377: \n378: #### Scenario: Environment variables from CodeInterpreter template\n379: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.Environment []corev1.EnvVar`\n380: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n381: - **THEN** the container `Env` SHALL include all environment variables from template\n382: \n383: #### Scenario: Environment variables merge\n384: - **GIVEN** system environment variables and template environment variables\n385: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n386: - **THEN** template environment variables SHALL be appended after system environment variables\n387: \n388: ---\n389: \n390: ### Requirement: Resource requirements handling\n391: \n392: The system SHALL apply resource requirements from template.\n393: \n394: #### Scenario: Resources from CodeInterpreter template\n395: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.Resources` containing limits and requests\n396: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n397: - **THEN** the container `Resources` SHALL be set from template\n398: \n399: #### Scenario: Default resources when not specified\n400: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with empty `Template.Resources`\n401: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n402: - **THEN** default resource limits SHALL NOT be applied (let Kubernetes defaults apply)\n403: \n404: ---\n405: \n406: ### Requirement: Command and Args handling\n407: \n408: The system SHALL apply command and args from template.\n409: \n410: #### Scenario: Command from template\n411: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.Command=[\"python\", \"-m\"]`\n412: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n413: - **THEN** the container `Command` SHALL be set to `[\"python\", \"-m\"]`\n414: \n415: #### Scenario: Args from template\n416: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.Args=[\"--port\", \"8080\"]`\n417: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n418: - **THEN** the container `Args` SHALL be set to `[\"--port\", \"8080\"]`\n419: \n420: #### Scenario: Empty Command and Args\n421: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with empty `Command` and `Args`\n422: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n423: - **THEN** the container SHALL use the default entrypoint from the image\n424: \n425: ---\n426: \n427: ### Requirement: Session management\n428: \n429: The system SHALL manage session lifecycle annotations.\n430: \n431: #### Scenario: Session start timestamp\n432: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created for a session\n433: - **WHEN** the pod is created\n434: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-start` SHALL be set\n435: \n436: #### Scenario: Session timeout calculation\n437: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `SessionTimeout=15m`\n438: - **WHEN** calculating session expiration\n439: - **THEN** the expiration time SHALL be `sessionStart + SessionTimeout`\n440: \n441: #### Scenario: Max session duration calculation\n442: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `MaxSessionDuration=8h`\n443: - **WHEN** calculating maximum session expiration\n444: - **THEN** the maximum expiration time SHALL be `sessionStart + MaxSessionDuration`\n445: \n446: ---\n447: \n448: ### Requirement: Error handling and responses\n449: \n450: The system SHALL handle Kubernetes API errors appropriately.\n451: \n452: #### Scenario: Kubernetes API error\n453: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API call returns an error\n454: - **WHEN** processing the sandbox request\n455: - **THEN** the error SHALL be wrapped in `InternalError`\n456: - AND response SHALL be HTTP 500 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"INTERNAL_ERROR\"`\n457: \n458: #### Scenario: Pod already exists\n459: - **GIVEN** a pod with the same name already exists\n460: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox\n461: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 409 Conflict\n462: - AND `ErrorResponse.Code` SHALL be `\"CONFLICT\"`\n463: \n464: #### Scenario: Namespace not found\n465: - **GIVEN** the target namespace does not exist\n466: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox\n467: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 404 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"NOT_FOUND\"`\n468: \n469: ---\n470: \n471: ### Requirement: Request context usage\n472: \n473: The system SHALL use request context for API calls.\n474: \n475: #### Scenario: Context propagation\n476: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request with context\n477: - **WHEN** making Kubernetes API calls\n478: - **THEN** `r.Context()` SHALL be used as the context parameter\n479: \n480: #### Scenario: Context timeout handling\n481: - **GIVEN** a request context that times out\n482: - **WHEN** the Kubernetes API call is in progress\n483: - **THEN** the API call SHALL be cancelled\n484: - AND response SHALL be HTTP 503 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\"`\n485: \n486: ---\n487: \n488: ### Requirement: JSON request parsing\n489: \n490: The system SHALL parse JSON request body correctly.\n491: \n492: #### Scenario: Valid JSON parsing\n493: - **GIVEN** a POST request with valid JSON body\n494: - **WHEN** parsing the request\n495: - **THEN** `json.NewDecoder(r.Body).Decode(&req)` SHALL be used\n496: - AND request body SHALL be closed\n497: \n498: #### Scenario: Invalid JSON parsing\n499: - **GIVEN** a POST request with invalid JSON body\n500: - **WHEN** parsing the request\n501: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 400 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"VALIDATION_ERROR\"`\n502: - AND `Details.reason` SHALL indicate JSON parsing failure\n503: \n504: ---\n505: \n506: ### Requirement: JSON response writing\n507: \n508: The system SHALL write JSON responses correctly.\n509: \n510: #### Scenario: Success response\n511: - **GIVEN** a successful sandbox creation\n512: - **WHEN** writing the response\n513: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 201 Created\n514: - AND `Content-Type` SHALL be `\"application/json\"`\n515: - AND body SHALL be `SandboxResponse` JSON\n516: \n517: #### Scenario: List response\n518: - **GIVEN** a successful sandbox list\n519: - **WHEN** writing the response\n520: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 200 OK\n521: - AND body SHALL be `SandboxListResponse` JSON\n522: \n523: ---\n524: \n525: ### Requirement: Unit tests\n526: \n527: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for SandboxHandler.\n528: \n529: #### Scenario: CreateSandboxRequest validation tests\n530: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n531: - **WHEN** running tests\n532: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n533:   - Missing name returns 400\n534:   - Missing runtimeName returns 400\n535:   - Invalid RuntimeKind returns 400\n536:   - Valid request passes validation\n537: \n538: #### Scenario: Label application tests\n539: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n540: - **WHEN** running tests\n541: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n542:   - Owner runtime label is applied\n543:   - Owner kind label is applied\n544:   - Sandbox type label is correct for AgentRuntime\n545:   - Sandbox type label is correct for CodeInterpreter\n546:   - Template labels are merged correctly\n547: \n548: #### Scenario: Annotation application tests\n549: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n550: - **WHEN** running tests\n551: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n552:   - Session start annotation is applied\n553:   - Last activity annotation is applied\n554:   - Auth mode annotation is applied for CodeInterpreter\n555: \n556: #### Scenario: Pod creation tests\n557: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n558: - **WHEN** running tests\n559: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n560:   - Pod is created with correct spec from AgentRuntime template\n561:   - Pod is created with correct spec from CodeInterpreter template\n562:   - Pod name follows naming convention\n563: \n564: #### Scenario: Warm pool tests\n565: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n566: - **WHEN** running tests\n567: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n568:   - Warm pool pod is reused when available\n569:   - New pod is created when warm pool not available\n570:   - Warm pool annotation is removed on reuse\n571: \n572: ---\n573: \n574: ### Requirement: Integration tests\n575: \n576: The system SHALL have integration tests with fake Kubernetes clients.\n577: \n578: #### Scenario: Full sandbox creation flow\n579: - **GIVEN** a fake clientset with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs\n580: - **WHEN** running integration tests\n581: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify complete sandbox creation from request to pod creation\n582: \n583: #### Scenario: End-to-end API test\n584: - **GIVEN** a running HTTPServer with SandboxHandler\n585: - **WHEN** sending POST request to `/api/v1/sandboxes`\n586: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify correct HTTP response and pod creation\n587: \n588: ---\n589: \n590: ### Requirement: Directory structure\n591: \n592: The system SHALL organize sandbox handler files correctly.\n593: \n594: #### Scenario: Sandbox handler file location\n595: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/`\n596: - **WHEN** listing files\n597: - **THEN** `sandbox.go` SHALL exist with `SandboxHandler` implementation\n598: \n599: #### Scenario: Sandbox handler test file location\n600: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/`\n601: - **WHEN** listing files\n602: - **THEN** `sandbox_test.go` SHALL exist with unit tests\n603: \n604: ---\n605: \n606: ## Implementation Files\n607: \n608: | File | Purpose |\n609: |------|---------|\n610: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go` | SandboxHandler implementation |\n611: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go` | SandboxHandler unit tests |\n612: \n613: ---\n614: \n615: ## Dependencies\n616: \n617: | Package | Purpose |\n618: |---------|---------|\n619: | `client-go/clientset/versioned` | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter typed client |\n620: | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Core Kubernetes API client |\n621: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Pod, Container types |\n622: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | ObjectMeta, ListOptions, CreateOptions |\n623: | `encoding/json` | Request/Response JSON handling |\n624: | `time` | Timestamp handling for annotations |\n625: \n626: ---\n627: \n628: ## API Endpoints\n629: \n630: | Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n631: |----------|--------|---------|\n632: | `/api/v1/sandboxes` | POST | Create a new sandbox |\n633: | `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` | GET | Get sandbox by name |\n634: | `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` | DELETE | Delete sandbox |\n635: | `/api/v1/sandboxes` | GET | List sandboxes |\n636: \n637: ---\n638: \n639: ## Error Codes\n640: \n641: | Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n642: |------|-------------|-------------|\n643: | `VALIDATION_ERROR` | 400 | Invalid request parameter |\n644: | `NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Runtime or sandbox not found |\n645: | `CONFLICT` | 409 | Pod already exists |\n646: | `INTERNAL_ERROR` | 500 | Kubernetes API error |\n647: | `SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE` | 503 | Context timeout or dependency unavailable |\n648: \n649: ---\n650: \n651: ## Label Keys Applied\n652: \n653: | Key | Value Source |\n654: |-----|--------------|\n655: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime` | `RuntimeName` from request |\n656: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-kind` | `RuntimeKind` from request |\n657: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type` | `\"agent\"` or `\"code-interpreter\"` |\n658: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-id` | `SessionID` from request |\n659: \n660: ---\n661: \n662: ## Annotation Keys Applied\n663: \n664: | Key | Value Source |\n665: |-----|--------------|\n666: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-start` | Current timestamp RFC3339 |\n667: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity` | Current timestamp |\n668: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/auth-mode` | `CodeInterpreter.Spec.AuthMode` |\n669: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-end` | Current timestamp (on deletion) |\n670: \n671: ---\n672: \n673: ## Validation Checklist\n674: \n675: - [ ] SandboxHandler implements Handler interface\n676: - [ ] POST `/api/v1/sandboxes` creates pods correctly\n677: - [ ] GET `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` retrieves sandbox info\n678: - [ ] DELETE `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` deletes sandbox pod\n679: - [ ] GET `/api/v1/sandboxes` lists all sandboxes\n680: - [ ] Labels are applied according to shared_types.go constants\n681: - [ ] Annotations are applied correctly\n682: - [ ] Warm pool handling works for CodeInterpreter\n683: - [ ] Port configuration from TargetPort\n684: - [ ] RuntimeClassName handling\n685: - [ ] Environment variables from template\n686: - [ ] Resource requirements from template\n687: - [ ] Command and Args from template\n688: - [ ] Validation errors return correct HTTP status\n689: - [ ] Kubernetes API errors handled correctly\n690: - [ ] Context propagated to API calls\n691: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n692: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n693: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n694: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n\n(End of file - total 694 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the Sandbox creation handler that processes sandbox creation requests for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, including pod creation, session management, status updates, and warm pool handling.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: SandboxHandler type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `SandboxHandler` as an HTTP handler for sandbox creation operations.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775864816392,"end":1775864816419}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864816425,"sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","part":{"id":"prt_d79caa2ef0010ATs6DnnvebLFP","messageID":"msg_d79ca7f24001sR3XA6SUiDCUPb","sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-9fcf87de6c834dabaa844b71f95d0b61","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the Sandbox Garbage Collector that periodically scans and deletes expired and idle sandboxes. The GC runs as a background goroutine with configurable intervals, enforces TTL via `ExpiresAt` timestamps, handles idle timeout cleanup via `LastActivity`, and limits batch operations to prevent cluster overload.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: GarbageCollector type definition\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define `GarbageCollector` as a background process for periodic sandbox cleanup.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: GarbageCollector struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `GarbageCollector` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `manager *SandboxLifecycleManager` for sandbox deletion delegation\n26:   - `interval time.Duration` for GC cycle interval\n27:   - `onceTimeout time.Duration` for single GC cycle timeout\n28:   - `stopCh chan struct{}` for graceful shutdown signal\n29:   - `wg sync.WaitGroup` for goroutine synchronization\n30:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n31:   - `idleTimeout time.Duration` for idle sandbox cleanup threshold\n32:   - `idleMu sync.RWMutex` for idleTimeout concurrent access protection\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: NewGarbageCollector constructor\n35: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n36: - **WHEN** calling `NewGarbageCollector(manager, interval, onceTimeout, logger)`\n37: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*GarbageCollector` with:\n38:   - `interval` defaulted to `GarbageCollectorInterval` (2 minutes) if zero\n39:   - `onceTimeout` defaulted to `2 * time.Minute` if zero\n40:   - `idleTimeout` initialized from `manager.config.DefaultIdleTimeout`\n41:   - `stopCh` initialized as `make(chan struct{})`\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: NewGarbageCollector with custom interval\n44: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n45: - **WHEN** calling `NewGarbageCollector(manager, 5*time.Minute, 3*time.Minute, logger)`\n46: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*GarbageCollector` with:\n47:   - `interval` = `5 * time.Minute`\n48:   - `onceTimeout` = `3 * time.Minute`\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ### Requirement: GarbageCollector lifecycle\n53: \n54: The system SHALL provide Start/Stop lifecycle methods for the GC background goroutine.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Start launches runLoop\n57: - **GIVEN** a `GarbageCollector` instance\n58: - **WHEN** calling `gc.Start()`\n59: - **THEN** `gc.wg.Add(1)` SHALL be called\n60: - AND `gc.runLoop()` SHALL be launched as a goroutine\n61: \n62: #### Scenario: Stop signals shutdown\n63: - **GIVEN** a running `GarbageCollector`\n64: - **WHEN** calling `gc.Stop()`\n65: - **THEN** `close(gc.stopCh)` SHALL be called\n66: - AND `gc.wg.Wait()` SHALL block until goroutine completes\n67: \n68: #### Scenario: runLoop initial execution\n69: - **GIVEN** a started `GarbageCollector`\n70: - **WHEN** `runLoop` begins\n71: - **THEN** `gc.runOnce(context.Background())` SHALL be called immediately\n72: - AND ticker SHALL be created with `time.NewTicker(gc.interval)`\n73: \n74: #### Scenario: runLoop ticker-driven execution\n75: - **GIVEN** a running `runLoop`\n76: - **WHEN** ticker fires\n77: - **THEN** `gc.runOnce(context.Background())` SHALL be called\n78: \n79: #### Scenario: runLoop stops on stopCh\n80: - **GIVEN** a running `runLoop`\n81: - **WHEN** `stopCh` receives signal\n82: - **THEN** `gc.logger.Info(\"garbage collector stopped\")` SHALL be called\n83: - AND goroutine SHALL return\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ### Requirement: runOnce GC cycle\n88: \n89: The system SHALL implement `runOnce` for a single garbage collection cycle.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: runOnce with context timeout\n92: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n93: - **WHEN** calling `runOnce(ctx)`\n94: - **THEN** `context.WithTimeout(ctx, gc.onceTimeout)` SHALL be created\n95: - AND cancel SHALL be deferred\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: runOnce queries expired sandboxes\n98: - **GIVEN** `runOnce` execution\n99: - **WHEN** listing sandboxes for cleanup\n100: - **THEN** `gc.manager.store.ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, now, GCBatchSize)` SHALL be called\n101: - AND result SHALL be limited to `GCBatchSize=16`\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: runOnce queries inactive sandboxes\n104: - **GIVEN** `runOnce` execution\n105: - **WHEN** listing sandboxes for cleanup\n106: - **THEN** `inactiveBefore = now.Add(-idleTimeout)` SHALL be computed\n107: - AND `gc.manager.store.ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, inactiveBefore, GCBatchSize)` SHALL be called\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: runOnce deletes expired sandbox\n110: - **GIVEN** an expired sandbox with `ExpiresAt < now`\n111: - **WHEN** `runOnce` processes it\n112: - **THEN** `gc.manager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID)` SHALL be called\n113: - AND deletion reason SHALL be `DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached`\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: runOnce deletes inactive sandbox\n116: - **GIVEN** an inactive sandbox with `LastActivity < inactiveBefore`\n117: - **WHEN** `runOnce` processes it\n118: - **THEN** `gc.manager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID)` SHALL be called\n119: - AND deletion reason SHALL be `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: runOnce ignores NotFound error\n122: - **GIVEN** a sandbox that no longer exists\n123: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandbox` returns `NotFoundError`\n124: - **THEN** error SHALL be ignored with `continue`\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: runOnce logs deletion success\n127: - **GIVEN** a successfully deleted sandbox\n128: - **WHEN** deletion completes\n129: - **THEN** `gc.logger.Info(\"gc deleted sandbox\", \"sessionID\", ..., \"sandboxName\", ..., \"reason\", ...)` SHALL be called\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: runOnce logs deletion failure\n132: - **GIVEN** a deletion that fails (not NotFound)\n133: - **WHEN** error occurs\n134: - **THEN** `gc.logger.Error(\"gc delete failed\", \"sessionID\", ..., \"err\", ...)` SHALL be called\n135: - AND processing SHALL continue for remaining sandboxes\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ### Requirement: Batch size limitation\n140: \n141: The system SHALL limit cleanup operations per cycle to prevent cluster overload.\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: GCBatchSize constant\n144: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n145: - **WHEN** reading constants\n146: - **THEN** `GCBatchSize` SHALL be `16`\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes respects limit\n149: - **GIVEN** `MemoryStore.ListExpiredSandboxes`\n150: - **WHEN** calling with `limit=16`\n151: - **THEN** result SHALL be truncated to at most `16` sandboxes\n152: - AND sandboxes SHALL be sorted by `ExpiresAt` ascending\n153: \n154: #### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes respects limit\n155: - **GIVEN** `MemoryStore.ListInactiveSandboxes`\n156: - **WHEN** calling with `limit=16`\n157: - **THEN** result SHALL be truncated to at most `16` sandboxes\n158: - AND sandboxes SHALL be sorted by `LastActivity` ascending\n159: \n160: #### Scenario: Combined batch limit\n161: - **GIVEN** 20 expired and 20 inactive sandboxes\n162: - **WHEN** `runOnce` executes\n163: - **THEN** at most `16 + 16 = 32` sandboxes SHALL be processed\n164: - AND remaining sandboxes SHALL be processed in subsequent cycles\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ### Requirement: Store interface extensions\n169: \n170: The system SHALL extend the Store interface with GC-specific query methods.\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: Store interface includes GC methods\n173: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n174: - **WHEN** reading the `Store` interface\n175: - **THEN** interface SHALL include:\n176:   - `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n177:   - `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: MemoryStore ListExpiredSandboxes implementation\n180: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go`\n181: - **WHEN** calling `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n182: - **THEN** all sandboxes with `ExpiresAt.Before(before)` SHALL be returned\n183: - AND result SHALL be sorted by `ExpiresAt` ascending\n184: - AND result SHALL be limited to `limit` entries\n185: \n186: #### Scenario: MemoryStore ListInactiveSandboxes implementation\n187: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go`\n188: - **WHEN** calling `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n189: - **THEN** all sandboxes with non-zero `LastActivity` and `LastActivity.Before(before)` SHALL be returned\n190: - AND result SHALL be sorted by `LastActivity` ascending\n191: - AND result SHALL be limited to `limit` entries\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes skips zero LastActivity\n194: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `LastActivity.IsZero() == true`\n195: - **WHEN** calling `ListInactiveSandboxes`\n196: - **THEN** that sandbox SHALL NOT be included in results\n197: \n198: ---\n199: \n200: ### Requirement: Runtime configuration\n201: \n202: The system SHALL support runtime configuration of GC parameters.\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: SetIdleTimeout method\n205: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n206: - **WHEN** calling `gc.SetIdleTimeout(30 * time.Minute)`\n207: - **THEN** `gc.idleMu.Lock()` SHALL be acquired\n208: - AND `gc.idleTimeout` SHALL be updated to `30 * time.Minute`\n209: - AND mutex SHALL be released\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: getIdleTimeout method\n212: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n213: - **WHEN** calling `gc.getIdleTimeout()`\n214: - **THEN** `gc.idleMu.RLock()` SHALL be acquired\n215: - AND current `idleTimeout` value SHALL be returned\n216: - AND mutex SHALL be released\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: GetStats method\n219: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n220: - **WHEN** calling `gc.GetStats()`\n221: - **THEN** `GarbageCollectorStats` SHALL be returned with:\n222:   - `Interval`: current GC cycle interval\n223:   - `OnceTimeout`: current single-cycle timeout\n224:   - `IdleTimeout`: current idle threshold\n225: \n226: #### Scenario: GarbageCollectorStats struct\n227: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n228: - **WHEN** reading `GarbageCollectorStats`\n229: - **THEN** struct SHALL contain:\n230:   - `Interval time.Duration`\n231:   - `OnceTimeout time.Duration`\n232:   - `IdleTimeout time.Duration`\n233: \n234: ---\n235: \n236: ### Requirement: Deletion reason determination\n237: \n238: The system SHALL categorize deletion reasons for logging and tracking.\n239: \n240: #### Scenario: determineDeletionReason function\n241: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n242: - **WHEN** calling `determineDeletionReason(sandbox, now, idleTimeout)`\n243: - **THEN** it SHALL return `DeletionReason`\n244: \n245: #### Scenario: MaxDurationReached reason\n246: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `now.After(sandbox.ExpiresAt)`\n247: - **WHEN** determining reason\n248: - **THEN** `DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached` SHALL be returned\n249: \n250: #### Scenario: IdleTimeout reason\n251: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with non-zero `LastActivity` and `now.After(sandbox.LastActivity.Add(idleTimeout))`\n252: - **WHEN** determining reason and `ExpiresAt` not yet reached\n253: - **THEN** `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout` SHALL be returned\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: UserRequest fallback reason\n256: - **GIVEN** a sandbox not expired and not idle\n257: - **WHEN** determining reason\n258: - **THEN** `DeletionReasonUserRequest` SHALL be returned as fallback\n259: \n260: ---\n261: \n262: ### Requirement: DeletionReason constants\n263: \n264: The system SHALL define deletion reason constants for categorization.\n265: \n266: #### Scenario: DeletionReasonIdleTimeout constant\n267: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n268: - **WHEN** reading constants\n269: - **THEN** `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout` SHALL be `\"IdleTimeout\"`\n270: \n271: #### Scenario: DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached constant\n272: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n273: - **WHEN** reading constants\n274: - **THEN** `DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached` SHALL be `\"MaxDurationReached\"`\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: DeletionReasonUserRequest constant\n277: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n278: - **WHEN** reading constants\n279: - **THEN** `DeletionReasonUserRequest` SHALL be `\"UserRequest\"`\n280: \n281: ---\n282: \n283: ### Requirement: Default constants\n284: \n285: The system SHALL define default timeout constants.\n286: \n287: #### Scenario: GarbageCollectorInterval constant\n288: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n289: - **WHEN** reading constants\n290: - **THEN** `GarbageCollectorInterval` SHALL be `2 * time.Minute`\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout constant\n293: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n294: - **WHEN** reading constants\n295: - **THEN** `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` SHALL be `15 * time.Minute`\n296: \n297: #### Scenario: DefaultSandboxTTL constant\n298: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n299: - **WHEN** reading constants\n300: - **THEN** `DefaultSandboxTTL` SHALL be `8 * time.Hour`\n301: \n302: ---\n303: \n304: ### Requirement: Concurrent safety\n305: \n306: The system SHALL handle concurrent access safely.\n307: \n308: #### Scenario: idleMu protects idleTimeout\n309: - **GIVEN** `GarbageCollector` with `idleMu sync.RWMutex`\n310: - **WHEN** concurrent reads/writes to `idleTimeout`\n311: - **THEN** `sync.RWMutex` SHALL prevent race conditions\n312: - AND `RLock` SHALL be used for reads\n313: - AND `Lock` SHALL be used for writes\n314: \n315: #### Scenario: Store mutex protection\n316: - **GIVEN** `MemoryStore` with `sync.RWMutex`\n317: - **WHEN** concurrent `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n318: - **THEN** `sync.RWMutex` SHALL prevent race conditions\n319: \n320: #### Scenario: runOnce called from single goroutine\n321: - **GIVEN** `runLoop` design\n322: - **WHEN** GC is running\n323: - **THEN** `runOnce` SHALL only be called from the single `runLoop` goroutine\n324: - AND no concurrent `runOnce` calls SHALL occur from GC itself\n325: \n326: ---\n327: \n328: ### Requirement: Deletion delegation\n329: \n330: The system SHALL delegate actual deletion to SandboxLifecycleManager.\n331: \n332: #### Scenario: DeleteSandbox delegation\n333: - **GIVEN** `runOnce` processing a sandbox\n334: - **WHEN** calling deletion\n335: - **THEN** `gc.manager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sessionID)` SHALL be called\n336: - AND deletion SHALL handle both K8s CR deletion and store cleanup\n337: \n338: #### Scenario: DeleteSandbox handles K8s resources\n339: - **GIVEN** `SandboxLifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox`\n340: - **WHEN** deletion executes\n341: - **THEN** `SandboxGVR` (agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/sandboxes) SHALL be deleted\n342: - AND `SandboxClaimGVR` SHALL be deleted if `Kind == SandboxClaimKind`\n343: \n344: ---\n345: \n346: ### Requirement: Integration with HTTPServer\n347: \n348: The system SHALL integrate GC with the HTTPServer lifecycle.\n349: \n350: #### Scenario: GC created in HTTPServer\n351: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go`\n352: - **WHEN** HTTPServer is initialized\n353: - **THEN** `NewGarbageCollector` SHALL be called with:\n354:   - `manager` = `SandboxLifecycleManager`\n355:   - `interval` = `config.GCInterval`\n356:   - `onceTimeout` = `config.GCOnceTimeout`\n357:   - `logger` = server logger\n358: \n359: #### Scenario: GC started on server start\n360: - **GIVEN** HTTPServer with GC\n361: - **WHEN** server starts\n362: - **THEN** `gc.Start()` SHALL be called\n363: \n364: #### Scenario: GC stopped on server shutdown\n365: - **GIVEN** running HTTPServer with GC\n366: - **WHEN** server shuts down\n367: - **THEN** `gc.Stop()` SHALL be called\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ### Requirement: Unit tests for GarbageCollector\n372: \n373: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for GC behavior.\n374: \n375: #### Scenario: TestNewGarbageCollector\n376: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n377: - **WHEN** running tests\n378: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n379:   - Constructor returns valid instance\n380:   - Custom interval and timeout are set correctly\n381: \n382: #### Scenario: TestNewGarbageCollector_DefaultInterval\n383: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n384: - **WHEN** calling `NewGarbageCollector(manager, 0, 0, logger)`\n385: - **THEN** default values SHALL be applied:\n386:   - `interval` = `GarbageCollectorInterval`\n387:   - `onceTimeout` = `2 * time.Minute`\n388: \n389: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_StartStop\n390: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n391: - **WHEN** running tests\n392: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n393:   - `Start()` launches goroutine\n394:   - `Stop()` completes without hanging\n395:   - Goroutine exits cleanly\n396: \n397: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Expired\n398: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n399: - **WHEN** running tests with expired sandbox\n400: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n401:   - Expired sandbox is deleted\n402:   - Active sandbox remains\n403: \n404: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Inactive\n405: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n406: - **WHEN** running tests with inactive sandbox\n407: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n408:   - Inactive sandbox (LastActivity > idleTimeout ago) is deleted\n409:   - Active sandbox remains\n410: \n411: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Limit\n412: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n413: - **WHEN** running tests with 20 expired sandboxes\n414: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n415:   - At most `GCBatchSize=16` sandboxes are deleted per cycle\n416: \n417: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_ContinueOnError\n418: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n419: - **WHEN** running tests\n420: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n421:   - All sandboxes are processed even if some deletions fail\n422: \n423: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_GetStats\n424: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n425: - **WHEN** running tests\n426: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n427:   - `GetStats()` returns correct interval, timeout, idleTimeout\n428:   - `SetIdleTimeout()` updates stats correctly\n429: \n430: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_ConcurrentRunOnce\n431: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n432: - **WHEN** running tests with concurrent `runOnce` calls\n433: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n434:   - Store handles concurrent access safely\n435:   - No race conditions occur\n436: \n437: ---\n438: \n439: ### Requirement: Integration tests for GC\n440: \n441: The system SHALL have integration tests verifying GC with lifecycle manager.\n442: \n443: #### Scenario: Full GC flow test\n444: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n445: - **WHEN** running tests\n446: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n447:   - GC deletes expired sandboxes\n448:   - Store is updated after deletion\n449:   - Multiple GC cycles process remaining sandboxes\n450: \n451: ---\n452: \n453: ### Requirement: Error handling\n454: \n455: The system SHALL handle errors gracefully in GC operations.\n456: \n457: #### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes error\n458: - **GIVEN** `runOnce` execution\n459: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` returns error\n460: - **THEN** `gc.logger.Error(\"failed to list expired sandboxes\", \"err\", err)` SHALL be called\n461: - AND `runOnce` SHALL return error\n462: \n463: #### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes error\n464: - **GIVEN** `runOnce` execution\n465: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes` returns error\n466: - **THEN** `gc.logger.Error(\"failed to list inactive sandboxes\", \"err\", err)` SHALL be called\n467: - AND `runOnce` SHALL return error\n468: \n469: #### Scenario: DeleteSandbox NotFound handling\n470: - **GIVEN** a sandbox already deleted\n471: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandbox` returns `NotFoundError`\n472: - **THEN** error SHALL be silently ignored\n473: - AND GC SHALL continue to next sandbox\n474: \n475: ---\n476: \n477: ### Requirement: File structure\n478: \n479: The system SHALL organize GC files correctly.\n480: \n481: #### Scenario: garbage_collector.go location\n482: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n483: - **WHEN** listing files\n484: - **THEN** `garbage_collector.go` SHALL exist with:\n485:   - `GarbageCollector` struct\n486:   - `NewGarbageCollector` constructor\n487:   - `Start`, `Stop`, `runLoop`, `runOnce` methods\n488:   - `SetIdleTimeout`, `getIdleTimeout`, `GetStats` methods\n489:   - `GCBatchSize` constant\n490:   - `GarbageCollectorStats` struct\n491: \n492: #### Scenario: garbage_collector_test.go location\n493: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n494: - **WHEN** listing files\n495: - **THEN** `garbage_collector_test.go` SHALL exist with unit tests\n496: \n497: #### Scenario: store.go with GC methods\n498: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go`\n499: - **WHEN** reading file\n500: - **THEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` SHALL be implemented\n501: \n502: #### Scenario: types.go with Store interface\n503: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n504: - **WHEN** reading `Store` interface\n505: - **THEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` SHALL be declared\n506: \n507: ---\n508: \n509: ### Requirement: LifecycleConfig integration\n510: \n511: The system SHALL use LifecycleConfig for GC configuration.\n512: \n513: #### Scenario: LifecycleConfig GC fields\n514: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n515: - **WHEN** reading `LifecycleConfig`\n516: - **THEN** struct SHALL contain:\n517:   - `GCInterval time.Duration`\n518:   - `GCOnceTimeout time.Duration`\n519:   - `DefaultIdleTimeout time.Duration`\n520: \n521: #### Scenario: DefaultLifecycleConfig GC defaults\n522: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n523: - **WHEN** calling `DefaultLifecycleConfig()`\n524: - **THEN** returned config SHALL have:\n525:   - `GCInterval` = `GarbageCollectorInterval` (2 minutes)\n526:   - `GCOnceTimeout` = `2 * time.Minute`\n527:   - `DefaultIdleTimeout` = `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` (15 minutes)\n528: \n529: ---\n530: \n531: ## Implementation Files\n532: \n533: | File | Purpose |\n534: |------|---------|\n535: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | GarbageCollector implementation with Start/Stop/runOnce |\n536: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` | Unit tests for GC behavior |\n537: | `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go` | ListExpiredSandboxes/ListInactiveSandboxes implementations |\n538: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` | Store interface extensions, DeletionReason constants |\n539: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` | determineDeletionReason, LifecycleConfig GC fields |\n540: | `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | GarbageCollectorInterval, DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout constants |\n541: \n542: ---\n543: \n544: ## Dependencies\n545: \n546: | Package | Purpose |\n547: |---------|---------|\n548: | `context` | Context with timeout for GC cycles |\n549: | `sync` | WaitGroup, RWMutex for concurrency |\n550: | `time` | Duration, Ticker, Now for timing |\n551: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo struct |\n552: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apierrors` | IsNotFound error checking |\n553: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | DeleteOptions |\n554: \n555: ---\n556: \n557: ## GC Flow Diagram\n558: \n559: ```\n560: GarbageCollector\n561: │\n562: ├── Start()\n563: │   └── wg.Add(1)\n564: │   └── go runLoop()\n565: │       ├── runOnce(ctx) [immediate]\n566: │       ├── ticker := NewTicker(interval)\n567: │       ├── select { stopCh, ticker.C }\n568: │       │   ├── ticker.C → runOnce(ctx)\n569: │       │   └── stopCh → return\n570: │       └── wg.Done()\n571: │\n572: ├── Stop()\n573: │   ├── close(stopCh)\n574: │   └── wg.Wait()\n575: │\n576: └── runOnce(ctx)\n577:     ├── ctx, cancel := WithTimeout(ctx, onceTimeout)\n578:     ├── expired := ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, now, GCBatchSize)\n579:     ├── inactiveBefore := now.Add(-idleTimeout)\n580:     ├── inactive := ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, inactiveBefore, GCBatchSize)\n581:     ├── for sb in expired + inactive:\n582:     │   ├── DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID)\n583:     │   ├── reason := determineDeletionReason(sb, now, idleTimeout)\n584:     │   └── logger.Info(\"gc deleted sandbox\", ...)\n585:     └── return nil\n586: ```\n587: \n588: ---\n589: \n590: ## Configuration Values\n591: \n592: | Parameter | Default | Configurable | Source |\n593: |-----------|---------|--------------|--------|\n594: | `interval` | 2m | Yes | `NewGarbageCollector` param |\n595: | `onceTimeout` | 2m | Yes | `NewGarbageCollector` param |\n596: | `idleTimeout` | 15m | Yes (runtime) | `SetIdleTimeout` |\n597: | `batchSize` | 16 | No (const) | `GCBatchSize` |\n598: \n599: ---\n600: \n601: ## Deletion Reasons\n602: \n603: | Reason | Condition | Description |\n604: |--------|-----------|-------------|\n605: | `IdleTimeout` | `LastActivity + idleTimeout < now` AND `ExpiresAt > now` | Sandbox inactive for too long |\n606: | `MaxDurationReached` | `ExpiresAt < now` | Sandbox exceeded maximum TTL |\n607: | `UserRequest` | Neither above | Fallback for manual deletion |\n608: \n609: ---\n610: \n611: ## Validation Checklist\n612: \n613: - [ ] GarbageCollector struct defined with all required fields\n614: - [ ] NewGarbageCollector constructor with default fallbacks\n615: - [ ] Start() launches background goroutine\n616: - [ ] Stop() signals shutdown and waits for completion\n617: - [ ] runLoop uses ticker for periodic execution\n618: - [ ] runOnce has context timeout protection\n619: - [ ] ListExpiredSandboxes queries expired by ExpiresAt\n620: - [ ] ListInactiveSandboxes queries inactive by LastActivity\n621: - [ ] Batch limit (GCBatchSize=16) enforced per query\n622: - [ ] NotFound errors silently ignored\n623: - [ ] Deletion errors logged but don't stop cycle\n624: - [ ] determineDeletionReason categorizes deletions correctly\n625: - [ ] SetIdleTimeout runtime configuration supported\n626: - [ ] GetStats returns current configuration\n627: - [ ] idleMu protects concurrent idleTimeout access\n628: - [ ] Store interface includes GC query methods\n629: - [ ] MemoryStore implements GC query methods\n630: - [ ] LifecycleConfig includes GC parameters\n631: - [ ] DefaultLifecycleConfig provides GC defaults\n632: - [ ] Unit tests cover expired/inactive/batch scenarios\n633: - [ ] Unit tests cover concurrent safety\n634: - [ ] Integration tests verify full GC flow\n635: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n636: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n637: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n\n(End of file - total 637 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the Sandbox Garbage Collector that periodically scans and deletes expired and idle sandboxes. The GC runs as a background goroutine with configurable intervals, enforces TTL via `ExpiresAt` timestamps, handles idle timeout cleanup via `LastActivity`, and limits batch operations to prevent cluster overload.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: GarbageCollector type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `GarbageCollector` as a background process for periodic sandbox cleanup.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775864816398,"end":1775864816423}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864816427,"sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","part":{"id":"prt_d79ca9f89001ciE1szf75Pi2yJ","messageID":"msg_d79ca7f24001sR3XA6SUiDCUPb","sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-371340925d994d0fb044ef29adabd79b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** L\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the Kubernetes Reconciler controller that watches AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources, maintains desired state by managing sandbox pods, updates resource status conditions, and integrates with the informer framework from the generated client-go library.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Reconciler type definition\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define `Reconciler` as a Kubernetes controller for reconciling AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Reconciler struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `Reconciler` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `client clientset.Interface` for typed Kubernetes API access (from `client-go/clientset/versioned`)\n26:   - `kubeClient kubernetes.Interface` for core Kubernetes API\n27:   - `store Store` for sandbox state persistence\n28:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n29:   - `namespace string` for default namespace\n30:   - `scheme *runtime.Scheme` for encoding/decoding resources\n31:   - `recorder record.EventRecorder` for Kubernetes events\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: NewReconciler constructor\n34: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n35: - **WHEN** calling `NewReconciler(client clientset.Interface, kubeClient kubernetes.Interface, store Store, logger Logger, namespace string, scheme *runtime.Scheme, recorder record.EventRecorder)`\n36: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*Reconciler` with all fields initialized\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Informer integration\n41: \n42: The system SHALL use informers from client-go library to watch custom resources.\n43: \n44: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime informer setup\n45: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n46: - **WHEN** initializing the reconciler\n47: - **THEN** `SharedInformerFactory` from `client-go/informers/externalversions` SHALL be used\n48: - AND `f.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()` SHALL be accessed for AgentRuntime watching\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter informer setup\n51: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n52: - **WHEN** initializing the reconciler\n53: - **THEN** `SharedInformerFactory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Informer()` SHALL be accessed for CodeInterpreter watching\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Informer event handlers\n56: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter informers\n57: - **WHEN** setting up event handlers\n58: - **THEN** `AddFunc`, `UpdateFunc`, `DeleteFunc` SHALL be registered on each informer\n59: - AND each handler SHALL call `Reconciler.Reconcile(ctx, key)` with the resource key\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Informer Start\n62: - **GIVEN** a configured `SharedInformerFactory`\n63: - **WHEN** calling `factory.Start(stopCh)`\n64: - **THEN** all informers SHALL begin watching resources\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: WaitForCacheSync\n67: - **GIVEN** a started informer factory\n68: - **WHEN** calling `factory.WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)`\n69: - **THEN** it SHALL return `map[reflect.Type]bool` indicating sync status\n70: - AND all types SHALL be `true` before reconciliation begins\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ### Requirement: Reconcile method\n75: \n76: The system SHALL implement the Reconcile method to process resource changes.\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Reconcile method signature\n79: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n80: - **WHEN** reading the `Reconcile` method\n81: - **THEN** it SHALL have signature `Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req reconcile.Request) (reconcile.Result, error)`\n82: - AND SHALL implement `reconcile.Reconciler` interface from `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime`\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: Reconcile parses request key\n85: - **GIVEN** a `reconcile.Request` with `Namespace=\"default\"` and `Name=\"my-runtime\"`\n86: - **WHEN** processing the reconcile request\n87: - **THEN** the reconciler SHALL use `req.Namespace` and `req.Name` to fetch the resource\n88: \n89: #### Scenario: Reconcile fetches AgentRuntime\n90: - **GIVEN** a reconcile request for an AgentRuntime\n91: - **WHEN** processing the request\n92: - **THEN** `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})` SHALL be called\n93: - AND the returned `AgentRuntime` SHALL be used for reconciliation\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: Reconcile fetches CodeInterpreter\n96: - **GIVEN** a reconcile request for a CodeInterpreter\n97: - **WHEN** processing the request\n98: - **THEN** `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})` SHALL be called\n99: - AND the returned `CodeInterpreter` SHALL be used for reconciliation\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: Reconcile handles not found\n102: - **GIVEN** a reconcile request for a deleted resource\n103: - **WHEN** `Get` returns `IsNotFound` error\n104: - **THEN** reconciliation SHALL return `reconcile.Result{}` with no error\n105: - AND cleanup logic SHALL be triggered if needed\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: Status update\n110: \n111: The system SHALL update status conditions on AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources.\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Update AgentRuntime status\n114: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with updated conditions\n115: - **WHEN** calling status update\n116: - **THEN** `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).UpdateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})` SHALL be called\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Update CodeInterpreter status\n119: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with updated conditions\n120: - **WHEN** calling status update\n121: - **THEN** `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).UpdateStatus(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.UpdateOptions{})` SHALL be called\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Set Ready condition\n124: - **GIVEN** a runtime that is ready to serve\n125: - **WHEN** updating status\n126: - **THEN** condition `ConditionTypeReady` SHALL be set with:\n127:   - `Type: \"Ready\"`\n128:   - `Status: metav1.ConditionTrue`\n129:   - `Reason: ConditionReasonRunning`\n130:   - `Message: \"Runtime is ready\"`\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Set Progressing condition\n133: - **GIVEN** a runtime being created or updated\n134: - **WHEN** updating status\n135: - **THEN** condition `ConditionTypeProgressing` SHALL be set with:\n136:   - `Type: \"Progressing\"`\n137:   - `Status: metav1.ConditionTrue`\n138:   - `Reason: ConditionReasonCreating` or `ConditionReasonUpdating`\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: Set Degraded condition\n141: - **GIVEN** a runtime with errors\n142: - **WHEN** updating status\n143: - **THEN** condition `ConditionTypeDegraded` SHALL be set with:\n144:   - `Type: \"Degraded\"`\n145:   - `Status: metav1.ConditionTrue`\n146:   - `Reason: ConditionReasonError`\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Set Available condition\n149: - **GIVEN** a runtime with active pods\n150: - **WHEN** updating status\n151: - **THEN** condition `ConditionTypeAvailable` SHALL be set with:\n152:   - `Type: \"Available\"`\n153:   - `Status: metav1.ConditionTrue`\n154:   - `Reason: ConditionReasonRunning`\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ### Requirement: Lister usage\n159: \n160: The system SHALL use listers from client-go for efficient resource lookup.\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime lister\n163: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n164: - **WHEN** using the AgentRuntime lister\n165: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeLister` from `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1` SHALL be used\n166: - AND `lister.AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(name)` SHALL return cached AgentRuntime\n167: \n168: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter lister\n169: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n170: - **WHEN** using the CodeInterpreter lister\n171: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreterLister` from `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1` SHALL be used\n172: - AND `lister.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(name)` SHALL return cached CodeInterpreter\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Pod lister for sandbox lookup\n175: - **GIVEN** a reconciler looking for sandbox pods\n176: - **WHEN** searching for pods owned by a runtime\n177: - **THEN** `corev1listers.PodLister` SHALL be used\n178: - AND `lister.Pods(namespace).List(selector)` SHALL return pods matching label selector\n179: \n180: ---\n181: \n182: ### Requirement: Warm pool reconciler for CodeInterpreter\n183: \n184: The system SHALL maintain warm pool pods for CodeInterpreter resources.\n185: \n186: #### Scenario: Warm pool size check\n187: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `WarmPoolSize=5`\n188: - **WHEN** reconciling\n189: - **THEN** the reconciler SHALL count existing warm pool pods\n190: - AND pods with annotation `AnnotationKeyWarmPoolMember=\"true\"` SHALL be counted\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: Create warm pool pod\n193: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `WarmPoolSize > currentWarmPoolCount`\n194: - **WHEN** reconciling\n195: - **THEN** new warm pool pods SHALL be created\n196: - AND annotation `AnnotationKeyWarmPoolMember` SHALL be set to `\"true\"`\n197: - AND label `LabelKeyOwnerRuntime` SHALL be set to CodeInterpreter name\n198: - AND label `LabelKeyOwnerKind` SHALL be set to `\"CodeInterpreter\"`\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Delete excess warm pool pods\n201: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `WarmPoolSize < currentWarmPoolCount`\n202: - **WHEN** reconciling\n203: - **THEN** excess warm pool pods SHALL be deleted\n204: - AND pods SHALL be selected based on oldest creation timestamp\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Warm pool pod spec\n207: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter template\n208: - **WHEN** creating warm pool pod\n209: - **THEN** pod spec SHALL be derived from `CodeInterpreter.Spec.Template`\n210: - AND `Image` SHALL be from `Template.Image`\n211: - AND `RuntimeClassName` SHALL be from `Template.RuntimeClassName` if set\n212: \n213: ---\n214: \n215: ### Requirement: Event recording\n216: \n217: The system SHALL record Kubernetes events for resource lifecycle.\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: Record created event\n220: - **GIVEN** a newly created AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\n221: - **WHEN** reconciliation succeeds\n222: - **THEN** `recorder.Event(object, \"Normal\", \"Created\", \"Runtime created successfully\")` SHALL be called\n223: \n224: #### Scenario: Record Updated event\n225: - **GIVEN** an updated AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\n226: - **WHEN** reconciliation succeeds\n227: - **THEN** `recorder.Event(object, \"Normal\", \"Updated\", \"Runtime updated successfully\")` SHALL be called\n228: \n229: #### Scenario: Record Error event\n230: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation error\n231: - **WHEN** error occurs\n232: - **THEN** `recorder.Event(object, \"Warning\", \"Error\", errorMessage)` SHALL be called\n233: \n234: #### Scenario: Record SessionStarted event\n235: - **GIVEN** a runtime with active session\n236: - **WHEN** session starts\n237: - **THEN** `recorder.Event(object, \"Normal\", \"SessionStarted\", \"Session started\")` SHALL be called\n238: \n239: #### Scenario: Record SessionEnded event\n240: - **GIVEN** a runtime with ended session\n241: - **WHEN** session ends\n242: - **THEN** `recorder.Event(object, \"Normal\", \"SessionEnded\", \"Session ended: <reason>\")` SHALL be called\n243: \n244: ---\n245: \n246: ### Requirement: Reconcile loop control\n247: \n248: The system SHALL control reconcile loop timing and retries.\n249: \n250: #### Scenario: Requeue on error\n251: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation that returns error\n252: - **WHEN** processing result\n253: - **THEN** `reconcile.Result{Requeue: true, RequeueAfter: ReconcileErrorRetryInterval}` SHALL be returned\n254: - AND default retry interval SHALL be `1 * time.Minute`\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: Requeue for periodic check\n257: - **GIVEN** a successful reconciliation\n258: - **WHEN** periodic status check is needed\n259: - **THEN** `reconcile.Result{RequeueAfter: ReconcilePeriodicInterval}` SHALL be returned\n260: - AND default periodic interval SHALL be `5 * time.Minute`\n261: \n262: #### Scenario: No requeue on completion\n263: - **GIVEN** a resource that is fully reconciled\n264: - **WHEN** no further action is needed\n265: - **THEN** `reconcile.Result{}` SHALL be returned\n266: \n267: ---\n268: \n269: ### Requirement: Controller setup\n270: \n271: The system SHALL provide controller setup and management functions.\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: ControllerManager setup\n274: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller.go`\n275: - **WHEN** reading the setup\n276: - **THEN** `SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager)` SHALL be implemented\n277: - AND SHALL use `ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).For(&runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}).Complete(r)` pattern\n278: \n279: #### Scenario: Watches setup for AgentRuntime\n280: - **GIVEN** controller setup for AgentRuntime\n281: - **WHEN** configuring watches\n282: - **THEN** `For(&runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{})` SHALL be called\n283: - AND `Owns(&corev1.Pod{})` SHALL be called for owned pods\n284: \n285: #### Scenario: Watches setup for CodeInterpreter\n286: - **GIVEN** controller setup for CodeInterpreter\n287: - **WHEN** configuring watches\n288: - **THEN** `For(&runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{})` SHALL be called\n289: - AND `Owns(&corev1.Pod{})` SHALL be called for owned pods\n290: \n291: ---\n292: \n293: ### Requirement: Resource deletion handling\n294: \n295: The system SHALL handle resource deletion gracefully.\n296: \n297: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime deletion\n298: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime being deleted\n299: - **WHEN** reconciling with deletion timestamp set\n300: - **THEN** all sandbox pods owned by the runtime SHALL be deleted\n301: - AND status SHALL be updated with `ConditionReasonDeleting`\n302: \n303: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter deletion\n304: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter being deleted\n305: - **WHEN** reconciling with deletion timestamp set\n306: - **THEN** all sandbox pods and warm pool pods SHALL be deleted\n307: - AND status SHALL be updated with `ConditionReasonDeleting`\n308: \n309: #### Scenario: Deletion cleanup\n310: - **GIVEN** a deleted runtime\n311: - **WHEN** all pods are deleted\n312: - **THEN** store entries SHALL be removed for associated sandboxes\n313: - AND finalizer SHALL be removed if present\n314: \n315: ---\n316: \n317: ### Requirement: Finalizer handling\n318: \n319: The system SHALL use finalizers for cleanup before deletion.\n320: \n321: #### Scenario: Add finalizer on creation\n322: - **GIVEN** a newly created AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\n323: - **WHEN** reconciling for the first time\n324: - **THEN** finalizer `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/finalizer` SHALL be added to metadata.finalizers\n325: \n326: #### Scenario: Process finalizer on deletion\n327: - **GIVEN** a runtime with deletion timestamp and finalizer present\n328: - **WHEN** reconciling\n329: - **THEN** cleanup logic SHALL run first\n330: - AND finalizer SHALL be removed after cleanup succeeds\n331: \n332: #### Scenario: Finalizer removal error handling\n333: - **GIVEN** cleanup that fails\n334: - **WHEN** processing finalizer\n335: - **THEN** finalizer SHALL NOT be removed\n336: - AND reconciliation SHALL requeue with error\n337: \n338: ---\n339: \n340: ### Requirement: Scheme registration\n341: \n342: The system SHALL register custom resource types in the scheme.\n343: \n344: #### Scenario: Scheme registration\n345: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` and `groupversion_info.go`\n346: - **WHEN** setting up the reconciler\n347: - **THEN** `runtimev1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme)` SHALL be called\n348: - AND `corev1.AddToScheme(scheme)` SHALL be called for Pod types\n349: \n350: #### Scenario: Scheme from client-go\n351: - **GIVEN** `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme`\n352: - **WHEN** using the scheme\n353: - **THEN** `Scheme` and `Codecs` SHALL be available from `register.go`\n354: - AND types SHALL be registered for `runtime/v1alpha1`\n355: \n356: ---\n357: \n358: ### Requirement: Concurrent reconciliation safety\n359: \n360: The system SHALL handle concurrent reconciliations safely.\n361: \n362: #### Scenario: Same resource concurrent reconcile\n363: - **GIVEN** two reconcile requests for the same resource\n364: - **WHEN** both execute concurrently\n365: - **THEN** only one SHALL proceed with status update\n366: - AND optimistic locking via `ResourceVersion` SHALL prevent conflicts\n367: \n368: #### Scenario: Conflict retry\n369: - **GIVEN** a status update that returns conflict error\n370: - **WHEN** retrying\n371: - **THEN** the resource SHALL be re-fetched\n372: - AND reconciliation SHALL retry with fresh data\n373: \n374: ---\n375: \n376: ### Requirement: Logger integration\n377: \n378: The system SHALL use structured logging for reconciliation.\n379: \n380: #### Scenario: Reconcile start logging\n381: - **GIVEN** a reconcile request\n382: - **WHEN** starting reconciliation\n383: - **THEN** `logger.Info(\"Reconciling\", \"kind\", kind, \"namespace\", namespace, \"name\", name)` SHALL be called\n384: \n385: #### Scenario: Reconcile error logging\n386: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation error\n387: - **WHEN** error occurs\n388: - **THEN** `logger.Error(err, \"Reconcile failed\", \"kind\", kind, \"namespace\", namespace, \"name\", name)` SHALL be called\n389: \n390: #### Scenario: Reconcile success logging\n391: - **GIVEN** a successful reconciliation\n392: - **WHEN** completing\n393: - **THEN** `logger.Info(\"Reconcile completed\", \"kind\", kind, \"namespace\", namespace, \"name\", name)` SHALL be called\n394: \n395: ---\n396: \n397: ### Requirement: Unit tests for Reconciler\n398: \n399: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for the reconciler.\n400: \n401: #### Scenario: Reconciler creation test\n402: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go`\n403: - **WHEN** running tests\n404: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n405:   - NewReconciler returns valid instance\n406:   - All fields are properly initialized\n407: \n408: #### Scenario: Reconcile AgentRuntime test\n409: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go`\n410: - **WHEN** running tests\n411: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n412:   - AgentRuntime fetch succeeds\n413:   - Status updates are called correctly\n414:   - Conditions are set properly\n415: \n416: #### Scenario: Reconcile CodeInterpreter test\n417: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go`\n418: - **WHEN** running tests\n419: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n420:   - CodeInterpreter fetch succeeds\n421:   - Warm pool pods are created/deleted as needed\n422:   - Status updates are called correctly\n423: \n424: #### Scenario: Not found handling test\n425: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go`\n426: - **WHEN** running tests\n427: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n428:   - NotFound error returns empty result\n429:   - Cleanup is triggered for deleted resources\n430: \n431: #### Scenario: Status conflict test\n432: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go`\n433: - **WHEN** running tests\n434: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n435:   - Conflict error triggers retry\n436:   - Resource is re-fetched on conflict\n437: \n438: ---\n439: \n440: ### Requirement: Integration tests for Reconciler\n441: \n442: The system SHALL have integration tests with fake clients.\n443: \n444: #### Scenario: Full reconciliation flow test\n445: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n446: - **WHEN** running tests\n447: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n448:   - Informer factory starts correctly\n449:   - WaitForCacheSync returns true\n450:   - Reconcile is triggered on resource changes\n451:   - Status is updated correctly\n452: \n453: #### Scenario: Warm pool integration test\n454: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n455: - **WHEN** running tests\n456: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n457:   - Warm pool pods are created to match WarmPoolSize\n458:   - Warm pool pods have correct labels and annotations\n459:   - Excess pods are deleted when WarmPoolSize decreases\n460: \n461: #### Scenario: Deletion integration test\n462: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n463: - **WHEN** running tests\n464: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n465:   - All pods are deleted when runtime is deleted\n466:   - Finalizer is removed after cleanup\n467:   - Store entries are removed\n468: \n469: ---\n470: \n471: ### Requirement: Fake client usage in tests\n472: \n473: The system SHALL use fake clients from client-go library in tests.\n474: \n475: #### Scenario: Fake clientset creation\n476: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go`\n477: - **WHEN** setting up tests\n478: - **THEN** `fake.NewSimpleClientset(objects)` from `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake` SHALL be used\n479: \n480: #### Scenario: Fake typed client\n481: - **GIVEN** test setup\n482: - **WHEN** creating fake typed client\n483: - **THEN** `fake_runtime_client.go`, `fake_agentruntime.go`, `fake_codeinterpreter.go` SHALL be available\n484: \n485: #### Scenario: Fake informer factory\n486: - **GIVEN** test setup\n487: - **WHEN** creating fake informer factory\n488: - **THEN** `informers/externalversions/factory.go` SHALL work with fake client\n489: \n490: ---\n491: \n492: ### Requirement: Constants and defaults\n493: \n494: The system SHALL define reconciler constants and defaults.\n495: \n496: #### Scenario: Reconcile intervals\n497: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n498: - **WHEN** reading constants\n499: - **THEN** `ReconcileErrorRetryInterval` SHALL be `1 * time.Minute`\n500: - AND `ReconcilePeriodicInterval` SHALL be `5 * time.Minute`\n501: \n502: #### Scenario: Finalizer name\n503: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n504: - **WHEN** reading constants\n505: - **THEN** `FinalizerName` SHALL be `\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/finalizer\"`\n506: \n507: ---\n508: \n509: ### Requirement: Directory structure\n510: \n511: The system SHALL organize reconciler files correctly.\n512: \n513: #### Scenario: Reconciler file location\n514: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n515: - **WHEN** listing files\n516: - **THEN** `reconciler.go` SHALL exist with `Reconciler` implementation\n517: \n518: #### Scenario: Reconciler test file location\n519: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n520: - **WHEN** listing files\n521: - **THEN** `reconciler_test.go` SHALL exist with unit tests\n522: \n523: #### Scenario: Controller setup file location\n524: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n525: - **WHEN** listing files\n526: - **THEN** `controller.go` SHALL exist with controller setup functions\n527: \n528: ---\n529: \n530: ## Implementation Files\n531: \n532: | File | Purpose |\n533: |------|---------|\n534: | `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go` | Reconciler implementation |\n535: | `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go` | Reconciler unit tests |\n536: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller.go` | Controller setup and manager integration |\n537: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller_test.go` | Controller setup tests |\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## Dependencies\n542: \n543: | Package | Purpose |\n544: |---------|---------|\n545: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned` | Typed client for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter |\n546: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/informers/externalversions` | SharedInformerFactory |\n547: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1` | AgentRuntimeLister, CodeInterpreterLister |\n548: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Reconciler interface, ControllerManager |\n549: | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Core Kubernetes API client |\n550: | `k8s.io/client-go/tools/record` | EventRecorder |\n551: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Pod types |\n552: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` | Scheme |\n553: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | Conditions, ObjectMeta |\n554: \n555: ---\n556: \n557: ## Client-go Integration Points\n558: \n559: | Component | Source File | Usage |\n560: |-----------|-------------|-------|\n561: | Typed client | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/` | Get, Update, UpdateStatus, Delete |\n562: | Informer factory | `informers/externalversions/factory.go` | Start, WaitForCacheSync |\n563: | AgentRuntime informer | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | Informer(), Lister() |\n564: | CodeInterpreter informer | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | Informer(), Lister() |\n565: | AgentRuntime lister | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | List, Get |\n566: | CodeInterpreter lister | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | List, Get |\n567: | Fake clientset | `clientset/versioned/fake/` | Unit test mock |\n568: | Scheme | `clientset/versioned/scheme/` | Resource encoding |\n569: \n570: ---\n571: \n572: ## Reconcile Result Values\n573: \n574: | Result | Requeue | RequeueAfter | Use Case |\n575: |--------|---------|--------------|----------|\n576: | `{}` | false | 0 | Completed, no further action |\n577: | `{Requeue: true}` | true | 0 | Immediate retry |\n578: | `{RequeueAfter: 1m}` | true | 1m | Error retry with delay |\n579: | `{RequeueAfter: 5m}` | true | 5m | Periodic check |\n580: \n581: ---\n582: \n583: ## Condition Types and Reasons\n584: \n585: | Condition Type | Reason | Status | Description |\n586: |----------------|--------|--------|-------------|\n587: | `Ready` | `Running` | True | Runtime ready to serve |\n588: | `Ready` | `Creating` | False | Runtime being created |\n589: | `Progressing` | `Creating` | True | Creation in progress |\n590: | `Progressing` | `Updating` | True | Update in progress |\n591: | `Available` | `Running` | True | Runtime available |\n592: | `Degraded` | `Error` | True | Runtime has errors |\n593: | `SessionActive` | `SessionStarted` | True | Active session |\n594: | `SessionActive` | `SessionEnded` | False | No active session |\n595: \n596: ---\n597: \n598: ## Event Types\n599: \n600: | Event Type | Reason | Message Pattern |\n601: |------------|--------|-----------------|\n602: | Normal | Created | \"Runtime created successfully\" |\n603: | Normal | Updated | \"Runtime updated successfully\" |\n604: | Normal | SessionStarted | \"Session started\" |\n605: | Normal | SessionEnded | \"Session ended: <reason>\" |\n606: | Warning | Error | \"<error message>\" |\n607: \n608: ---\n609: \n610: ## Warm Pool Labels and Annotations\n611: \n612: | Key | Value | Purpose |\n613: |-----|-------|---------|\n614: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/warm-pool-member` | `\"true\"` | Mark pod as warm pool member |\n615: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime` | `<name>` | Reference to CodeInterpreter |\n616: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-kind` | `\"CodeInterpreter\"` | Owner kind |\n617: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type` | `\"code-interpreter\"` | Sandbox type |\n618: \n619: ---\n620: \n621: ## Validation Checklist\n622: \n623: - [ ] Reconciler struct defined with all required fields\n624: - [ ] NewReconciler constructor initializes all fields\n625: - [ ] Reconcile method implements reconcile.Reconciler interface\n626: - [ ] AgentRuntime informer registered with event handlers\n627: - [ ] CodeInterpreter informer registered with event handlers\n628: - [ ] WaitForCacheSync called before reconciliation\n629: - [ ] Status updates use UpdateStatus method\n630: - [ ] Conditions set with proper Type, Status, Reason, Message\n631: - [ ] AgentRuntimeLister used for cached lookups\n632: - [ ] CodeInterpreterLister used for cached lookups\n633: - [ ] Pod lister used for sandbox pod lookup\n634: - [ ] Warm pool pods created/deleted to match WarmPoolSize\n635: - [ ] Events recorded for lifecycle changes\n636: - [ ] Requeue intervals configured appropriately\n637: - [ ] ControllerManager setup implemented\n638: - [ ] Watches configured for CRDs and Pods\n639: - [ ] Finalizer added on creation\n640: - [ ] Finalizer processed on deletion\n641: - [ ] Scheme registered with runtime/v1alpha1 and corev1\n642: - [ ] Conflict retry handles optimistic locking\n643: - [ ] Logger integration with structured logging\n644: - [ ] Fake clientset used in unit tests\n645: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n646: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n647: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n648: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n\n(End of file - total 648 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the Kubernetes Reconciler controller that watches AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources, maintains desired state by managing sandbox pods, updates resource status conditions, and integrates with the informer framework from the generated client-go library.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Reconciler type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `Reconciler` as a Kubernetes controller for reconciling AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775864816396,"end":1775864816426}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864816431,"sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","part":{"id":"prt_d79ca9b17001pycrSNHc0vLmkg","messageID":"msg_d79ca7f24001sR3XA6SUiDCUPb","sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c7398b08783e42b6b961b51b1ec50479","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the Sandbox lifecycle manager that handles sandbox deletion, TTL-based cleanup, idle timeout monitoring, max session duration enforcement, and integration with the Store interface for sandbox state persistence. This includes the garbage collector that runs periodically to clean up expired sandboxes.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: LifecycleManager type definition\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define `LifecycleManager` as a manager for sandbox lifecycle operations.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: LifecycleManager struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `LifecycleManager` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `client clientset.Interface` for Kubernetes API access\n26:   - `kubeClient kubernetes.Interface` for core Kubernetes API\n27:   - `store Store` for sandbox state persistence\n28:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n29:   - `namespace string` for default namespace\n30:   - `gcInterval time.Duration` for garbage collection interval\n31:   - `stopCh chan struct{}` for stopping the manager\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: NewLifecycleManager constructor\n34: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n35: - **WHEN** calling `NewLifecycleManager(client clientset.Interface, kubeClient kubernetes.Interface, store Store, logger Logger, namespace string, gcInterval time.Duration)`\n36: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*LifecycleManager` with all fields initialized\n37: - AND `gcInterval` SHALL default to `GarbageCollectorInterval` if zero\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ### Requirement: Store interface implementation\n42: \n43: The system SHALL implement the `Store` interface for sandbox state persistence.\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: MemoryStore implementation\n46: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go`\n47: - **WHEN** reading the `MemoryStore` struct\n48: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain:\n49:   - `mu sync.RWMutex` for thread-safe access\n50:   - `sandboxes map[string]*types.SandboxInfo` keyed by sessionID\n51:   - `expirationIndex map[string]time.Time` keyed by sandboxID for TTL tracking\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: StoreSandbox method\n54: - **GIVEN** a `MemoryStore` instance\n55: - **WHEN** calling `StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo)`\n56: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL be stored keyed by `sandbox.SessionID`\n57: - AND `expirationIndex` SHALL be updated with `sandbox.ExpiresAt`\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: GetSandboxBySessionID method\n60: - **GIVEN** a `MemoryStore` with stored sandboxes\n61: - **WHEN** calling `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string)`\n62: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*types.SandboxInfo` if found\n63: - AND return `NotFoundError` if not found\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: UpdateSandbox method\n66: - **GIVEN** a `MemoryStore` with stored sandboxes\n67: - **WHEN** calling `UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo)`\n68: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL be updated in the store\n69: - AND `expirationIndex` SHALL be updated if `ExpiresAt` changed\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID method\n72: - **GIVEN** a `MemoryStore` with stored sandboxes\n73: - **WHEN** calling `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string)`\n74: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL be removed from `sandboxes` map\n75: - AND the sandbox SHALL be removed from `expirationIndex` map\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: ListSandboxes method\n78: - **GIVEN** a `MemoryStore` with stored sandboxes\n79: - **WHEN** calling `ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context)`\n80: - **THEN** it SHALL return `[]*types.SandboxInfo` with all stored sandboxes\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ### Requirement: LifecycleManager Start method\n85: \n86: The system SHALL start the lifecycle manager with garbage collection loop.\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Start begins garbage collection\n89: - **GIVEN** a `LifecycleManager` instance\n90: - **WHEN** calling `Start(ctx context.Context)`\n91: - **THEN** the garbage collection loop SHALL start\n92: - AND the loop SHALL run at `gcInterval` frequency\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: Stop stops garbage collection\n95: - **GIVEN** a running `LifecycleManager`\n96: - **WHEN** calling `Stop()`\n97: - **THEN** `stopCh` SHALL be closed\n98: - AND the garbage collection loop SHALL stop\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ### Requirement: Garbage collection implementation\n103: \n104: The system SHALL implement garbage collection for expired sandboxes.\n105: \n106: #### Scenario: GC checks expired sandboxes\n107: - **GIVEN** a `LifecycleManager` with `store` containing sandboxes\n108: - **WHEN** the garbage collection runs\n109: - **THEN** it SHALL check `expirationIndex` for expired entries\n110: - AND current time SHALL be compared against `ExpiresAt`\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: GC deletes expired sandbox pod\n113: - **GIVEN** an expired sandbox in the store\n114: - **WHEN** garbage collection runs\n115: - **THEN** `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Delete(ctx, podName, metav1.DeleteOptions{})` SHALL be called\n116: - AND the sandbox SHALL be removed from the store\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: GC handles multiple expired sandboxes\n119: - **GIVEN** multiple expired sandboxes in the store\n120: - **WHEN** garbage collection runs\n121: - **THEN** all expired sandboxes SHALL be deleted in sequence\n122: - AND errors for individual deletions SHALL be logged but not stop the loop\n123: \n124: #### Scenario: GC logs deletion activity\n125: - **GIVEN** a garbage collection deletion\n126: - **WHEN** a sandbox is deleted\n127: - **THEN** `logger.Info` SHALL be called with sandbox ID and reason\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ### Requirement: TTL-based cleanup\n132: \n133: The system SHALL enforce TTL-based cleanup for sandboxes.\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: Default TTL value\n136: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n137: - **WHEN** reading the constants\n138: - **THEN** `DefaultSandboxTTL` SHALL be `8 * time.Hour`\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: Sandbox TTL from runtime spec\n141: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `MaxSessionDuration=4h`\n142: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n143: - **THEN** the sandbox `ExpiresAt` SHALL be `CreatedAt + MaxSessionDuration`\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: Sandbox TTL from CodeInterpreter spec\n146: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `MaxSessionDuration=6h`\n147: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n148: - **THEN** the sandbox `ExpiresAt` SHALL be `CreatedAt + MaxSessionDuration`\n149: \n150: #### Scenario: TTL exceeded triggers deletion\n151: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt` in the past\n152: - **WHEN** garbage collection runs\n153: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL be marked for deletion\n154: - AND deletion reason SHALL be `ConditionReasonMaxDurationReached`\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ### Requirement: Idle timeout enforcement\n159: \n160: The system SHALL enforce idle timeout for sandboxes.\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: Default idle timeout value\n163: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n164: - **WHEN** reading the constants\n165: - **THEN** `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` SHALL be `15 * time.Minute`\n166: \n167: #### Scenario: Idle timeout from runtime spec\n168: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `SessionTimeout=30m`\n169: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n170: - **THEN** the idle timeout SHALL be derived from `SessionTimeout`\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: LastActivity tracking\n173: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod with annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity`\n174: - **WHEN** garbage collection runs\n175: - **THEN** `LastActivity` SHALL be compared against current time\n176: - AND if `current - LastActivity > SessionTimeout`, sandbox SHALL be deleted\n177: \n178: #### Scenario: Idle timeout exceeded triggers deletion\n179: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with no activity for longer than `SessionTimeout`\n180: - **WHEN** garbage collection runs\n181: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL be deleted\n182: - AND deletion reason SHALL be `ConditionReasonIdleTimeout`\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ### Requirement: DeleteSandboxHandler implementation\n187: \n188: The system SHALL implement the sandbox deletion handler.\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: DeleteSandboxHandler struct\n191: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n192: - **WHEN** reading the handler struct\n193: - **THEN** `SandboxHandler` SHALL have method `DeleteSandbox(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) error`\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: DELETE endpoint registration\n196: - **GIVEN** `SandboxHandler.Register(r chi.Router)`\n197: - **WHEN** examining registered routes\n198: - **THEN** `DELETE /api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` SHALL be registered\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox by name\n201: - **GIVEN** a DELETE request to `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}`\n202: - **WHEN** processing the request\n203: - **THEN** the handler SHALL find the pod by sandbox name using label selector\n204: - AND call `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Delete(ctx, podName, metav1.DeleteOptions{})`\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox with grace period\n207: - **GIVEN** a DELETE request with query parameter `gracePeriodSeconds=30`\n208: - **WHEN** processing the request\n209: - **THEN** `DeleteOptions.GracePeriodSeconds` SHALL be set to 30\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox updates store\n212: - **GIVEN** a sandbox being deleted via API\n213: - **WHEN** the pod deletion succeeds\n214: - **THEN** `store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` SHALL be called\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox sets session-end annotation\n217: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being deleted\n218: - **WHEN** the pod is found before deletion\n219: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-end` SHALL be set to current timestamp\n220: - AND the pod SHALL be updated with `Update` call before deletion\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox returns success\n223: - **GIVEN** a successful sandbox deletion\n224: - **WHEN** writing the response\n225: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 200 OK\n226: - AND `Content-Type` SHALL be `\"application/json\"`\n227: - AND body SHALL be `SuccessResponse{Data: {\"deleted\": true, \"sandboxId\": \"<id>\"}}`\n228: \n229: ---\n230: \n231: ### Requirement: DeleteSandboxRequest type\n232: \n233: The system SHALL define request types for sandbox deletion API.\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: DeleteSandboxRequest struct\n236: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n237: - **WHEN** reading the `DeleteSandboxRequest` struct\n238: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n239:   - `Name string` with JSON tag `name` (optional, can use URL path)\n240:   - `Force bool` with JSON tag `force` (optional, force delete)\n241:   - `GracePeriodSeconds int64` with JSON tag `gracePeriodSeconds` (optional)\n242: \n243: ---\n244: \n245: ### Requirement: Session end handling\n246: \n247: The system SHALL properly handle session end transitions.\n248: \n249: #### Scenario: Session-end annotation on deletion\n250: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod with active session\n251: - **WHEN** the sandbox is deleted\n252: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-end` SHALL be set\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: Session-end annotation format\n255: - **GIVEN** a session-end annotation being set\n256: - **WHEN** setting the annotation value\n257: - **THEN** the value SHALL be RFC3339 formatted timestamp\n258: \n259: #### Scenario: Session-end updates pod before deletion\n260: - **GIVEN** a sandbox being deleted with grace period\n261: - **WHEN** updating the pod\n262: - **THEN** the pod SHALL be updated with `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Update(ctx, pod, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`\n263: - AND the deletion SHALL proceed after update\n264: \n265: ---\n266: \n267: ### Requirement: NotFoundError handling\n268: \n269: The system SHALL handle not found errors for sandbox operations.\n270: \n271: #### Scenario: Sandbox not found on delete\n272: - **GIVEN** a DELETE request for non-existent sandbox\n273: - **WHEN** processing the request\n274: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 404 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"NOT_FOUND\"`\n275: - AND `Message` SHALL indicate sandbox not found\n276: \n277: #### Scenario: Sandbox not found in store\n278: - **GIVEN** a `GetSandboxBySessionID` call for non-existent session\n279: - **WHEN** the call executes\n280: - **THEN** `NotFoundError{Resource: \"sandbox\", Name: sessionID}` SHALL be returned\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ### Requirement: Force deletion\n285: \n286: The system SHALL support force deletion of sandboxes.\n287: \n288: #### Scenario: Force delete bypasses grace period\n289: - **GIVEN** a DELETE request with `force=true`\n290: - **WHEN** processing the request\n291: - **THEN** `DeleteOptions.GracePeriodSeconds` SHALL be set to 0\n292: \n293: #### Scenario: Force delete removes finalizers\n294: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod with finalizers\n295: - **WHEN** force deleting\n296: - **THEN** finalizers SHALL be removed before deletion\n297: \n298: ---\n299: \n300: ### Requirement: Deletion validation\n301: \n302: The system SHALL validate deletion requests.\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: Name required for delete\n305: - **GIVEN** a DELETE request without name in path\n306: - **WHEN** processing the request\n307: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 400 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"VALIDATION_ERROR\"`\n308: \n309: ---\n310: \n311: ### Requirement: Lifecycle status tracking\n312: \n313: The system SHALL track sandbox lifecycle status.\n314: \n315: #### Scenario: SandboxInfo status field\n316: - **GIVEN** `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go`\n317: - **WHEN** reading `SandboxInfo`\n318: - **THEN** `Status` field SHALL be present with JSON tag `status`\n319: \n320: #### Scenario: Status values\n321: - **GIVEN** sandbox lifecycle transitions\n322: - **WHEN** updating status\n323: - **THEN** valid values SHALL include:\n324:   - `\"creating\"` - sandbox being created\n325:   - `\"running\"` - sandbox active\n326:   - `\"expiring\"` - sandbox approaching TTL\n327:   - `\"idle\"` - sandbox idle timeout approaching\n328:   - `\"terminating\"` - sandbox being deleted\n329:   - `\"terminated\"` - sandbox deleted\n330: \n331: #### Scenario: Status update on deletion\n332: - **GIVEN** a sandbox being deleted\n333: - **WHEN** deletion begins\n334: - **THEN** status SHALL be updated to `\"terminating\"`\n335: \n336: #### Scenario: Status update after deletion\n337: - **GIVEN** a sandbox deleted successfully\n338: - **WHEN** deletion completes\n339: - **THEN** status SHALL be updated to `\"terminated\"`\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ### Requirement: Error handling for lifecycle operations\n344: \n345: The system SHALL handle Kubernetes API errors during lifecycle operations.\n346: \n347: #### Scenario: Pod deletion error\n348: - **GIVEN** a pod deletion that returns error\n349: - **WHEN** garbage collection or delete handler executes\n350: - **THEN** error SHALL be logged\n351: - AND `InternalError` SHALL be returned for API calls\n352: \n353: #### Scenario: Pod update error before delete\n354: - **GIVEN** a pod update that fails before deletion\n355: - **WHEN** setting session-end annotation\n356: - **THEN** the error SHALL be logged\n357: - AND deletion SHALL proceed anyway (annotation update is non-blocking)\n358: \n359: ---\n360: \n361: ### Requirement: Concurrent deletion safety\n362: \n363: The system SHALL handle concurrent deletion requests safely.\n364: \n365: #### Scenario: Same sandbox deleted concurrently\n366: - **GIVEN** two delete requests for the same sandbox\n367: - **WHEN** both requests execute\n368: - **THEN** only one SHALL succeed\n369: - AND the second SHALL receive 404 Not Found or 409 Conflict\n370: \n371: #### Scenario: Store deletion thread safety\n372: - **GIVEN** `MemoryStore` with concurrent operations\n373: - **WHEN** multiple goroutines access the store\n374: - **THEN** `sync.RWMutex` SHALL protect all map operations\n375: \n376: ---\n377: \n378: ### Requirement: GC interval configuration\n379: \n380: The system SHALL allow configurable garbage collection interval.\n381: \n382: #### Scenario: Default GC interval\n383: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n384: - **WHEN** reading the constants\n385: - **THEN** `GarbageCollectorInterval` SHALL be `2 * time.Minute`\n386: \n387: #### Scenario: Custom GC interval\n388: - **GIVEN** `NewLifecycleManager` with `gcInterval=5m`\n389: - **WHEN** creating the manager\n390: - **THEN** garbage collection SHALL run every 5 minutes\n391: \n392: ---\n393: \n394: ### Requirement: Unit tests for LifecycleManager\n395: \n396: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for lifecycle management.\n397: \n398: #### Scenario: LifecycleManager creation test\n399: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go`\n400: - **WHEN** running tests\n401: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n402:   - NewLifecycleManager returns valid instance\n403:   - Default gcInterval is applied\n404: \n405: #### Scenario: GC loop test\n406: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go`\n407: - **WHEN** running tests\n408: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n409:   - Start begins the GC loop\n410:   - Stop terminates the GC loop\n411: \n412: #### Scenario: TTL cleanup test\n413: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go`\n414: - **WHEN** running tests\n415: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n416:   - Expired sandboxes are detected\n417:   - Expired sandboxes are deleted from store and Kubernetes\n418: \n419: #### Scenario: Idle timeout test\n420: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go`\n421: - **WHEN** running tests\n422: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n423:   - Idle sandboxes are detected\n424:   - Idle sandboxes are deleted\n425: \n426: ---\n427: \n428: ### Requirement: Unit tests for MemoryStore\n429: \n430: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for MemoryStore.\n431: \n432: #### Scenario: Store CRUD test\n433: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go`\n434: - **WHEN** running tests\n435: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n436:   - StoreSandbox stores sandbox correctly\n437:   - GetSandboxBySessionID returns correct sandbox\n438:   - UpdateSandbox updates sandbox correctly\n439:   - DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes sandbox\n440:   - ListSandboxes returns all sandboxes\n441: \n442: #### Scenario: Store concurrency test\n443: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go`\n444: - **WHEN** running tests\n445: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n446:   - Concurrent StoreSandbox operations are safe\n447:   - Concurrent Get and Delete operations are safe\n448: \n449: #### Scenario: NotFound error test\n450: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go`\n451: - **WHEN** running tests\n452: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n453:   - GetSandboxBySessionID returns NotFoundError for missing sandbox\n454: \n455: ---\n456: \n457: ### Requirement: Unit tests for DeleteSandbox handler\n458: \n459: The system SHALL have unit tests for sandbox deletion handler.\n460: \n461: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox success test\n462: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n463: - **WHEN** running tests\n464: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n465:   - DELETE returns 200 on success\n466:   - Pod is deleted from Kubernetes\n467:   - Sandbox is removed from store\n468: \n469: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox not found test\n470: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n471: - **WHEN** running tests\n472: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n473:   - DELETE returns 404 for non-existent sandbox\n474: \n475: #### Scenario: Grace period test\n476: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n477: - **WHEN** running tests\n478: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n479:   - GracePeriodSeconds is applied to DeleteOptions\n480: \n481: #### Scenario: Force delete test\n482: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n483: - **WHEN** running tests\n484: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n485:   - Force=true sets GracePeriodSeconds=0\n486: \n487: ---\n488: \n489: ### Requirement: Integration tests for lifecycle\n490: \n491: The system SHALL have integration tests for lifecycle management.\n492: \n493: #### Scenario: Full lifecycle flow test\n494: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n495: - **WHEN** running tests\n496: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n497:   - Sandbox creation stores in MemoryStore\n498:   - TTL expiration triggers deletion\n499:   - Store reflects deleted sandbox\n500: \n501: #### Scenario: Concurrent lifecycle test\n502: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n503: - **WHEN** running tests\n504: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n505:   - Multiple sandboxes handled concurrently\n506:   - No race conditions\n507: \n508: ---\n509: \n510: ### Requirement: Directory structure\n511: \n512: The system SHALL organize lifecycle files correctly.\n513: \n514: #### Scenario: Lifecycle file location\n515: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n516: - **WHEN** listing files\n517: - **THEN** `lifecycle.go` SHALL exist with `LifecycleManager` implementation\n518: \n519: #### Scenario: Lifecycle test file location\n520: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n521: - **WHEN** listing files\n522: - **THEN** `lifecycle_test.go` SHALL exist with unit tests\n523: \n524: #### Scenario: Store file location\n525: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n526: - **WHEN** listing files\n527: - **THEN** `store.go` SHALL exist with `MemoryStore` implementation\n528: \n529: #### Scenario: Store test file location\n530: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n531: - **WHEN** listing files\n532: - **THEN** `store_test.go` SHALL exist with unit tests\n533: \n534: ---\n535: \n536: ## Implementation Files\n537: \n538: | File | Purpose |\n539: |------|---------|\n540: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` | LifecycleManager implementation |\n541: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go` | LifecycleManager unit tests |\n542: | `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go` | MemoryStore implementation |\n543: | `pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go` | MemoryStore unit tests |\n544: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go` | DeleteSandbox handler (extends AR-005) |\n545: \n546: ---\n547: \n548: ## Dependencies\n549: \n550: | Package | Purpose |\n551: |---------|---------|\n552: | `client-go/clientset/versioned` | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter typed client |\n553: | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Core Kubernetes API client |\n554: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Pod types |\n555: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | ObjectMeta, DeleteOptions |\n556: | `sync` | Thread-safe store operations |\n557: | `time` | TTL and interval handling |\n558: | `context` | Context propagation |\n559: \n560: ---\n561: \n562: ## API Endpoints\n563: \n564: | Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n565: |----------|--------|---------|\n566: | `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` | DELETE | Delete sandbox by name |\n567: \n568: ---\n569: \n570: ## Error Codes\n571: \n572: | Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n573: |------|-------------|-------------|\n574: | `VALIDATION_ERROR` | 400 | Missing or invalid parameters |\n575: | `NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Sandbox not found |\n576: | `INTERNAL_ERROR` | 500 | Kubernetes API error |\n577: | `SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE` | 503 | Lifecycle manager not running |\n578: \n579: ---\n580: \n581: ## Deletion Reasons\n582: \n583: | Reason | Description |\n584: |--------|-------------|\n585: | `IdleTimeout` | Sandbox deleted due to idle timeout exceeded |\n586: | `MaxDurationReached` | Sandbox deleted due to max session duration exceeded |\n587: | `UserRequest` | Sandbox deleted via DELETE API request |\n588: \n589: ---\n590: \n591: ## Annotation Keys for Lifecycle\n592: \n593: | Key | Value Source |\n594: |-----|--------------|\n595: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-end` | Current timestamp on deletion |\n596: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity` | Updated on each activity |\n597: \n598: ---\n599: \n600: ## Sandbox Status Values\n601: \n602: | Status | Description |\n603: |--------|-------------|\n604: | `creating` | Sandbox pod being created |\n605: | `running` | Sandbox active and serving |\n606: | `expiring` | Approaching TTL expiration |\n607: | `idle` | Approaching idle timeout |\n608: | `terminating` | Sandbox being deleted |\n609: | `terminated` | Sandbox deleted |\n610: \n611: ---\n612: \n613: ## Validation Checklist\n614: \n615: - [ ] LifecycleManager struct defined with all required fields\n616: - [ ] NewLifecycleManager constructor initializes all fields\n617: - [ ] MemoryStore implements Store interface\n618: - [ ] StoreSandbox stores sandbox keyed by sessionID\n619: - [ ] GetSandboxBySessionID returns sandbox or NotFoundError\n620: - [ ] UpdateSandbox updates sandbox and expiration index\n621: - [ ] DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes from both maps\n622: - [ ] ListSandboxes returns all sandboxes\n623: - [ ] Start begins garbage collection loop\n624: - [ ] Stop terminates garbage collection loop\n625: - [ ] GC checks expirationIndex for expired entries\n626: - [ ] TTL exceeded triggers deletion with MaxDurationReached reason\n627: - [ ] Idle timeout exceeded triggers deletion with IdleTimeout reason\n628: - [ ] DELETE endpoint registered at `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}`\n629: - [ ] GracePeriodSeconds query parameter applied\n630: - [ ] Force delete sets GracePeriodSeconds=0\n631: - [ ] Session-end annotation set before deletion\n632: - [ ] Store updated on successful deletion\n633: - [ ] NotFound handling for missing sandbox\n634: - [ ] Concurrent deletion handled safely\n635: - [ ] Status tracking for lifecycle transitions\n636: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n637: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n638: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n639: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n\n(End of file - total 639 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the Sandbox lifecycle manager that handles sandbox deletion, TTL-based cleanup, idle timeout monitoring, max session duration enforcement, and integration with the Store interface for sandbox state persistence. This includes the garbage collector that runs periodically to clean up expired sandboxes.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: LifecycleManager type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `LifecycleManager` as a manager for sandbox lifecycle operations.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775864816394,"end":1775864816428}}}}
