{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864909498,"sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","part":{"id":"prt_d79cc0e96001zZMvTWYYww7cMi","messageID":"msg_d79cbf9c5001MQgUCASRI2yrym","sessionID":"ses_286364eb9ffenAm0pp4GOpO95D","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-d53f2512ea58418fa6f3f0cff763ae52","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/agentd`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Implement an idle cleanup controller for Agentd that monitors and cleans up idle agent runtime sessions. This controller tracks session activity timestamps, enforces idle timeout policies, and triggers cleanup operations when agents exceed configured idle thresholds. The controller integrates with the Router's session management and Workload Manager's sandbox lifecycle to ensure efficient resource utilization.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: IdleCleanupController type definition\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define `IdleCleanupController` as a background process for monitoring and cleaning idle agent sessions.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: IdleCleanupController struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `IdleCleanupController` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `store Store` for session state lookup\n26:   - `lifecycleManager *SandboxLifecycleManager` for sandbox deletion delegation\n27:   - `interval time.Duration` for cleanup check interval\n28:   - `idleTimeout time.Duration` for idle threshold\n29:   - `stopCh chan struct{}` for graceful shutdown signal\n30:   - `wg sync.WaitGroup` for goroutine synchronization\n31:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: NewIdleCleanupController constructor\n34: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n35: - **WHEN** calling `NewIdleCleanupController(store, lifecycleManager, interval, idleTimeout, logger)`\n36: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*IdleCleanupController` with:\n37:   - `interval` defaulted to `DefaultIdleCleanupInterval` (1 minute) if zero\n38:   - `idleTimeout` defaulted to `DefaultIdleTimeout` (15 minutes) if zero\n39:   - `stopCh` initialized as `make(chan struct{})`\n40: \n41: ---\n42: \n43: ### Requirement: IdleCleanupController lifecycle\n44: \n45: The system SHALL provide Start/Stop lifecycle methods for the cleanup background goroutine.\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: Start launches cleanup loop\n48: - **GIVEN** an `IdleCleanupController` instance\n49: - **WHEN** calling `ctrl.Start()`\n50: - **THEN** `ctrl.wg.Add(1)` SHALL be called\n51: - AND `ctrl.runLoop()` SHALL be launched as a goroutine\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: Stop signals shutdown\n54: - **GIVEN** a running `IdleCleanupController`\n55: - **WHEN** calling `ctrl.Stop()`\n56: - **THEN** `close(ctrl.stopCh)` SHALL be called\n57: - AND `ctrl.wg.Wait()` SHALL block until goroutine completes\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: runLoop initial execution\n60: - **GIVEN** a started `IdleCleanupController`\n61: - **WHEN** `runLoop` begins\n62: - **THEN** `ctrl.runOnce(context.Background())` SHALL be called immediately\n63: - AND ticker SHALL be created with `time.NewTicker(ctrl.interval)`\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: runLoop ticker-driven execution\n66: - **GIVEN** a running `runLoop`\n67: - **WHEN** ticker fires\n68: - **THEN** `ctrl.runOnce(context.Background())` SHALL be called\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: runLoop stops on stopCh\n71: - **GIVEN** a running `runLoop`\n72: - **WHEN** `stopCh` receives signal\n73: - **THEN** `ctrl.logger.Info(\"idle cleanup controller stopped\")` SHALL be called\n74: - AND goroutine SHALL return after `ticker.Stop()` and `ctrl.wg.Done()`\n75: \n76: ---\n77: \n78: ### Requirement: runOnce cleanup cycle\n79: \n80: The system SHALL implement `runOnce` for a single idle cleanup check cycle.\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: runOnce lists active sessions\n83: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n84: - **WHEN** calling `runOnce(ctx)`\n85: - **THEN** `ctrl.store.ListSessions(ctx)` SHALL be called\n86: - AND all sessions SHALL be iterated for idle check\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: runOnce checks session idle status\n89: - **GIVEN** a session with `LastActivity` timestamp\n90: - **WHEN** evaluating idle status\n91: - **THEN** `time.Now().Sub(session.LastActivity)` SHALL be computed\n92: - AND session SHALL be marked idle if `duration > ctrl.idleTimeout`\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: runOnce skips zero LastActivity\n95: - **GIVEN** a session with `LastActivity.IsZero() == true`\n96: - **WHEN** evaluating idle status\n97: - **THEN** session SHALL be skipped (not marked idle)\n98: - AND no cleanup SHALL be triggered\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: runOnce triggers cleanup for idle session\n101: - **GIVEN** an idle session with `duration > idleTimeout`\n102: - **WHEN** `runOnce` processes it\n103: - **THEN** `ctrl.lifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, session.SessionID)` SHALL be called\n104: - AND deletion reason SHALL be `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`\n105: \n106: #### Scenario: runOnce logs cleanup action\n107: - **GIVEN** a successfully cleaned idle session\n108: - **WHEN** cleanup completes\n109: - **THEN** `ctrl.logger.Info(\"idle cleanup deleted session\", \"sessionID\", ..., \"idleDuration\", ..., \"reason\", \"IdleTimeout\")` SHALL be called\n110: \n111: #### Scenario: runOnce handles NotFound error\n112: - **GIVEN** a session that no longer exists in sandbox\n113: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandbox` returns `NotFoundError`\n114: - **THEN** error SHALL be ignored with `continue`\n115: - AND cleanup SHALL proceed for remaining sessions\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: runOnce logs cleanup failure\n118: - **GIVEN** a cleanup that fails (not NotFound)\n119: - **WHEN** error occurs\n120: - **THEN** `ctrl.logger.Error(\"idle cleanup failed\", \"sessionID\", ..., \"err\", ...)` SHALL be called\n121: - AND processing SHALL continue for remaining sessions\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ### Requirement: Runtime configuration support\n126: \n127: The system SHALL support runtime configuration of idle timeout.\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: SetIdleTimeout method\n130: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n131: - **WHEN** calling `ctrl.SetIdleTimeout(30 * time.Minute)`\n132: - **THEN** `ctrl.idleTimeout` SHALL be updated atomically\n133: - AND subsequent cleanup cycles SHALL use new timeout\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: GetIdleTimeout method\n136: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n137: - **WHEN** calling `ctrl.GetIdleTimeout()`\n138: - **THEN** current `idleTimeout` value SHALL be returned\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: GetStats method\n141: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n142: - **WHEN** calling `ctrl.GetStats()`\n143: - **THEN** `IdleCleanupStats` SHALL be returned with:\n144:   - `Interval`: current cleanup check interval\n145:   - `IdleTimeout`: current idle threshold\n146:   - `LastCleanupTime`: timestamp of last cleanup cycle\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: IdleCleanupStats struct\n149: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n150: - **WHEN** reading `IdleCleanupStats`\n151: - **THEN** struct SHALL contain:\n152:   - `Interval time.Duration`\n153:   - `IdleTimeout time.Duration`\n154:   - `LastCleanupTime time.Time`\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ### Requirement: Default constants\n159: \n160: The system SHALL define default timeout constants for idle cleanup.\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: DefaultIdleCleanupInterval constant\n163: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/defaults.go`\n164: - **WHEN** reading constants\n165: - **THEN** `DefaultIdleCleanupInterval` SHALL be `1 * time.Minute`\n166: \n167: #### Scenario: DefaultIdleTimeout constant\n168: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/defaults.go`\n169: - **WHEN** reading constants\n170: - **THEN** `DefaultIdleTimeout` SHALL be `15 * time.Minute`\n171: \n172: ---\n173: \n174: ### Requirement: Store interface usage\n175: \n176: The system SHALL use Store interface for session state operations.\n177: \n178: #### Scenario: Store ListSessions method\n179: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n180: - **WHEN** listing sessions for cleanup\n181: - **THEN** `store.ListSessions(ctx)` SHALL be called\n182: - AND result SHALL return `[]*types.SandboxInfo` with active sessions\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: Session LastActivity field usage\n185: - **GIVEN** `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go`\n186: - **WHEN** checking session idle status\n187: - **THEN** `SandboxInfo.LastActivity` SHALL be used for idle calculation\n188: - AND `LastActivity` SHALL be `time.Time` type\n189: \n190: ---\n191: \n192: ### Requirement: Integration with SandboxLifecycleManager\n193: \n194: The system SHALL delegate sandbox deletion to SandboxLifecycleManager.\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: DeleteSandbox delegation\n197: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n198: - **WHEN** triggering cleanup for idle session\n199: - **THEN** `lifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sessionID)` SHALL be called\n200: - AND deletion SHALL handle K8s sandbox CR and store cleanup\n201: \n202: #### Scenario: DeleteSandbox handles Sandbox and SandboxClaim\n203: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n204: - **WHEN** deletion executes\n205: - **THEN** `SandboxGVR` (agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/sandboxes) SHALL be deleted\n206: - AND `SandboxClaimGVR` SHALL be deleted if `Kind == SandboxClaimKind`\n207: \n208: ---\n209: \n210: ### Requirement: Deletion reason tracking\n211: \n212: The system SHALL categorize deletion reasons for idle cleanup.\n213: \n214: #### Scenario: DeletionReasonIdleTimeout constant\n215: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n216: - **WHEN** reading constants\n217: - **THEN** `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout` SHALL be `\"IdleTimeout\"`\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: Log deletion reason\n220: - **GIVEN** idle cleanup deletion\n221: - **WHEN** logging cleanup action\n222: - **THEN** reason SHALL be logged as `\"IdleTimeout\"`\n223: - AND idle duration SHALL be logged for observability\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ### Requirement: Concurrent safety\n228: \n229: The system SHALL handle concurrent access safely.\n230: \n231: #### Scenario: Single goroutine cleanup\n232: - **GIVEN** `IdleCleanupController` design\n233: - **WHEN** cleanup is running\n234: - **THEN** `runOnce` SHALL only be called from single `runLoop` goroutine\n235: - AND no concurrent `runOnce` calls SHALL occur from controller itself\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: Store concurrent access protection\n238: - **GIVEN** `MemoryStore` with `sync.RWMutex`\n239: - **WHEN** concurrent `ListSessions` and session updates\n240: - **THEN** `sync.RWMutex` SHALL prevent race conditions\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ### Requirement: Logger integration\n245: \n246: The system SHALL use structured logging for cleanup operations.\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: Cleanup start logging\n249: - **GIVEN** a cleanup cycle starting\n250: - **WHEN** `runOnce` begins\n251: - **THEN** `ctrl.logger.Info(\"idle cleanup cycle started\")` MAY be called\n252: \n253: #### Scenario: Cleanup completion logging\n254: - **GIVEN** a cleanup cycle completing\n255: - **WHEN** `runOnce` finishes\n256: - **THEN** `ctrl.logger.Info(\"idle cleanup cycle completed\", \"cleanedCount\", count)` SHALL be called\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: Cleanup error logging\n259: - **GIVEN** a cleanup that fails\n260: - **WHEN** error occurs\n261: - **THEN** `ctrl.logger.Error(\"idle cleanup failed\", \"sessionID\", ..., \"err\", ...)` SHALL be called\n262: \n263: ---\n264: \n265: ### Requirement: Unit tests for IdleCleanupController\n266: \n267: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for idle cleanup behavior.\n268: \n269: #### Scenario: TestNewIdleCleanupController\n270: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n271: - **WHEN** running tests\n272: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n273:   - Constructor returns valid instance\n274:   - Custom interval and timeout are set correctly\n275:   - Default values are applied when parameters are zero\n276: \n277: #### Scenario: TestIdleCleanupController_StartStop\n278: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n279: - **WHEN** running tests\n280: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n281:   - `Start()` launches goroutine\n282:   - `Stop()` completes without hanging\n283:   - Goroutine exits cleanly\n284: \n285: #### Scenario: TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_IdleSession\n286: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n287: - **WHEN** running tests with idle session\n288: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n289:   - Idle session (LastActivity > idleTimeout ago) is cleaned\n290:   - Active session remains\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_ZeroLastActivity\n293: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n294: - **WHEN** running tests with session having zero LastActivity\n295: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n296:   - Session is skipped (not cleaned)\n297: \n298: #### Scenario: TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_ContinueOnError\n299: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n300: - **WHEN** running tests\n301: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n302:   - All sessions are processed even if some cleanups fail\n303:   - NotFound errors are silently ignored\n304: \n305: #### Scenario: TestIdleCleanupController_SetIdleTimeout\n306: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n307: - **WHEN** running tests\n308: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n309:   - `SetIdleTimeout()` updates threshold correctly\n310:   - `GetIdleTimeout()` returns updated value\n311:   - `GetStats()` reflects updated timeout\n312: \n313: ---\n314: \n315: ### Requirement: Package structure\n316: \n317: The system SHALL organize agentd files correctly.\n318: \n319: #### Scenario: Package doc.go location\n320: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/`\n321: - **WHEN** listing files\n322: - **THEN** `doc.go` SHALL exist with package documentation\n323: \n324: #### Scenario: idle_cleanup.go location\n325: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/`\n326: - **WHEN** listing files\n327: - **THEN** `idle_cleanup.go` SHALL exist with `IdleCleanupController` implementation\n328: \n329: #### Scenario: idle_cleanup_test.go location\n330: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/`\n331: - **WHEN** listing files\n332: - **THEN** `idle_cleanup_test.go` SHALL exist with unit tests\n333: \n334: #### Scenario: defaults.go location\n335: - **GIVEN** `pkg/agentd/`\n336: - **WHEN** listing files\n337: - **THEN** `defaults.go` SHALL exist with default constants\n338: \n339: ---\n340: \n341: ## Constants Summary\n342: \n343: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n344: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n345: | `DefaultIdleCleanupInterval` | `1 * time.Minute` | `defaults.go` | Default cleanup check interval |\n346: | `DefaultIdleTimeout` | `15 * time.Minute` | `defaults.go` | Default idle threshold for cleanup |\n347: \n348: ---\n349: \n350: ## Dependencies Summary\n351: \n352: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n353: |---------|---------|---------|\n354: | `pkg/workloadmanager` | Internal | `SandboxLifecycleManager`, `Store`, `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout` |\n355: | `pkg/common/types` | Internal | `SandboxInfo` struct with `LastActivity` field |\n356: | `context` | Standard | Context for cleanup operations |\n357: | `sync` | Standard | `WaitGroup` for goroutine synchronization |\n358: | `time` | Standard | Duration, Ticker, Now for timing |\n359: \n360: ---\n361: \n362: ## File Changes Summary\n363: \n364: | File | Action | Description |\n365: |------|--------|-------------|\n366: | `pkg/agentd/doc.go` | Create | Package documentation for agentd module |\n367: | `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` | Create | `IdleCleanupController`, `NewIdleCleanupController`, `Start`, `Stop`, `runLoop`, `runOnce`, `SetIdleTimeout`, `GetIdleTimeout`, `GetStats` |\n368: | `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for idle cleanup controller |\n369: | `pkg/agentd/defaults.go` | Create | `DefaultIdleCleanupInterval`, `DefaultIdleTimeout` constants |\n370: \n371: ---\n372: \n373: ## References\n374: \n375: - `changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md` — Sandbox lifecycle and deletion management\n376: - `changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md` — Sandbox GC garbage collector pattern\n377: - `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` — `SandboxLifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox`\n378: - `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` — GC implementation pattern\n379: - `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` — `SandboxInfo.LastActivity` field\n380: - `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client for sandbox operations\n381: \n382: ---\n383: \n384: ## Validation Checklist\n385: \n386: - [ ] IdleCleanupController struct defined with all required fields\n387: - [ ] NewIdleCleanupController constructor with default fallbacks\n388: - [ ] Start() launches background goroutine\n389: - [ ] Stop() signals shutdown and waits for completion\n390: - [ ] runLoop uses ticker for periodic execution\n391: - [ ] runOnce checks session idle status via LastActivity\n392: - [ ] Sessions with zero LastActivity skipped\n393: - [ ] Idle sessions trigger DeleteSandbox delegation\n394: - [ ] NotFound errors silently ignored\n395: - [ ] Deletion errors logged but don't stop cycle\n396: - [ ] SetIdleTimeout runtime configuration supported\n397: - [ ] GetStats returns current configuration\n398: - [ ] Default constants defined correctly\n399: - [ ] Store ListSessions method used for session lookup\n400: - [ ] SandboxLifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox used for cleanup\n401: - [ ] DeletionReasonIdleTimeout logged for observability\n402: - [ ] Unit tests cover idle/active/zero scenarios\n403: - [ ] Unit tests cover Start/Stop lifecycle\n404: - [ ] Package structure follows agentcube conventions\n405: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n406: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n407: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n\n(End of file - total 407 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器\n\n**Module:** `pkg/agentd`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement an idle cleanup controller for Agentd that monitors and cleans up idle agent runtime sessions. This controller tracks session activity timestamps, enforces idle timeout policies, and triggers cleanup operations when agents exceed configured idle thresholds. The controller integrates with the Router's session management and Workload Manager's sandbox lifecycle to ensure efficient resource utilization.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: IdleCleanupController type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `IdleCleanupController` as a background process for monitoring and cleaning idle agent sessions.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775864909487,"end":1775864909495}}}}
